impact_achieved_description: seven-bed hospital (primary health center) built at a cost of crores at chhatrutand (mahuda) under baghmara block of district dhanbad. the hospital is ready but no facilities have been made available to the villagers and health workers. for the change of this video, halima ji took it up in the meeting of community health action team dhanbad and then got it published in social media and daily newspapers regarding the demand for restoration of doctors and health facilities. then the health action team dhanbad met the then block head smt. meenakshi gudiya rani and handed over the demand letter. the problem was put before the deputy commissioner dhanbad by the chief. chief minister jharkhand government honorable hemant soren was tweeted through twitter. then on january 17, 2021, a female doctor mrs. anika kujur was posted from ranchi. but after a few days the lady doctor left after giving her resignation letter. the problem before us remained the same. the members of the community health action team dhanbad raised the issue in a meeting again and while urging in the public interest, demanded to restore the doctors and health facilities for the proper operation of the health center. then, on behalf of the jharkhand government, three doctors were reinstated. at present, about 50,000 people are benefiting from this health center.

impact_achieved_description: district chatra block kanhachatti under the health hospital campaign in the primary health center by our community correspondent formed a 10-member campaign team and conducted a survey in the kanha chatti primary health center as per the government guidelines! the problem was the problem of ambulance due to non-availability of ambulance service, about 63 people of kanha chatti primary block were facing a lot of trouble in the sudden incident! regarding this problem, meeting with the team of swasthya hospital abhiyan 2, 3 times, gave an application to the dc of the district and one application to the civil surgeon of the district! a video was also made on the problem of hospital and ambulance vehicle, the video was posted several times on social media with the community and its selected team as well as sent to the mobile of the officer and public representative! the print media of the region also published this news as a result of which a new ambulance vehicle was given to kanhachatti primary health center in collaboration with ntpc chatra. about 63,000 people of this block have been benefited by getting an ambulance vehicle. now, in case of any accident or serious illness, you will be able to get an ambulance free of cost by calling 108!

impact_achieved_description: bokaro district bermo block panchayat armo village gandke beneath tola nadia dhari of jharkhand state, there was a huge water problem for about 150 years. a meeting took place in panchayat bhavan, during the meeting, i wrote an application and submitted it to the block office. after making the video, i contacted mr. maniram murmu through video whatsapp and talked on the phone. i also whatsapp video to surendra soren of the village and went to the block and contacted the block development officer and showed them the video and also contacted the current head and showed them the video and whatsapp, in this way the work started on 2020 21 under the megha water supply scheme by the jharkhand government and now for about 2 months, water is being received in tola below gandke, which is benefiting 280 people of 40 families, they are getting water and they are very happy. 5000 people from 8 villages around people will get water, this work will be completed in 6 months, then everyone will get water. surendra soren, the former headman of maniram murmu village and mrs. katrina hansda, the current headman, block development officer helped me a lot in getting water.

impact_achieved_description: in district-khuti, block-torpa, panchayat-marcha, village-navatoli, 300 people, including 60 families, were facing a lot of trouble for pure water due to the failure of 4 hand pumps for the last 6 months. they are forced to drink a small well in the field. the old woman was also facing problems due to the road not being in good condition. regarding these problems of the villagers, after preparing the application after meeting with the community, on 17/11/22, after submitting the memorandum with the villagers, 300 including 60 families, after 15 days, after 15 days, 4 chapakals were made through continuous efforts through phone. people are getting pure water and now the people of this village are not facing any kind of problem for water.

impact_achieved_description: august main in lohajimi village, electricity went out for fifteen days. due to which the entire 85 families of the village had to face the terror of elephants. there was no electricity in the whole month of august and independence day, 15th august was also celebrated here. the people of the village tried to contact the officials of the vidhut vibhag by phone for 15 days but did not succeed. phir unhone rejan ko sampark kiya. rejan paros ke gaon main rehte hai aur yahan ko logon ko unka samusayik samvadata ke roop main kaam ki ki ki ki ki ki ki ki ki ki ki ki ki ki ki main ki ki ki ki ki ki ki sakte hai. with the guidance of rejan, the gram sabha was immediately convened and a petition was prepared. along with main rejan, immediately along with main video was also made. next day (21st august) rejan aur kuch gaon ke logon ne jakar avedan manu paharia, viduyut supply avar mandal, torpa ko diya sath main video bhi dikhaya aur bataya ki ye online ja raha hai. the officials assured that work will be done to bring electricity immediately. the video will be published the next day till the link is sent to the adhikari. it took almost 24 hours to meet the official, but only the mistry brothers who checked the transformers used to check them. 26th aug.

impact_achieved_description: august main in lohajimi village, electricity went out for fifteen days. due to which the entire 85 families of the village had to face the terror of elephants. there was no electricity in the whole month of august and independence day, 15th august was also celebrated here. the people of the village tried to contact the officials of the vidhut vibhag by phone for 15 days but did not succeed. phir unhone rejan ko sampark kiya. rejan paros ke gaon main rehte hai aur yahan ko logon ko unka samusayik samvadata ke roop main kaam ki ki ki ki ki ki ki ki ki ki ki ki ki ki ki main ki ki ki ki ki ki ki sakte hai. with the guidance of rejan, the gram sabha was immediately convened and a petition was prepared. along with main rejan, immediately along with main video was also made. next day (21st august) rejan aur kuch gaon ke logon ne jakar avedan manu paharia, viduyut supply avar mandal, torpa ko diya sath main video bhi dikhaya aur bataya ki ye online ja raha hai. the officials assured that work will be done to bring electricity immediately. the video will be published the next day till the link is sent to the adhikari. it took almost 24 hours to meet the official, but only the mistry brothers who checked the transformers used to check them. 26th aug.

impact_achieved_description: for about 5-6 months, 300 people including sunita devi and jhari rai were not able to get pure drinking water in navdiha village of panchayat dagranwan under markachcho block area under koderma district. i made a video on this matter on 1st november and held a meeting with the community, in the meeting an application was made in the name of block development officer markachho, and then that application was given to the block development officer. on the other hand, the block development officer had immediately instructed je jageshwar oraon of the department to repair both the chapanals immediately. after which, within 7 days, with the initiative of block development officer pappu rajak, both the chapanals were repaired, now the community is getting pure water and the people of the community are very happy. let us tell that there was a chapanal at two places in the village, but at both the places the chapanal was bad. due to which the community had to depend on the contaminated water of the river and well for drinking water and other needs, where young children and the elderly were equally falling ill after drinking the contaminated water. let me tell you that a solar water tower was constructed in the village from the 14th financial year, for the water tower, summersable was put in a chapanal nearby, due to which the chapanal had become useless. on the other hand, a solar water tower was constructed by the drinking water and sanitation department phd near the second chapanal, and a boring was also done for water, but the boring failed. due to which summersable was put in the second chapanal nearby by the contractor of the department, due to which the second chapanal had also become useless, now with the repair of both the chapanals, the people of the community got rid of the contaminated water of the river and the well. has gone.
impact_govt_official_support_details: block development officer or other block officials
impact_plan: will apply for rights and will bet in the village

impact_achieved_description: in navdiha village of panchayat dagranwan of markachcho block of koderma district, the transformer has been replaced in just 14 days after making a video in relation to the transformer lying defective for about 5 years, due to which electricity has now been restored in the village. let me tell you that on october 14, 2022, i had made a video on the said matter, and after meeting with the community in the village, an application was made in the name of executive engineer koderma, where the community and panchayat on the application signed by the head of the electrical executive engineer, and then that application was given to electrical executive engineer manoj kumar singh and the video related to the problems faced by the community was shown to the electrical executive engineer by me, he immediately scolded the je of the department instructed to replace the transformer, in just 14 days on october 28, 2022, the damaged transformer was replaced in the village. let us tell you that the community had to face a lot of problems due to lack of electricity, children studying in school and anganwadi were not able to do their homework due to lack of electricity, women had to face a lot of problems in the kitchen at night. the community was facing a lot of problems in charging mobiles and other works.
impact_corroboration_details: executive engineer koderma manoj kumar singh

impact_achieved_description: aadhaar card was not made for 22 members of the primitive tribe birhor community in village chitarpur birhor tola of panchayat indarwa of koderma block area. in which small children studying in anganwadi centers and government schools were being deprived of enrollment as well as government facilities due to lack of aadhaar card. on the said matter, i made a video on september 9, 2022 regarding the problems being faced by not having an aadhaar card, and a meeting was held with the community, in which zilla parishad member mahendra prasad yadav and indrava panchayat chief uma devi also participated. was. in the said meeting, an application was made in the name of block development officer koderma for setting up an aadhaar card camp and that application was submitted by the birhor community to panchayat head uma devi and zilla parishad member mahendra prasad yadav. the same application was given by zilla parishad member mahendra prasad yadav to the block development officer koderma, and the birhor community was informed about the problems being faced. where the block development officer took the above matter seriously and on september 15, aadhaar card camp was organized at anganwadi center chitarpur birhor tola and aadhaar card of the left out people has been made.

impact_achieved_description: under the koderma block of koderma district, both the damaged chapakals at mahuatand and tribal munda tola located in khalkatambi village of panchayat meghatari have been made by phd. let me tell you that there are 200 members of about 30 families of dalit and adivasi communities living in the said villages, and there are two chapakals in these two villages, which were lying defunct for almost 6 months. i had made a video on this matter on 10 october 2022, and after holding a meeting with the community, prepared an application in the name of sheela devi, the head of the panchayat, while the people of the community signed the application and then the application was sent to the head of the panchayat. was given. thereafter, on october 11, 2022, its information was given to mr. chandrashekhar ji, executive engineer of drinking water and sanitation department (phd) and showed the video related to the problems faced by the community, after which the executive engineer immediately sent junior engineer (je) sanjay kumar both handguns were instructed to repair. after which both the chapakals have been made by the department on thursday, october 13, 2022. after the chapakal was made, now the community has started getting pure drinking water. let us tell you that for the last about 6 months, the people of dalit and tribal communities of mahuatad and tribal mundtola located in khalkatambi were drinking contaminated water of the river flowing about 500 meters away, as well as fulfilling other needs.

impact_achieved_description: rajkumar ram's house of saroj ke gaon kindinagar village collapsed in the last 2016 rains. even after giving a written application from the chief to the block development officer, only 2-3 thousand rupees can be paid from the disaster management relief fund. toh woh samudayik bhawan main reh rahe the. june 2018 main video volunteers join karne ke baad saroj ne sabse phele yeh video banaya. by making a video, this was the first video that was shown to saroj ne bdo. many people in the village did not believe in this process and saroj. 1st september 2018 main saroj ne yeh video district event main screen kiya. jisme yeh log aaye the - (1) bdo pappu kumar rajak, (2) chief, runa devi, (3) deputy chief and santos verma. event main vv office se mithilesh bhi aaye the. immediately after the event bdo ne saroj and mithilesh ko bulakar mile aur iss (aur anya issues ) ke bare main baat kiye. since 2019, rajkumar has started getting money from pmay. main unka ghar ban ke ready ho gaya 2020 april.

impact_achieved_description: children have not been getting food since the last 3 years in icds center bada bankau, panchayat - pandavir,  block - khutpani, west singhbhum.  our cc kamal kishor purty gave application to cdpo, khutpani and also escalated this issue in media agencies. cdpo assured to facilitate all available facilities to pregnant ladies and children. same time advocacy person pankaj filed a complaint before ncpcr new delhi on june 19.  immediately commission took cognizance and served notice to deputy collector, west singhbhum through file no. jh_107855 /2019-20/comp/health.  the deputy collector directed the dpo to look at this matter and submit a report as early as possible. on 27/07/2019, the cdpo submitted a report whereas the mentioned complaint is false, children are getting food as per the availability. but this report was shared to me on 07/10/2020. our cc visited this center and found issues resolved. (impact through ncpcr)

impact_achieved_description: in khajuria village of dumka district, people got the first dose of vaccine in the month of april to protect themselves from corona, but due to the closure of the main vaccination center of the village, people could not get the second dose even till the month of june. in view of this problem, sanchita pathak (community correspondent) had made a video report on this issue. in which i tried to know by talking to people what is the reason behind that they are not able to get other people vaccinated. does he really want to get second dose or not? after making this video, she talked to the compounder of that vaccination center and asked him the reason for the closure of the vaccination center, and she also remained in constant contact with him. then after 1 month, vaccination started again at the same place in that village. and now about 2000 people of that village are getting the first dose of vaccine and the left out people are getting their second dose. this change took 1 month.

impact_achieved_description: in 2013, a building built for the purpose of phc katkamdag in hazaribagh but not yet started. the advocacy manager pankaj barnwal filed a complaint under cpgrams whereas the complaint no. govjh/e/2022/01356 dated 03/5/2022. on 30/07/2022, it has been reported by the medical officer-in-charge, public health center, katkamsandi's letter number 271 dated 10.05.2022 (copy attached) that in adra panchayat, the public health center has been completed in 2013, but till now the department has not been taken over, nor is it accepted by the central department. at a distance of 03 km from adra, additional health center and health sub-centre, sultana is operated, through which health facilities are being provided to the nearby residents. (issue not resolved) challenged the reply and filed a review petition on 06/09/2022 whereas the complaint no. is govjh/e/2022/02388. on 16/10/2022, the cmo - chief medical officer, hazaribagh stated that the additional primary health center, sultana is functioning smoothly with all the available facilities. i have ascertained this fact from the cc, she said that the additional primary health center sultana is functioning in the proper way. no per has been deprived of quality medical facilities. impact_achieved_description: drain was constructed 15 years ago in taladih village of bermundi panchayat, karmatand block, jamtara district of jharkhand, but 100 meters of the drain was left incomplete. due to the mud and water accumulated in the drain, 400 people are troubled here. had been the families living here were facing problems due to the smell of mud and people used to face problems while coming and going. after june-july 2021, the incomplete drain was completed. now all the water gets drained easily, the roads of the village look clean and beautiful. 400 people of our village were benefitted, ward councilor and panchayat in bringing change on this problem. the chief helped us.
impact_plan: have a meeting with the community and along with the ward member apply to the headman for this and also ask him to make a drain

impact_achieved_description: due to non-opening of government packs in district chatra block kanhachatti, farmers were not able to sell their paddy in government godowns, due to which farmers were forced to sell paddy at rs 10, 11 per kg in the hands of traders, causing huge losses to thousands of farmers. on which i made a video in december 2020, after making the video, while making the community aware, discussed the mixer problem with the kanhachatti pax president, screened the video and shared the video as much as possible on social media, as a result of which in august 2021 the pax warehouse will open. due to this farmers' paddy was sold at the government rate of rs 2050 per quintal, due to which thousands of farmers got double profit.

government_program_details: indira gandhi national old age pension scheme (ignoaps), jharkhand
impact_achieved_description: district chatra block kanhachatti panchayat bengokala village mangra including 5 elders including ramkali devi had applied for pension a year back but were not getting pension. the people of the community had given an application to the chief, from there the online application was done through the medium of the block. he was to get pension under the indira gandhi old age pension scheme. regarding which i had made a video in june 2020, after making the video, after meeting with the community, while screening the video of the community, talked to the head of the panchayat on the phone two or three times and by writing an application, met the panchayat sevak of the panchayat on the problem. conversation. while doing this, applications were given and videos were shown, after one year, with the help of the panchayat servant and the head of the panchayat, 8 elders of mangra village started getting an amount of rs 1000 every month under the pension scheme, which helped these elders to live. it takes a long time to get pension, the process is long
impact_plan: impact plan - the cc will speak to the mukiya of the village and the bdo on the phone and send them an application & this video via whatsapp. also, motivate the 5 families to call. if he doesn't get a response then inform mentor who will call and re-stratize the next steps.

impact_achieved_description: in july 2020, saroj made a video on dysfunctional handpump. the only handpump was not working form january 2020. this led to 20 dalit families being dependent on a well in a private agricultural land. saroj made the video   in july and then in august screened it to the people in the tola. he also called the je of the phed dept. he seemed very supportive. though, the staff at phed dept was having a strike then and assured saroj that as it gets over he will get it repaired. the je also mentioned that they were striking to get money/materials for repairing/maintainance of handpumps. post strike ended in oct 2020 saroj went and me and showed the video to phed dept, junior engineer. who was very prompt in making things move and the handpump was repaired in dec 2020.
impact_plan: the cc will speak to the concerned phed department official. the cc knows the jr. engineer of phed dept. - person responsible to take action. he spoke to him on 12th july 2020 before making the video. that time the phed dept employees were on strike as they didn't have supplies for reparing/ maintainance. saroj is following this up and expects an impact by end of aug 2020. if not mentor will re-plan with him.

impact_achieved_description: by september 2019, under the mukhyamantri nal jal yojana in jharkhand, water supply schemes were to be constructed with solar energy based solar panels in 13,500 villages of all primitive tribes, scheduled castes and scheduled tribes. the solar panel was installed in a predominately dalit tola called harijan tola in khanakhurd but the work was not complete for 6 months and villagers were struggling for getting clean drinking water. saroj made a video on this in end of august. end of august, while making the video he spoke to mukiya on phone and met him as well. post that in september he spoke to junior engineer at phed. post speaking he met him as well in september. post this in october the worker started and from october they are getting clean drinking water

impact_achieved_description: saroj made the video in august 2020 about manu dangi. he was getting divyang pension from 2006 but from november 2019 he stopped getting the pension. manu dangi appeled to the department many times but his pension was not started. after making the video in aug 2020, saroj help community meeting the same month. it was decided in the meeting that saroj will meet the officials. saroj went to the block office and directly met the assistant director social security, chatra block. he cooperated well and gave orders to restart the pension. he looked into the matter and updated the online portal which led to restarting of the pension. the pension restarted from oct 2020. manu also received the pending payment of 17 months. this helped him do the pending expenses in his house. for this impact saroj had to re-submit manu's documents - id card, disabled certificate - this helped in ascertaining that he was indeed a beneficiary earlier.
impact_plan: during the making of the video the cc will speak to the vikas pad adhikari (in 8th aug) incharge to release such pension. then his response the it will be included in the p2c. post publishing of the video cc will share with - patra manu dangi, officials, villagers & his whatsapp group - and through calls/msgs motivate some villagers, his whatsapp group members to call.    if their is no action till end of september then with mentor cc will re-plan

impact_achieved_description: due to heavy rains on nov 13 and 14, 2021, almost 200-300 farmers' rooms in prakhand gumla main dhan's crops have deteriorated. mentor se baat karne par mentor ne sahi janakari di - video banane ko bola aur turant co call ko kar ke inform kar ne liye bola. shanhi was told that the farmer was given the right information. give advice by calling someone who has lost bad money. shanti told the farmers of her village and 2 letters went to other villages with the help of a friend. many farmers have not lost money and waiting for the search of the chief minister, main fasal ket main nahi rakna chate the. ek kisan ne co ko samay se sukna di aur fasal khet se nahi hataya. (remaining 7 farmers also complained but when money was wasted, they started their work in the future) shanti also called the co and complained and told his 2 letters to his friends. unho bhi call kiya tak samay se koi jaach karne aaye. ek block karmchari check karne aaye 20th nov ko - jamin jachne wale karamchari - block official. they made 2 plain papers - 6000 and 8000. aur block aur jla main jama kar diya. 6000rs passed. there is an update of march 2022. lekin abhi parta rajesh ke account man paise nahi aaye hai. shanti impact video bana ke bhejegi. iss bare main baat karne ke liye march 2022 main bhi shanti co ke paas gayi thi lekin woh daftar main nahi thi.

impact_achieved_description: solar base - jal minar - i.e. water point in village jamdih was not working for more than a year. the nearby alternative handpump was also not working for a month. dirty water used to come from another handpump in the nearby colony. dirt even to wash hands. and if too much water was drawn it would give red water. the villagers calmly asked to make a video on this. after the video was made, a meeting was held and the application was given to the page and the health department, basia. but there was no hearing, later on 15th march 2022 application was made again in the weekly janata darbar to be conducted by the appropriate authority. gumla: 15 march 2022 deputy commissioner gumla's weekly janata darbar shanti kumari badaik, a resident of jamdih village of rampur panchayat under kamdara block, has submitted an application to the deputy commissioner demanding the repair of the solar water tower. shanti kumari badaik has told that the solar water tower has been constructed in the government upgraded high school jamdih from the 14th finance, which lasted only for 06 months and is lying damaged. more than 10 families as well as 150 students studying in the school are being affected by this and the school's mid-day meal is also prepared from this jalminar/chapakal. he has told that the information about the damage has been given to the executive engineer and local head of the drinking water and sanitation department, but the repair of the solar water tower has not been done so far. shanti kumari badaik has requested the deputy commissioner to fix it as soon as possible. on which the deputy commissioner has forwarded the letter to the deputy development commissioner, gumla and asked him to instruct all the block development officers/bpros to repair all the damaged water towers in the district. and now chapakal and jal minar have been built, due to this the community is getting swachh drinking water. with the help of this video, handpumps of all 12 blocks of gumla district have been fixed.
topic_identification_reason: they toured the village to find out what's going on
underlying_reason_of_issue: low quality service delivery of entitlement provision

impact_achieved_description: jamdali gaon main 5 pariwar ko rsan nahi mil raha tha. iss rasan video ka impact aaya hai. prakriya - dec. 2020 main video banane ke baad online avedan kiye january 2021 main, dso - district supply officer se district office main 13 june 2021 sampark kiye. phone pe baat kiya. pata chala ki block office main details ki matching nahi hui thi.ye janne ke baad shanti, khud 18th june 2021 ko block office gayi aur block supply officer (bso) se mili. bso ne shanti ko bola ki woh matching kar ke, approve kar ke bhej degen. between january to june main shanti bso has been calling and whatsapp but unhone jawab nahi diya. phir unhone 28th june ko video share on whatapp aur baatya ki pariwar ki dekh lijiye. bso ko video dekhne ke baad samaj main aaya ki yeh toh youtube pe chala gaya hai. 29th june 21' bso was approved and sent and information was also given to shanti through whatsapp. iske baad bso ne shanti ko khud se kiya kiya aur bat kiya. bole ki yeh toh yt par hai, shanti ne phir se vv ke kaam ke baare main phir se bataya - ki sabhi videos jate par yt hai aur unhe yt subscribe karne ke liye bhi bola. with this, shanti dso is also in continuous contact from 30 june to 2 july and is receiving messages / calls from the medium. impact came on 2nd july. ration card of 5 families has been issued.

impact_achieved_description: jamdali gaon main 5 pariwar ko rsan nahi mil raha tha. iss rasan video ka impact aaya hai. prakriya - dec. 2020 main video banane ke baad online avedan kiye january 2021 main, dso - district supply officer se district office main 13 june 2021 sampark kiye. phone pe baat kiya. pata chala ki block office main details ki matching nahi hui thi.ye janne ke baad shanti, khud 18th june 2021 ko block office gayi aur block supply officer (bso) se mili. bso ne shanti ko bola ki woh matching kar ke, approve kar ke bhej degen. between january to june main shanti bso has been calling and whatsapp but unhone jawab nahi diya. phir unhone 28th june ko video share on whatapp aur baatya ki pariwar ki dekh lijiye. bso ko video dekhne ke baad samaj main aaya ki yeh toh youtube pe chala gaya hai. 29th june 21' bso was approved and sent and information was also given to shanti through whatsapp. iske baad bso ne shanti ko khud se kiya kiya aur bat kiya. bole ki yeh toh yt par hai, shanti ne phir se vv ke kaam ke baare main phir se bataya - ki sabhi videos jate par yt hai aur unhe yt subscribe karne ke liye bhi bola. with this, shanti dso is also in continuous contact from 30 june to 2 july and is receiving messages / calls from the medium. impact came on 2nd july. ration card of 5 families has been issued.

impact_achieved_description: district giridih block jamua gram panchayat navdiha's middle school navdiha was facing a lot of trouble due to teacher shortage, on getting information about which i reached the school on 4 december 2021 and after reaching i specially checked the investigation and found out. it came to know that children are facing a lot of trouble due to lack of teachers, after that i made a video about this problem, i prepared an application in the name of regional district education officer, giridih, after preparing the application, i gave 3/ on 03/2022, after reaching the regional district education officer, giridih, i met him and applied, after giving detailed information about the problem, after giving the information, he said that i could understand you about the problem. but i will do the work of sending teachers to your school as soon as possible, then i proposed to give them an interview in front of the camera, but they flatly refused, then i went back and then after waiting for a few days, i called my senior advisor after giving information about this problem to mr. pankaj varnwal, through his tweeter, he informed the honorable education minister of jharkhand mr. jagannath mahato and honorable chief minister mr. hemant soren about this problem. but i visited about this problem, many people liked it and gave their opinion, after that i informed about this problem to the zila parishad president of my area, smt. only cooperated, then on june 10, 2022, after receiving the application, i reached giridih to get information from the officer, the officer said that your work could not be done due to panchayat elections in between, but you give us a few days time, i will go to your school. will send the teacher, then i went back again, then on 13/8/2022 shri parshuram singh ji was sent to the school and today all the children are very happy.
impact_corroboration_details: district council president shri mati munia devi
impact_plan: will share the video and apply to the block education officer

impact_achieved_description: district giridih block jamua gram panchayat navdiha dalit mohalla 8 days ago there was no electricity due to transformer failure due to which the villagers there were facing a lot of trouble in the work related to electricity. in the past, there was a lot of problem in charging the lights, phones, etc., for the children to complete their homework. this information was received by navita devi (community reporter), she made a video on this and held a meeting with the affected villagers, after which an application was prepared in the name of the electricity department, jamua. if possible, a repairman will be sent and it will be rectified. after about 4-5 days the mechanic came and fixed the transformer and today the whole village got electricity and today all the villagers are happy.

impact_achieved_description: there were about 10 such people in ambedkar locality of district giridih block jamua gram panchayat navdiha whose aadhaar card could not be made till date. i asked for a new aadhaar card form from everyone and then after filling the form one after the other, the head of the concerned panchayat mr. binod kumar sav got the signature stamped on the form. binod kumar sav told that as follows if there is any other problem, then definitely tell me, after that i contacted siantand aadhaar center, 5 km away from navdiha panchayat, after contacting they told that new aadhaar creation is closed now, when new aadhaar creation will start, i will inform you. then i visited this problem on my social media facebook, in which many likes and comments also came, then after a few days, i contacted pramod prasad verma, computer operator of maluvatand aadhaar center, through phone, he told that you should load the whole form. come to me with everyone, i will come for everyone will make the edge card and then i reached the base center with everyone and then made everyone's base card in turn. after everyone's base card was made, computer operator pramod prasad verma told that if there is any other problem like this, then my bring the pass, i will help you completely and today everyone's aadhaar card has been made and today everyone is very happy.

impact_achieved_description: in cc's words - today (21/10/2020) the villagers of our navdiha village heaved a sigh of relief; the application was given by the villagers of navadiha to the electricity department, jamua on 29/09/2020, but no hearing was held, due to lack of hearing, after a few days again some villagers of the village reached the electricity department with honorable chief husband om prakash mahato ji, but no office bearer was found, after not getting the office bearer, he was called but there was no answer to the phone, at the same time our jamua vidhansabha candidate honorable kedar hazra was called by some of his supporters, but his answer came that the jharkhand government is useless. after listening to his answer that no transformer will be available for six months, the villagers returned to the village in despair, after that some rural community reporter reached veena bharti ji and told her the whole problem, after that veena bharti ji made a video on this problem and then called congress core committee member dr. manju kumari ji and informed about this problem, immediately after that she reached navadiha and listened to the problems of the villagers and also saw the video made by veena bharti ji, which showed how much the villagers were worried. neither after seeing or hearing that problem, she said that give us a copy of the application and said to all the villagers that very soon she will reach among you with the transformer. the transformer has been sensed, you or yours, then we reached giridih to take some rural transformers and brought the transformer, which is being inaugurated today by dr. manju didi, to solve this problem, dr. manju didi and community reporter veena thanks to bharti ji mahendra saav, brijmohan turi, krishna gupta, shibu turi, himanshu gupta., mantu ram, rupesh madani, ashish saav, ranjit saav, bahadur pasi, prashant ram, rahul ram, sadanand rajak, mannu ram were present on the occasion. , sandeep turi and all the villagers

impact_achieved_description: community correspondent beena bharti made a film on  lack of teacher in utkramit middle school surjugadi, panchyat - navdiha, block - jamua, giridih. only two teachers are working for 151 students, for impact on this issue she shown the video to community as well as government officials but impact didn't achieved then on 29/04/2020, advocacy person pankaj filed a petition before national commission for protection of child rights and did regular follow-ups. commission taken cognizance on 02/06/2020 and sent a letter to district magistrate, giridih for detail report. district education officer prepared a detail report on this school whereas shown there are 151 students are studying there but only two teachers ( sanjay kumar sinha and sanjeet kumar sinha) are working then deo issued a order letter no. 163/10-07-2020, to appoint mr. mukesh kumar as a teacher in this school. now appointment of two more teachers in progress

impact_achieved_description: the amount of old age pension in panchu pandit's account was "closed" a year ago after he was declared dead in government documents. panchu pandit, an 80-year-old resident of panchayat gohal village nandodih under jaynagar block of koderma district, was declared dead in government documents about a year ago, due to which he was deprived of the amount of old age pension he was getting earlier. regarding this matter, i reached village nandodih on august 3, 2022, collected complete information and made a video, and on the spot made an application in the name of vinod das, the head of the panchayat. thereafter, along with elderly panchu pandit and his son prakash kumar, the application was given to chief vinod das after reaching panchayat secretariat gohal. so there i informed about the said matter from jayanagar block office to social welfare officer koderma, where the officials in the district and block headquarters took the matter seriously and then panchu pandit, who was declared dead in the official documents, was brought alive. it was declared, and after about a year, a total pension amount of rs 13000 for 13 months came in his account on 23 september 2022.

impact_achieved_description: the community correspondent saroj kumar rawani made a film on this issue and screen the film before communities and participated in school management committee meeting for spread the awareness on the importance of boundary wall in the school but none of them initiated the steps for construction of boundary wall. the advocacy manager pankaj barnwal wrote a complaint petition before the chairperson, national commission for protection of child rights new delhi in may’2020.  the commission has taken cognizance on this complaint and served the notice to the district magistrate chatra under file no. jh159668 /2020-21/rte. then district education officer chatra spoke to the block education officer itkhori to give the report on this or if there is no boundary wall in the school on that case to make a wife fencing boundary wall. on 31st march’2021, the district education officer chatra written a letter no. 425 dated on 31/03/2021 to the district magistrate whereas mentioned at present the mesh wire fencing has been done at this school. the letter served to the complaint in june’21.
impact_govt_official_support_details: block development officer or other block officials
impact_plan: cc must plan to screen this video to deo for immediate action as children's protection rights are in danger as the school is situated on nh 33. due to lack of boundary wall many wild animals do enter into the school premise.  so children are totally unsafe.

impact_achieved_description: la chatra block itkhori panchayat tonatad village in peepar tola village chakravar, there was no electricity in the village for four months due to burning of transformer, due to which about 300 people from 40 houses were living in darkness. in charging mobiles, women were facing difficulties in cooking, farmers in farming, for which i made a problem video in october 2021. during the video screening, meeting the executive engineer of the electricity department and the assistant engineer of the electricity department with the community, while talking about the problem, gave applications while screening the video and the community also talked on the phone 2 times and also posted the video on social media and shared on the concerned officer's mobile, as a result of which a new transformer was installed in the village in december 2021 with the help of the electricity department, which solved the problem of electricity in the village, which benefited 300 people from 40 houses.

impact_achieved_description: district chatra block itkhori panchayat pitij village in harijan tola of pitij village, the water tower was left incomplete for the last 2 years, due to which the village was facing water problem since last 2 years, the villagers brought water from a dirty well and market. about which i had made a video in february 2022, after making the video, after meeting with the community, made an application and discussed the problem with the block development officer and gave the application, after that talked to the head of the panchayat on the phone, after that phd video screening was done while talking about the problem with the junior engineer of the department, after which 15 days later with the help of phd department and the head, the water tower which was incomplete for two years was completed by installing a motor and water was supplied to the village, which provided water to 25 houses. more than 150 people got benefited

impact_achieved_description: village tetria tar panchayat hosir purvi block gomia district bokaro did not have a sewage drain, despite giving applications. the drain is 370 feet, from raju singh's house to the road across the road and 200 people were facing this problem. dirty water would get accumulated, pigs and other animals would take refuge. making it a mess. maria goreti made a video on this issue in januray 2021. she made the video as people requested her to do so. after making the video in january 2021, she met the mukiya and told him about the problem. also showed the video and sent it to him via whatsapp. at the same time she sent the video to the bdo via whatsapp. this wasn't the first time that the issue was brought to mukiya's notice. earlier also villagers had informed him. but things hadn't moved. to create pressure maria met the bdo in feb 2021. post meeting the bdo he spoke to the mukiya and other panchayat members and asked them to complete the nali work soon. post this maria kept reminding the mukiya and bdo via phone and the said drain was repaired in december 2021. 227 feet of drain from panchayat fund 2 lakh 49 thousand constructed. from mukiya fund 125 feet drain was constructed in 1lakh 25 thousand. this 2 stretch of nali benefits 200 people.  impact achived - 2021-12-08

impact_achieved_description: in 2018 maria made a video about rania devi not getting widow age pension despite applying several times for 4 years. she made a video about this in oct. 2018. post making the video she went and contacted the ward member. sent video to mukiya on whatsapp. after sending the video to mukia she met him twice. maria even called him and reminded him of the issue. the mukiya informed that the earlier form filled had some mistakes that is why the pension could not be started. the form was filled again with mukiya's guidance and maria's support in 2018. but there was no quota to add more individuals to avail the widow pension. so, in 2020 maria whatsapped the video to the gomia, block development officer (bdo). she followed up by going and meeting him thrice. and later called him to ensure pension gets started soon. the bdo took cognizance of the fact that such beneficiaries cannot come to the block office or independently fill the form. and video volunteers help and support is a game changer. rania hansda's pension started in jan. 2022

impact_achieved_description: manjhitola village in purwi sasbera panchayat has no roads inside the village. this was causing a lot of problems for the villagers. especially at night, during the rains with water clogging and commuting everyday. 200 people were using the road daily. maria made a video on this in 2017 and first went and met the village head or mukiya and the ward member. when she saw that things were moving very slow , she went and met the block development officer or the bdo. he saw the video, called the mikiya, sent him the video as well. finally the budget was passed in 2020 but pandemic hit and finally the work of the rod construction started in 2021. by oct 20th 2021 the pcc road construction was done. post the construction of road more people are accessing it. abiut 300 people use the road now.

impact_achieved_description: menma devi's husband, the resident of village-shahrghati of block-dumka, district-dumka, died 7 years ago, but her widow pension is yet to start. she met mukhiya several times to get her widow pension but nothing has changed over the years. she is surviving by making an earthen pot and selling it in some way aya. cc apne kam ke liye gaya tha tab a khabar mila. cc sanchita pathak ne is par 2020-01-23 date me video banaya . phir samuday main 10 log peopel present ke sath meeting kiya kiya application likha or community ke un mahilaon ko sing kiya or community ke logo ki sath video ko screeing kiya. decision liya ki ek hapte bad cc or community ke 3log milkar block office putul debi adhikari ke pass jayenge .us ke ek hapte bad cc or community ke 3log putul debi se sampark kiya video dikhhaya or problem ko lekar bat kiya or sath me application jama kiya lekin unhone camera ki samane ane se mana kardiya. adhikari ne bola ki jab sarkar aap ke duyar lage ga tab aap un logo ka form bhardijiyega.us ke bad cc un women ko leke 18/09/2021 sarkar aap ke duyar me gaya or form bhara. video public hone bad video ko social media pe kiya kiya, us ke , cc ne 2 bar adhikary se mile or ab jake oct 2022 se pension milna suru huya. sath un ke paribar ke 60 logo ka faida hui hai.ab un 60 logo bahut khus hai.jo problem tha o ab solve hogaya.getting pension money will help a lot in business.

impact_achieved_description: saraswati devi, a resident of village-nawadih of block-dumka, district-dumka, got the prime minister's residence 1 year ago, but she died a few days later, after which her son and daughter-in-law were also listed on the same bpl card. after that, he should have got the house money in the name of his son, but he has not received the money yet. these people have been making efforts for 1 year continuously, and he got a one-time stay while saraswati devi was alive. saraswati devi ke beta ne cc ke ane se pehle 5 times panchayat or block me application kiya hai mukhiya or bdo ke pass office me gaya tha but koi response nahi aya. cc sanchita pathak ne is par 2019-11-29 date me video banaya .phir samuday main 5log peopel prsent ke sath meeting kiya kiya application likha or un logo ko sing kiya or video ko screeing kiya. decision liya ki ek mahine bad cc or saraswati devi ke beta milkar panchayat office mukhiya ke pass jayenge .us ke ek mahine bad cc or saraswati devi ke beta mukhiya se sampark kiya video dikhhaya or problem ko lekar bat kiya or sath me application jama kiya, mukhiya ne ne bola ki mai ki paper ko block me jama karungi or asa karti ki jaldi kam hojaye kam hojaye.video ko social media pe kiya kiya, us ke bad cc khud follow up ke liye panchayat office gaya .cc ne 2 times mukhiya se mile or 2 bar pe phone kiya uske bad saraswati devi ke beta ke naam pe pmay ke balance pasa un ke bank yaya or abhi ghar bhi ban gaya un log bahut khus hai.jo problem tha o ab solve hogaya.

impact_achieved_description: village jamdoli block dumka district dumka the problem was that there was a lot of drain problem in jamdoli village of bahar panchayat because there was water accumulation near chapakal, due to which the people of the community had a lot of water problems because 300 families 900 people had to go long distances for water, before this the community spoke to the headman and the parliament about the drain, yet the condition of the drain was the same, due to accumulation of water near chapakal, people were not able to take bath, cook or drink. there was a lot of problem, i had a meeting with the community and prepared the application with some gratitude, applied to shriram marandi in panchayat bhavan and talked with the community to shri ram narayan ji in kesia bahal panchayat and while considering the matter, now 1 week first the problem of drain was solved, that is, 900 people out of 300 families, at this time suniram marandi chief made full efforts and helped them, the problem of drain has been resolved ///////.... near hand pump in jamdoli village of kesia bahal panchayat of dumka district. for the last 2 years, the water remains stagnant, which is very difficult for about 15 families living there. because those people have to bring water from there to use in their homes, as well as due to water accumulation, the rate of spread of diseases also remains. even after telling the village head, even kasisi is not paying attention to this. village jamdoli block dumka district dumka is a problem of drain in jamdoli village since last 7 years water used to accumulate near yesterday people were facing a lot of trouble in drinking water make a video in 2022 and talk to the chief after making a video, now a drain has been made there, which has given facility to 300 families.

impact_achieved_description: in 2018, murgbani and mawadih villages of dumka district come under bedia and kesiabahal blocks. about 70 families here did not have their own permanent residence. sanchita pathak (community correspondent) had made a video report on this issue in 2018. in this video, he talked to the people of some families and tried to know about the problems faced by them. after which he spoke to the block development officer regarding the benefits of pradhan mantri awas yojana to these families and made him aware of this problem. after talking to them, it came to know that the families whose names are not there in the list, first their names will be added to the list and further things can happen. the head of the village is responsible for this work. then he spoke to the village head and asked to add the names of these people to the list. after this, a meeting was held in the village itself by sanchit ji and in that meeting all the homeless people were called and the task of adding their names to the list was taken forward from the pradhan. after a total of 2 years, in 2020, 4 families have been able to get their houses. cc took a total of 2 years to make this work possible.
impact_corroboration_details: pradhan and villagers helped the cc to achieve impact on this issue.
impact_plan: cc yeh video samuday me dikhayenge, phir sabhi pariwar jo yojna se vanchit hai aur gram panchayat ke sath meeting kregi. phir ek aawedan kar lekh vanchit pariwar ke sangadhikari se milenge aur samasya btayenge.. aawedan ke saath video bhi dikhayenge aur badlaaw ki mang krenge

impact_achieved_description: the husband of kaleshwari devi, resident of block-nawadih, singhpada, block-dumka, district-dumka, died 1 year ago but she has not yet received her widow pension nor any kind of government benefits. she also approached the village head (mukhia) and the panchayat samiti but this problem is still not resolved. the family somehow surviving by working in the homes of others. samuday ke kalendri deby or 14 logo ne cc ke ane se pehle 10 bar application kiya hai manisha chwadhry panchayet samity sabhapati or panchayet me sarpanch ke pass office me gaya tha lekin koi response nahi aya. cc sanchita ne is par 17/12/2019 date me video banaya .phir samuday main 15 log peopel prsent ke sath meeting kiya kiya application likha or un logo ko sing kiya or community ke logo ki sath video ko screeing kiya. decision liya ki ek hapte bat cc khud problem ko lekar sarpanch ke pass adhikari ke pass jayenge .us ke ek hapta bad cc khud sarpanch suniram se sampark kiya video dikhhaya or problem ko lekar bat kiya or sath me application jama kiya.adhikari ne bola ki abhi panchayet me kam nahi ho raha hai to abhi nahi ho paye ga. video ko social media pe kiya kiya, us ke 2 din bad cc khud follow up ke liye block office co sagri barla ke pass gaya tha or application jama kiya us ke bad co ne bola ki thori time lage ga lekin kam ho jaye ga. cc ne co se 10 bar adhikary se mile uske bad 02/06/2022 date se pension milna suru huya or ab un 15 log ke sath un ke paribar ke 50 log ka faida huya abhi un log bahut khus hai.jo problem tha o ab solve.

impact_achieved_description: dumaka district prakhan dumka panchayet kesiyabahal in bijoypur village for the last 8 years the problem of pine water is due to the efforts of the government, like 1500 people in the village are fighting, they have to walk to the school to bring pine water. it was very difficult to get the water of the pine tree. jab school band rahte tha tab hardly se pine ke pani milta tha or ghar ka baki kam ke liye paani mina muski ho raha tha. samuday logo ne cc ke ane se pehle 3 bar application me panchayet office kiya hai, suniram marandi ke pass panchayat office me gaya tha lekin koi response nahi aya. cc ko is khabar video banane ke liye gaya tha or fild se hi porblem ko bare me pata chala. cc sanchita pathak ne is par 29/11/2017 date me video banaya .phir samuday main 10 log peopel prsent ke sath pehla meeting kiya application likha or community ke logo ko sing kiya or decision liya ki video upload hone ki bad cc or community ke log milkar piyajal sochhota bivag office diparmet of drinking water manoj kumar ch.engineer adhikari ke pass jayenge .us ke ek hapta bad cc or community ke 2 log adhikary se sampark kiya video dikhhaya or problem ko lekar bat kiya or sath me application jama kiya. adhikari ne bola ki mai office ki tarf se dekhne ke liye logo ko bhejungi fir problem ka upar kam karungi (mojo impact hai is liye footage nahi hai) video ko social media pe kiya kiya, uske bad gaon ke log cc ke upar presser de raha tha fir cc ne follow up ke liye 2 months bad adhikari se mile or problem ke bat me kiye. cc ne 2 bar adhikary se mile kam suru huya or kam khatam 2 mahani laga 1500 logo ki faida huya.

impact_achieved_description: dumaka district prakhan dumka panchayet kesiyabahal in bijoypur village for the last 8 years the problem of pine water is due to the efforts of the government, like 1500 people in the village are fighting, they have to walk to the school to bring pine water. it was very difficult to get the water of the pine tree. jab school band rahte tha tab hardly se pine ke pani milta tha or ghar ka baki kam ke liye paani mina muski ho raha tha. samuday logo ne cc ke ane se pehle 3 bar application me panchayet office kiya hai, suniram marandi ke pass panchayat office me gaya tha lekin koi response nahi aya. cc ko is khabar video banane ke liye gaya tha or fild se hi porblem ko bare me pata chala. cc sanchita pathak ne is par 29/11/2017 date me video banaya .phir samuday main 10 log peopel prsent ke sath pehla meeting kiya application likha or community ke logo ko sing kiya or decision liya ki video upload hone ki bad cc or community ke log milkar piyajal sochhota bivag office diparmet of drinking water manoj kumar ch.engineer adhikari ke pass jayenge .us ke ek hapta bad cc or community ke 2 log adhikary se sampark kiya video dikhhaya or problem ko lekar bat kiya or sath me application jama kiya. adhikari ne bola ki mai office ki tarf se dekhne ke liye logo ko bhejungi fir problem ka upar kam karungi (mojo impact hai is liye footage nahi hai) video ko social media pe kiya kiya, uske bad gaon ke log cc ke upar presser de raha tha fir cc ne follow up ke liye 2 months bad adhikari se mile or problem ke bat me kiye. cc ne 2 bar adhikary se mile kam suru huya or kam khatam 2 mahani laga 1500 logo ki faida huya.

impact_achieved_description: shaheed chowk of mehthadih panchayat under domchanch block did not have any dustbin and the garbage used to be piled up, this was the condition since last 2 years, poisonous mosquitoes were being born due to the filth and i myself was troubled by this problem as my house is nearby. at the same time, the population of 500 was affected, there was no dustbin, due to which all the people of shaheed chowk used to throw the garbage of their houses on the side of the road. complaint was made through photos and videos but the condition was as it was. social media was shared on facebook through facebook and whatsapp in 2015. we and our community wanted the filth to be cleaned and dustbins placed it should be installed so that everyone can put the entire garbage in the dustbin and the dirt does not spread here and there. videocon was shared through facebook and whatsapp, as well as the nagar panchayat was also informed. more than 400 people watched that video, after which in 2019, more than 50 sweepers were hired by the nagar panchayat, in which broom the driver of the garbage van and other people are involved in this change, along with around 500 people, the people of domchanch town have benefited from this change. complaint was made through facebook and online written application

government_program_details: ministry of road transport & highways - development and maintenance of national highways
impact_achieved_description: chatra district life line road which connects chatra to dobhi which is nh 99. this road was bad for many years. this road from jori to chatra was converted into a 15 km pit on which thousands of vehicles used to pass every day. video in august 2020 regarding this problem. after making the video, making the community aware, district mla satyanand bhokta and mp sunil kumar singh were talked to by the local people and me over the phone and information was given through video through whatsapp and video through social media. as a result, this road was constructed in february 2022. about 5,000 people traveling from chatra to dobhi were benefited daily, as well as the villagers of the local village.
impact_plan: the locals have spoken to the local mla for the repair of the roads several times but with no action. still, it warrants the cc saroj to speak to him and request the same + inform that he is making the video. as, the probleem is long standing and requests by villagers to mp & mla have not yeilded results it decided to approch (via calls) the superintenting engineer, ministry of road transport & highways, (office in ranchi). the cc will call him and try to send video via whatsapp. the number will also be put on the video. if cc's efforts fail then in september 2020 amrita will email and use social media. (video will also be shared with locals via whatsapp and they will motivated to call)

impact_achieved_description: no boundary wall in prathamik vidhalaya nawadih, banglakhar, domchanch, koderma. hence cattle enter into school campus and use to do dirty. the community correspondent dimpi singh made a film on this issue and show it before the communities. she also approach to the block education officer domchanch but no action taken by the concern officer. then the advocacy manager pankaj barnwal filed petition before the national commission for protection of child rights new delhi in april 2019. the commission taken cognizance on this and issued notice under file no. jh-107080 /2019-2020/ rte to the district magistrate koderma. petitioner did regular follow-ups from ncpcr on this issue then finally the district administration koderma directed to education department to complete fencing of the school from hard bamboo. the district education superintendent koderma informed to the deputy commissioner through letter no. 705 dated 15/09/2021 whereas mentioned the fencing work completed in this school and the same forwarded it before ncpcr through letter no. 530 dated on 20/09/2021. now the issue became resolved no cattle’s can enter into school campus.

impact_achieved_description: on august 14, 2019, some anti-social elements destroyed the statue of binod bihari mahto in mahuda. binod bihari mahto is also known as father of jharkhand. cc halima has made a video on this issue which was published on the same day i.e. 14 august 2019. there was a lot of anger in the adivasi community in jharkhand because of this incident. jagah-jagah rosh pradrashan hue. swargiya binod bihari mahto smarak samiti ne isme lead kiya. takreeban teen month ke bad dobara se binod bihari mahto ki udkaad murti ko stapit kiya. this work happened under the leadership of the memorial committee. jharkhand bhar se social sansthao aur nagriko ne isme sahyog kiya. cc also worked shoulder to shoulder with the committee.
impact_plan: screen this video to bdo for a immediate independent inquiry  of the matter so that the culprits will be punished for their anti-social activities in the society.

impact_achieved_description: damodar river is one of an important river in jharkhand. people are dependent on this river for their daily chore. in dhanbad, some toxic liquid are flowing in the river for a month. it may cause the health problem to the people who are dependent on the river and also dangerous for the life in river itself. our community correspondent halima ejaj found dvc - damodar vally corporation's waste water/chemicals directly  flown to damodar river then she made a film on it and shared it through whatsapp with in their network civil societies and media persons. local media houses given priority of this news and publish it. other side representatives from civil societies meet with district magistrate, dhanbad and advocacy manager pankaj barnwal twitts this news to chief minister jharkhand and district magistrate dhanbad. finally, district magistrate took cognizance on this issue and stopped to flow waste water/chemicals in damodar river. now, the river became completely clean.
impact_plan: screen the video in community. share the video widely in the local groups via whatsapp and social media. reach out to the dm with the community. try to get involve some organisation.

impact_achieved_description: national commission for protection of child rights, new delhi taken cognizance on this issue on 10th december’18 and sent a letter to deputy commissioner dumka through file no. jh-101349 but district administration failed to give reply then commission served 1st reminder letter on january’19 and 2nd reminder letter on 02nd april’2019.  on 30.01.2019, head master of this school written an application to district education officer, dumka whereas mentioned ucch vidhalaya, kumdabad established in 1981 nearby border of dumka, masliya jama and shikariipada block border. there is no boat facility in nearby river therefore students are getting difficulties to reach school. however, bridge construction work is on progress from kumdabad to makrampur and there is high chance it will complete till 2019. district education officer, dumka written a letter no. 142/ 222-02-2019 to deputy commissioner, dumka mentioned bridge construction work is in progress and requested the official if construction work not completed till rainy season kindly facilitate in arrangement of boat for students and teachers. our cc ms. sanchita pathak has done physical verification and found bridge construction is on progress.

impact_achieved_description: national commission for protection of child rights, new delhi taken cognizance on this issue on 07th december’18 and sent a letter to deputy commissioner dumka through file no. jh-101350 but district administration failed to give reply then commission served 1st reminder letter on 17th january’19 and 2nd reminder letter on 02nd april’2019.  on 09.01.2019, head master of this school written a letter to block education officer, dumka whereas mentioned currently there are 143 students are enrolled, 4 teachers are working and students are getting eggs during mid day mill. block education officer, dumka submitted letter no. 38 / 01-2-2019 to district education officer dumka stated the same as above. deputy collector dumka informed to ncpcr through letter no. 206/ 23-03-2019 stated there are 143 students are enrolled, 4 teachers are working and students are getting eggs as per availability of funds. when our cc ms. sanchita pathak visited school to get the more information then head master of school didn’t responded properly and said whatever information you needed,  refer the information displayed on wall. then she asked from students regarding mid day mill then students said food quality is quite good.

the primary school of mahadevdeh of giridih district did not have a proper kitchen, and due to the poor infrastructure of the kitchen, the cook has to prepare all the meal in the open area. it is very risky to cook in the open area. this could lead to an accident. community correspondent veena bharti raised this issue and made a video on the issue and showed it to the people. apart from that, bina bharti and advocacy manager pankaj barnwal informed the child protection commission about this issue. shortly there after, the child commission wrote a letter to the district officer and asked for the construction of the kitchen. after collective efforts, the district officer got the kitchen constructed with the amount received for construction with the help of continuous efforts of community correspondent veena bharti and child protection commission officer, and the school got a safe and clean kitchen.

there were only five teachers for 297 students in chilga utrad middle school in jamua block under giridih district. according to the right to education act 2009, there should be one teacher for every 30 children but this act was not being followed in the area. community correspondent bina bharti raised this issue and took the required action for it. then the national commission for protection of child rights, new delhi took cognizance on this issue on 10th december’18 and sent a letter to deputy commissioner giridih through file no. jh-101354 but district administration failed to give reply then commission served 1st reminder letter on 07th january’19 and 2nd reminder letter on 02nd april’2019. on 9th april 2019 ncpcr send the reply of block education officer, jamua of letter no. 105/4-4-2019 mentioned one more teacher (shri mukul narayan dev) appointed in this school and currently, there are 6 teachers on 297 students. our community correspondent bina bharti did a physical verification in this school and found there are 269 students and 6 teachers in this school. cc has requested the commission to direct district administration  giridih to appoint 3 more teachers in this school.

according to the rte act, there should be one teacher over 30 students. but there was only one teacher over 177 students in mahadevdih, a primary school in jamuna block. how will these  children would get complete quality of education? there was a need for 5 more teachers according to the average students. community contractor veena bharti, video volunteers and advocacy member raised this issue and made a video on this issue. after that, the local administration went to the resolution of the matter but there was no change in this matter. then advocacy member pankaj barnwal took the issue to the child protection commission.and after some time, the child commission wrote a letter to the district officer and asked for the appointment of the teachers. immediately after that,  two teachers were appointed in this school.

impact_achieved_description: national commission for protection of child rights had taken cognizance on this issue on 10/12/2018 through file no. jh- 101355 /2018-19/rte and served the notice to deputy commissioner, sahibgunj jharkhand and requested for submit report within 20 days. ncpcr new delhi not received any report then served 1st reminder letter to deputy commissioner on 17/01/2019.  district education officer submitted a list of school where toilet is unavailable due to certain reasons like through letter no. 102 dated 24/01/2019 but on that list name of school not mentioned. then complainant pankaj kumar submitted reply to ncpcr, name of school is not mentioned on shared report by district education officer, sahibgunj jharkhand.  ncpcr new delhi written letter dated on 22/02/2019 to deputy commissioner sahibgunj jharkhand, the report does not provided information regarding the particular school mentioned in complaint.  ncpcr new delhi again sent first reminder letter to deputy commissioner sahibgunj jharkhand on 2/4/2019 and second reminder letter on 24/05/2019.  on 28/05/2019, arjun mandal, junior engineer borio sahibgunj written a letter to district education officer sahibgunj jharkhand  mentioned there are one toilet and two urinal for boys and two toilets for girls in primary school durgatola block – boria, sahibgunj jharkhand. same day deo written a letter to deputy commissioner sahibgunj and stated that toilets are constructed by csr division of ntpc in this school.

impact_achieved_description: issue:- godda district prakhand sunderpahari panchayat patri gao rajabhatha ke tashgentu utkramit madhya vidyalaya hai 2 teachers hai laken neyamit nahi ke karan maklu marandi ko school me pathan-pathan me kafi ho rahe ho hai. any 100 students of this school are equally well. impact process:- at first marynisha sat with the villagers in the body of 60-70 people. baithak me logon ne school me teacher nahi aane ke face bachon ki parahi prabhavit hoti hai au mid day meal bhi nahi ilti thi. it was decided in the meeting that applications will be written in the name of the beo of sundarpahari block and submitted to his office. nischit din ko 5 log beo ke office me gaye par wo nahi the. in his absence i applied to bpo neeraj chawdhri. mary nisha ne apna parichay diya aur camera par hi interview dikhaya jo usne shoot kiya tha. bpo ne unse kaha ki office me teachers ke duwara report jama ki jati hai aur ham tak nahi pahunch pate hain. aapka acha prayas hai, ham isme jald karwai karenge. bpo ne kaha ki jab video ban jayega toh office me bhi ek copy jama kar dijyega. within a month the department took action, now regular teachers are getting bachon ko impact_achieved_description: mukesh rajak did the community  screening in the kansjore village which comes under madhupur block in deoghar district. the purpose behind screening the video was to make the villagers aware about their right so that they can raise their voice against irregularities and negligences. the issue was in 2007 a private company was given the task of installing the required infrastructure to fulfill the need of electricity. 8 year later there is only few poles of this mission. villagers of this community has written multiple applications to the electricity board asking for the electrification work in this village to be completed.  mukesh talked to the gm and in 2013 the gm ensured him to work will be done in 2 or 3 months by the end of fiscal year 2013-14 but till now has not done anything. so when mukesh was in ranchi iu training that time mukesh thought there is a issue pending in which he has to work to resolve the problem. but this time he has to follow some other strategy. on saturday(14-02-15) from the training centre  he called the gm p. r. ranjan once again and asked about the update but that was not fruitful. so mukesh  decided it would be better to train the villagers so that they may give phone calls to the gm until they don�t get any impacts.  mukesh did the screening some of the iu videos and few part of  a film named satyagraha by prakash jha starring amitabh bacchan, ajay devgan, karrena kapoor , manoj bajpal etc in the led role and encouraged them to call the gm until you are not getting any result on the ground. and from today they have started calling the gm. right  now the gm is in tense and he has called the ae of the madhupur to see the problem asap. he has also started saying how many mobile phones are there in your village? i hope the work will be done but you all may also call to the gm so that it may also play vital in the process of impact or it shall pressurize the gm so that he will solve the problem. it took five months to light the village when the community got involved to change the scene of the village.

the main road in kasiadh village of cherhi panchayat, hazari baug district (jharakhand) was badly damaged and due to that 1500 people of 4 villages were facing problems. no official was paying attention on repairing it. the road was full of potholes and because that road was main road of the village many vehicles used to pass from it and used to generate a lot of dust which generally was making their houses and food dirty. the district collector and block development officer had also inspected the road they assured villagers to repair the road but nothing happened. villagers were demanding to tar the road so no dust would blow and then there would be no difficulties for people to travel. community correspondent chunnu hansda, who lives in the same village documented this issue in december 2013 and then discussed it with the village head and block development officer. as a result in december 2014, repairing of that road had been started and people were travelling more easily on it.

handpump, that was the source of drinking water for 35 people in the matigara sarak hamlet of aydega village, was broken down since the last two years. after making a video on this issue, cc warles surin met with the ward member (elected village representative) and screened the video. he later did the same with the village council head (gram pradhan) and subsequently the handpump was repaired.  a handpump, that was the source of drinking water for 35 people in the matigara sarak hamlet of aydega village, was broken down since the last two years. after making a video on this issue, cc warles surin met with the ward member (elected village representative) and screened the video. he later did the same with the village council head (gram pradhan) and subsequently the handpump was repaired.

sand blocks in chitpoor village of torpa block, khunti district (jharkhand) were mined for lakhs of rupees of sand and dumped in trucks and sent to ranchi but villagers were not getting benefit from that. when villagers went to dc (district collector) office, he forewarned them that none of such discussion would be addressed. the local block development office and the mining department have sold mining permits of these blocks to city contractors. there were around 250 to 300 laborers who were not getting their wages. in december 2012 community correspondent amit topno who lives in the scheduled area of chitpoor village, documented this whole issue and screened it to many villagers and officials as a result of that, many villagers raised their voice against this issue, they marched for their resolving this issue. after 3 years in september 2015, mining officer gave to manage 80% to the gram panchayat and 20% to mining department. - by sandhya marwada

in bhirakhap village, hazaribagh district, jharkhand two government school teachers did not receive their respective salary for over four years. the school in the village held regular classes for the children and without fail supported the education of these children irrespective of being unpaid. the issue was reported to every possible hierarchy in the government organization but to no affect it was shunned. the use of video documentation as a tool to provide justice is effectively visible in this context. our community correspondent chunnu hansda has worked closely in that area over different issues and as soon as he was informed about this mishap he decided to film the scenario with testimonies from the children as well. the video was then published at different platforms and was screened at the district collector’s office. dr. manish ranjan the district education officer at hazaribagh assured that the issue will be resolved and within 15 days the matter was acted upon. the fault was held to be a few paperwork approval at the panchayat level. as soon as the district education officer was informed about the hold-up, he acted upon the matter and got the papers at the panchayat approved. he sanctioned the salary and 18 months of their unpaid salary which stands out to be 90000 was cleared at once. he assured that the remaining amount will be transferred to their bank accounts within a month. his assurance even extended to the point of keeping a watchful eye on every teacher’s salary in the state and clearing past dues, if any. the children and the villagers have now seen an act of change which has reinforced their faith on media and the impact it can bring about.
