impact_achieved_description: sameer entered : xavier hamsay, or xavier 'dada' as he is fondly referred to, is an unashamed techno-geek who took to the technical aspects of indiaunheard like a fish to water. though he was not on the original list of community correspondents, xavier's passion for technology & fierce articulation on human rights issues enchanted the recruitment & training team, and he soon became an essential part of the jharkhandindiaunheard team. xavier hails fromwest singhbhum, one of jharkhand's largest districts. a core area of the tribal communities of jharkhand, it is nestled in a densely forested fertile river basin alternated by hills. this much coveted land is rich with minerals and has currently been conveniently categorized as part of the 'red corridor'.  xavier's frequent travels through the district take him to the remotest villages of west singhbhum. one such trip took him to mathagoda village in katwatola. anita bodra'shusband joseph died in november 2012. as per the indira gandhi national widow pension scheme as floated by the department of rural development, she was entitled to receive inr 400 per month as widow pension. however, because she hadn't yet received a copy of joseph's death certificate, she had not received any money. the village got together & filed an application on the 5th of december, 2012. however, the application disappeared in the bermuda triangle of bureaucracy. finally frustrated, anita turned to xavier 'dada' for help.  "when i heard anita's story, i spent some time with the villagers, researching the facts of this story. since i have already filmedother stories on similar issues, i knew that corruption was probably the key player in this story too. sure enough, i found that despite the villagers having submitted an application, bhushanbanra, the panchayat member in question hadn't bothered to respond. i filmed anita's testimony, and then i took about 8-10 villagers with me to my studio. i had also requested veronica bodra, the sarpanch, and bhushanbanra to join us. once in my studio, i loaded the video on my computer & screened it for everybody. then we all sat down & had an honest discussion about this. since i knew that corruption was the core problem here, i categorically stated that if issuing joseph's death certificate was being held back due to any individual attempting to siphon off money meant for anita, it was illegal, and mathagoda village would stand by me to ensure that these individuals would pay the price."  bhushanbodra immediately issued the death certificate, and anita began receiving her pension from february 2013. "i know this will seem a paltry payoff to most people. a single person in a small village benefitted from this video. but for anita, her world changed. it was a huge victory that we, as a community, had won together. her family was already fragmented because of poverty. her son was unable to complete his education & is now in odisha somewhere, slogging as a driver. her daughter enrolled in college with much difficulty, only because someone loaned anita the enrollment fees. and her story isn't something unique. many of my people suffer like this - they don't know anything about schemes available from the government to support them - even if they do, they don't know whom to approach, how to approach. the village headman, champamunda, in this case, was powerless to intervene on behalf of his people, because of threats from cheaters (sic). however, when he saw how much faith his people had in me, he too came on camera to record his testimony." anita is yet to receive her arrears. xavier has no intention of giving up. he whips out his little 'data book' where he jots copious notes about every video he's made. with nine videos to his name, he now knows the importance of preparation, research and documentation. he speaks of the lengthy process of identifying the relevant department to approach to facilitate change, and ways of approaching administration. "earlier, i'd hear a story & start filming immediately. now i prepare a list of b-rolls i want to capture, questions i'd like to ask. when i go up to question anybody, i can't just blast (sic) them with accusations. i need to have facts & data to validate what i'm saying. also, because there are so many people just waiting for me to mess up, i have to be extra certain with every cause i take up."  the cynicism creeps through when he talks of how he is currently under threat from certain citizens who are sitting back and reaping the benefits of other's broken dreams. however, despite the occasional disillusionment, xavier is determined to carry forth his father's legacy of being central to his tribal community's struggle for rights & recognition. "my people are disempowered because of poverty. their struggles for survival shrouds all other scarcity. i will change that with every story i film & follow up. it's crucial to be able to work together - if we sort out a system where we can sit down with administration and freely discuss our problems and come up with a solution, change is definitely possible. and of course, a camera helps!"  read also: directive principles of state policy, national social assistance programme (nsap)

condition of main road from chainpur to majhatoli in gumla district was in very bad condition and thousands of people were facing many problems due to that. number of accidents on that road had increased. villagers had given written application several times to the dc and road construction department but none action was taken. community correspondent pramila ekka who lives in the same village made video about it and showed it to the community, gram pradhan and in the road construction department. he assured them to repair the road and he did it. after a year of making a video, construction of new road was started. - by sandhya marwada

gumla district, raidih block, . a half constucted bridge on sankh river flowing between sarnatoli and mariamtoli village wast being completed since 8 years. during the rainny season the village acroos the river were cutoff from the mainland for more than 4 months every year. life was almost impossible since the half constructed bridge was affecting education, development, healthacre and much more. cc filmed this issue and discussed this issue with bridge constructing officials. a few days later the constrcution of the bridge began and the bridge is complete in todays date.

the road in phakodi village built by the aluminium conductor steel reinforce, a tata company, was in very bad condition. 200 villagers in the villages couldn't get by during the rains. children often got injured walking or playing on the road. acsr . cc mohan bhuyan held a community meeting and wrote down an application to the incharge of tata's rural development society. cc also screened video in community. after 2 months the road was fully repaired.

the post man in cc xavier hamsay's village was not doing his job of delivering letters. the letters would keep lying in the post office. this issue, that affected 7000 people in the village was solved after xavier made the video.

5 km road in hatimara dakin tola village of sitarampur panchayat was in bad condition since 4 years. a total population of 600 was suffering as they commute on the road. cc is a residenst of the same village council thus she was aware of teh issue and teh issue was also published in local newspapers. cc filmed a video on this issue and discussed the issue in the village. in the following days the local mla was in neighbouring village for a visit where cc was also visited. during this meeting with mla cc discussed the issue with him and also submitted an application. mla told cc that the work of repairing the road is under process and will began in short time. 3 months later the repair of the road began and the 5 km road is completely repaired now.
impact_plan: video bena kar screening karna aur awaden bena kar adhikari ko dena.

impact_achieved_description: ration card was not having for 2 poor women like manju devi and shanti devi, women of bpl families - sasbeda, panchayat - puvi sasbeda, block - gomiya, district- bokaro, and district- jharkhand. these people were suffering a lot. on 11th august 2015, i made a video and screened all the staff in the block with our state coordinator and then went to screen these district level officers to see the people given to dc sahib and now all rice cards of all the four families made all rice. are picking up and are happy now.
impact_corroboration_details: 91 - 9431733648 nirmal kumar, block supply officer. gomia, bokaro, jharkhand.

impact_achieved_description: the anms have stopped taking money from all the patients after the post delivery, after raising the voice against them by the sahiyas of mahuadabar cluster along with some families. in the beginning i thought they may stop this custom only with those people who have raised their voice or participated in the process but the scenario is totally different. they have stopped taking the money from all the patient coming to the hospital and there are so many sahiyas who are our witnesses.  but i think they may once again start this custom with those people or sahiyas who are not aware about this incident which has happened inside the hospital.

impact_plan: video bena kar screening karna aur bivag me awaden dena.
fill up the form and submit it to circle officer of borio block.
fill up the form and submit it to circle office of borio block

impact_achieved_description: under pradhan mantri vidhwa pension yojana, there is a provision for pension to every poor and helpless widow, but parvati devi of panchayat siyari village chittu of bokaro district gomia block of jharkhand state, who was widowed for more than 10 years, has been deprived of pension for three to four years. even after filling the form, he was not getting the benefit of pension. i had made a video on this problem on june 9, 2015. after making the video, i contacted the chief to show him the video. , went to the block and contacted the block development officer, showed him the video and sent the video through whatsapp and kept reminding him by calling once in three to four months, in this way he started getting pension from august 2017, me or the head of our panchayat in working i got a lot of support from mr. bunty who helped me even when he did not come inside his panchayat, so i thank him from the bottom of my heart.
impact_raised_awareness: screened/shared a video about the problem
impact_steps_followed_at_local_level: making a social media post, explaining the problem and showing some of the footage
screening_shared_to: community members, panchayat official, bdo, news outlets or journalists
themes: an entitlement problem - meaning a government anti-poverty scheme that people apply for, a material problem (eg delivery of a service, repair of infrastructure)
underlying_reason_of_issue: low quality service delivery of entitlement provision

impact_achieved_description: dalit family getting their due ration which had been stopped because of a personal fight.in this cases official corruption and neglect had resulted in beneficiaries being denied their government entitlements.

construction of a well sanctioned under the mgnrega program to a poor family was lying incomplete for last one and half years. mukesh met the woman who was running pillar to post to get her work done. she had already appraised the village council head and the ward member but it was of no use. cc mukesh rajak made a video on her plight and followed up with impact plans, including filing an application under the right to information act, and the well got constructed in 7 days. mukesh has often used the rti in his work to get rightful entitlements for his community.

360 old aged villagers belonging to 5 villages were not receiving the old age monthly pension of rs.550 initiated by the government. they had submitted several applications to thier respective village head however they never received any response. cc filmed a video on thsi issue. then cc called a community meeting and decided that they will visit the block development officer (bdo) withan application. in next days, cc with 25 old aged visited the bdo office and submitted the application. after submitting the application cc also kept pressurizing the newly elected vilalge head to clear all the formalities from his side so that the pension can be released. 6 months later all the 360 old age villagers received thier due pension.

tulsi and the community had the meeting weekly. they did couple of times. they decided to to take rally. there was rally in jadugora for the arresting kamal singh at jadugora thana. the application was given to jadugora thana prabhari. but the action was not taken by him. later on community decided to do the dharna before dc of the dist. around 40 people were involved in this dharna. zila parisahd purna mandal and the team submit the application to dc. then he forwarded the appliction to sp. after four months kamal sing was arreseted. now kamal singh is in jail. kamal sing said when i am out from jail then i will return money. community says, first we want money then only the case can be withdraw.
impact_plan: screening of isu video near sp.
target_official: purbi singhbhum - supdt.of police rural- sulander kumar sinha

impact_achieved_description: somali devi and 30 other people of cilga panchayat were not paid their old age pension for the last 6 months. cc aparna marandi made a video on this. the mere fact that a video was being filmed on this matter resulted in action and somali devi and others started getting their pensions.

somra munda of jamdih village hadnt received any benefit from the indira awas housing scheme from the time teh scheme had been implemented in village. scheme madated bpl card for teh scheme benefit. somra munda wasnt enlsited in bpl list, however he was economically weak and his house structure had worsened. he  had filled up forms for teh ebnefit in gram sabha several times but his name was never lsited. cc filmed a video on this sissue and held a meeting with community for planning. as planned they approached the bdo and submitted him teh application. the video was screened too to which bdo assured them help. the cc also screened teh video to village cocuncil head who was also crucial in enlsiting teh caraters name in teh scheme. as the year was passing teh governemnt removed teh manadtory condition of bpl and apl listing from teh scheme. during the upcoming gramsabha a year later where teh cc was also present, somras name was lsited in the scheme. somra later received teh hosuing amount rs. 130000 in his account in three installments.

issue - surujmuni devi is 63 years old but not getting old age pension. she is from dmbardih village, block - narayanpur and panchayat rupdih. impact process - surujmuni devi ko old agepension nahi mil rahi thi, is samasya ke upar karanti ne video banayi thi. video baanane ke baad unhone awedan likha aur prkahnd vikas padadhikari ko awedan diya. awedan dene ke baad bhi kranti ne kaphi lambe samay tak iska follow up kiya.  abhi surujmuni devi ko old age pension shuru ho gayi hai. english: surujmuni devi aged 63 years, residing in dambardih village, narayanpur block, pancahyat rupdih wasnt receiving the old age pension rs.600 entitled for old age by government. she is illiterate and doesnt know whereabouts of the process availing the pension. cc being of the same community filmed the video and held a discussion and planning meeting wth surujmuni. they wrote down an application in the name of bdo. in later days cc along with the suruj submitted the application along with necessary documents to bdo and discussed the issue with them. cc in the following days lept on following the issue via phone calls to bdo. after much wait suruj started reciving her pension.

300 several people employed under contract basis in bsnl for minor jobs like peons in khunti distrct & across jharkhand were not being paid for several months. the empolyees are poor & have no other source of livlihood. cc shot a issue video. cc screened the video to labour officer during the one day protest at ranchi bsnl head office , due to which the officer became aware of the problem. later 2 officials arrived at the bsnl exchange office for the investigation & took away the details of employees & number of days they have woked. some days later the employees recived thier wages for teh first time after 7 months. only 3 months remaining. cc nirmala also assisted & anand hembrom called manager too.

13 tribal labourers who worked at jaipal jayant singh farmhouse for 18 months were not being paid by the owner. the labourers worked in the floriculture farmhouse. cc filmeda video on this issue.he also made the unpaid labourers aware of thier rights. cc along with these unpaid labourers vsisted the labor officer and screnned the video in his office. they also submitted an application in teh same office. 15 days latera notice was sent from labor department to teh fram owner to pay the wages. on 24 august 2016 the farm owner called all the labourers to collect thier wages. all teh 13 labourers have received thier wages .

issue:- the villagers of cherabaar of chainpur block of palamu district are not getting the ration for three months. although they have cards. impact process:- some people of cherabar village had gone to the mla regarding their problem but the mla was not in his residence. anil guria advised him to go to ruby kumari, bdo of chainpur block and talked about helping. anil talked to bdo then bdo - ruby kumari called him in her chamber and heard the problem. they told that their dealer is not giving them ration since 3 months, on asking for ration they say that ration is not coming at all. she told those people that she would go to their village the next day. the next day anil gudiya had reached the village, bdo did not reach there but sent the census officer (jss) there as his representative. jss-madan ram took cognizance of the problem and assured to take action against the dealer and get the ration again. after 2 months, the villagers started getting ration again and the old dealer was replaced by a new dealer. english: the villagers of cherabar village, chainpur block, palamu district were not being given ration by the ration dealer in the village since 3 months. the villagers had valid ration cards but even then the ration dealer never gave them ration. cc filmed a video on thsi issue. community had visited the mla regarding this problem however they could not meet him since he wasn't present at his place. cc and community decided to visit block development officer named ruby (bdo). bdo carefully heard the issue from cc and community. bdo assured cc and community taht she will take action and either visit the village herself or will send her representative. next day, bdo sent census officer (jss) in the village for investigation of the matter. on investigation jss found out that whatever villagers were saying was true. he assured villagers that they would get their ration soon and also an action would be taken against the dealer. after 2 months a new ration dealer was allotted in the village while previous ration dealers license was cancelled.

impact_plan: apllication has t be written with the community in the name of bdo and has to be submitted.

impact_achieved_description: friend of cc, a retired schoolteacher, told him about swang village, wherein construction of a road that was to be made using plain cement concrete (pcc) was made with bricks. intriguingly, the cc warles surin instead of making the story on material he decided to make the story on less wages given to workers as notice board of the project was missing . speaking with the supervisors & junior contractors on site cc realized that people are being employed for less wages ie rs.120 (as against the correct amount of rs.148). villagesr were unaware of their entitled wages. on one of community screening organized by the cc, 200 people had gathered and warles made them aware of their rights to correct wages. the next day the went to the block development officer (bdo), the district collector (dc) and the labour department. after a few days the dc issued an order to halt all work & money commissioned to this contractor across the whole block of jaldega. the sub-contractors were all immediately instructed to release full payment to all labourers across jaldega. the villagers & cc then wrote another letter stating that complete wages were being paid.

the condition of the 11 km of road from lachragar to jaldega was so bad that it took more than an hour to reach. besides, many from the 35 villages using this road, had met with accidents because of the big potholes in the road. cc warles surin gave apllication to the bdo and screened video to him. bdo said this is high level issue but promised that he'll do his best to solve it. application was forwarded to the dc (district collector). the issue was that an earlier tender issued to repair this road was of less amount and couldn't have covered the risen prices of materials required and so no contracters were willng to accept the tender. this tender was revised after the cc submitted the application. a few days later rs.14 lakhs sanctioned for the road repair was released . pothholes were filled and the road is now fully repairedand it only takes 15 minutes to cover the 11 km distance.

the government runs red card and bpl card which are given to the people who are below poverty line. under public distribution system, they are provided ration and oil at very low cost. but in ramajari basti simdega district, kolebira block, (jharkhand) 15 people�s name had been struck off from the ration list. their families were big and they were not getting proper ration and due to that they were facing many problems. they asked the ration dealer about the reason of striking off their name but he didn�t reply well. community correspondent warles surin made a video about the issue in september 2014. he screened it to the gram pradhan and villagers also talked to the ration dealer and ward members. as a result after a month (october 2014) those 15 villagers started receiving their ration (30 kg rice) regularly.             new description :  in ramjadi basti of chattri village 50 people from 10 families were not getting their food supplies from the fair price shop (under the public distribution system) for the last 4 years. in a survey held in village in 2010 the shop keeper had wrongly cut the names of these 10 families because the primary card holders were dead. this was done without informing the families. new ration cards were made for the surviving family members but they weren't aware of this. cc warles surin met the village council head (gram pradhan) and the new shop keeper along with the family members. the cc advised the shop keeper to match his ration beneficiary list to that approved by the block office. the shop keeper after matching the two lists found that the omitted people were actually eligible for ration and he started giving ration to the families from the following month.

kamal purthy was asked by residents of his village to make a video to convey the difficulties they were facing due to the delay in releasing the funds due to them under the indira awas yojana. this scheme provides funds for impoverished families to build homes. the shooting began. the villagers began to articulate their troubles and their demands. word spread throughout the village that soon these powerful and discontent voices would move the issue beyond the village, beyond jharkhand and present it before the world. the officials began to feel the heat. within 4 days, before kamal kishor could extract his footage from his camera and script his closing anchor-piece, the installment due was released. the people rejoiced. their houses would now be built. they would soon have a roof on their heads. before they knew it, the process had turned into the desired change.iu impact: homes built by people's media, pandrasali

impact_achieved_description: pooja : the bridge on the banai river had been broken for as long as three and a half years, and has been the root cause for the people and children going to school to be at constant risk. the main mandi is on the other side of the bridge, which makes it difficult for the farmers to sell their grown fruits and vegetables. rajen guria lives in khunti district, and he made a video on the problem. he screened the video for the community members and accompanied them to meet with the rural development authority, where the concerned official assured they would start the reconstruction within three to four months. when it did not happen, rajen sent the video to sub-divisional magistrate and then had a meeting with him. the whole process took one and a half years before the bridge could be rebuilt for ease in travelling.

in behradih village of kodarwa district of domchas block, a panchayat bhavan was started constructing in june 2008 but due to irresponsibleness of the contractor it was incomplete. village head gave written application to the block development officer regarding the issue but nothing happened. community correspondent dimpy singh, who lives in a nearby village, came to know about the issue. she documented this issue and talked to the head of the village. after 7 months construction of panchayat bhawan (building) was completed.  - by sandhya marwada

impact_achieved_description: nearly 25 km of road between charhi and naiyo, ramgarh district, mandu block (jharkhand) was in a bad shape. the repair and upkeep of that road was the responsibility of central coalfields ltd. (ccl). there was a rampage use of the stretch of that route by coal dumper trucks. the helpless villagers had no other alternative than that road. travelers had hard time commuting on the road because of the huge potholes and slurry surface. community correspondent basanti soren, who uses the same road, documented this issue and gathered people. she also went to meet the po and as a result of that after more than 1 year, in december 2015 the road was repaired by ccl. - by sandhya marwada

community correspondent mukesh rajak from deoghar district, jharkhand heard of a school where a single teacher was not only taking all the classes across subjects and grades but also running the canteen. 112 dalit children from 5 or 6 villages were attending the school. mukesh showed his video to the block education officer who immediately recruited another teacher to the school and he is still pursuing the matter as per educational standards in india, there have to be atleast three teachers in a school of 112.

people from kumargadiya, a neighboring village, called mukesh and informed that teachers in their school were not attending classes and asked mukesh to help them. mukesh motivated the ask villagers to sign a petition against the corrupt teachers. community met the government official (beo), shared a report on the mismanagement in the school. mukesh  also presented the video footage and a petition,which included over 50 signatures of people from the village. on receiving this petition and after watching the video the beo took action at once and punished the teachers. while visiting the schools she also noticed the crumbling infrastructure and lack of proper facilities. she personally supervised the problem and got the building renovated. the children of over 150 families in the district now receive a higher quality of education. this video have ended negligence by the teacher at a school in belatand and around 50 children from some of the most underprivileged families in the village are now receiving better quality of education.

hadtopa primary school of jamshedpur potka block in east singbhum district (jharkhand) had 35 students but due to only one teacher since 2008, school was not being conducted properly. students and teacher both were facing many problems due to lack of teacher. community correspondent tulsi hembrom, who belongs to the same community made a video about the issue and discussed with the community people to give a written application to block education officer to get one more teacher within 5 months. . community prepared the application for one more teacher so that school runs smoothly. they had submitted the application to block education officer and visited her with the community. after seven months, in march 2015 a new teacher was appointed into the school.
impact_plan: have the meeting in community and prepare the application in the name block education officer.

impact_achieved_description: chunnu hansdas  "all work and no pay for jharkhand teachers" was his first ever video as an iu correspondent. he had made this to help two school teachers in the government school in birakhap village of hazaribagh district who had been working without salaries for over 4years! using the video made by chunnu, video volunteers launched a petition on change.org to help create pressure on the district administration. this strategy strengthened chunnus efforts to convince the district commissioner of the urgency of the issue. with over 4100 signatures and a very strong video, the dc took up the issue immediately and within a month the teachers received rs. 90,000/- each that was due to them. they now receive regular monthly salaries.                                                                                                                                                                                                               background: siddharth and tasmeel from change.org have done great work with the petition and we have over 3000 signatures in less than a week. the district collector has received calls from over 50 people and is ready to take action.  chunnu and anand met with the dc and screened the video on anand's laptop. they also showed him the petition webpage with 3000+ signatures. chunnu interviewed the dc on his plan of action and duration in which impact will take place. june 2012: the teachers have received salary from 2010 till date.

sameer : 18/11/2016 : in february 2012 a woman from  khunti district, dadigutu panchayat, village daeo was selected as new anaganwadi helper by cdpo in prseence of village council memebers. however she wasnt given any joining letter at that time and she continued to work then. she kept on asking her officail joining letetr but she was always avoided by officails. she approcahed cc for help. cc filmed the issue. cc discussed issue with cdpo. a big video screening was organised in the village which was attended by all vv team in ranchi ,officials, &  villagers. finally in december 2015 a review process was done for selection of same woman helper by cdpo, village council members and superviser. she has been given official appointment letter and her salary is started now.
impact_plan: patr ko cdpo ke pass la kar gay thay tab new cdpo bolay es ka mamla kalyan bivag ma ruka huwa hai mujhay es ke baray ma nahi pata hai.

impact_achieved_description: there was a primary school in meromguttu village of bandgaon block, (jharkhand) which was closed since past 3 years and it was working only on papers. waste and dirt was accumulated in the corridors of the school also near the old building of school a new building�s construction was started but it was also left incomplete and the structure was about to collapse. there were no teachers in the school to teach children. the villagers were demanding to repair both buildings and appointing new teachers in the school. community correspondent basanti purti, who is a resident of the same village documented the issue and discussed the issue with the block education officer. he assured that he will take some action and he did it. in november 2013 repairing of the building was started and a new teacher was also appointed due to which 24 students started getting education in school properly.
impact_plan: samuday ke sath awaden bana kar beo ko denay ka bola gaya.

impact_achieved_description: 60 tribal students staying in tribal welfare boys hostel, khunti district have been facing prolems. there are 16 toilets out of which only 2 are working, all teh window doors are broken, ceilings are cracked, there no cook in hostel, solar panels not working too for many years (even the hostel building has not been painted for years). students & hostel incharge several times applied to welfare department for the repair but the officials never took it seriously nor visited hostel anytime. all students are poor & somehow managed to buy ration, cook themselves, cover windows with newspaper, plastic. cc made a video & it was screened at international tribal day program attended by total 1500 students & officials. cc then held  ascreening in hostel & discussed issue with students. a decision was taken to meet the dwo. cc & students approached dwo , screened the video & appealed her to take action. (officer asked cc to meet her regularly till work is done). by then a letter (district judge) was received by dwo which mentioned 8 hostels that required emergency repairwhich include tribal students hostel. dwo informed this to cc, & then cc used this letter copy as a proof & met pwd officers (asking them until when will the hostel be repaired & to issue a tender). then the tender was issued for reparing. in todays date doorswindows are repaired, ceiling is plastered,( this is the first repairing in lifetime of hostel)

the torakel primary school in tirla village is just 4km from the district education officer's building. and yet, many of the facilties guaranteed under the right to education act are absent in this school: there is no door or windows on the wall, no toilets, no boundry wall, no roof on the kitchen. cc amita tuti made this video as part of the national video audit campign by vv and followed up with the deo's office. the school now has all the facilities it requires.

the building of thakar bapa tribal students hostel in khunti was in a bad state since 3-4 years: broken windows and doors, leaky roof, broken toilets,  rusted pipes and gutters and no cook. cc amita tuti made a video and she screened it during the international tribal day program attended by1500 students and officials. the cc then held  a screening in the hostel and discussed the issue with and strategized action with the students. a decision was taken to meet the dwo. the cc and the students met the dwo, screened the video and appealed her to take action. she was responsive and asked the cc to meet her regularly till repairs were done. in the meanshile she received a letter from the district judge that listed 8 hostels that required urgent repairs. the list included thakar bapa hostel and the dwo informed this to the cc. cc amita took a copy of this letter and met the public works department and pushed them to issue a tender for repairs. after much follow up by amita, the repairs began. toay the hostel has new doors and windows repaired, ceiling is replastered and pipes fixed. an incomplete wing was also completed. this is the first repairs undertaken since the hostel was built.

in the upgraded middle school nawadih, due to lack of boundary wall and dirty toilets, 286 children of the school had a lot of trouble for playing and thinking. there was a pond near the village in which the children used to go for defecation. the child died by drowning, the teacher had applied several times but due to the conflict between the school and the village, the four walls of the school were not surrounded, i came to know about this problem from the villagers. and i requested the community, no change process has been done on this problem from the community. i made a video on 1/1/2015. and in janbari itself, a meeting was held with some people of the village and in the call to action, you gave the number of block development officer narayal ram in the video. in which many calls were made by me and you people, due to which the officer called me after getting upset and said that you make a change video and put it on youtube because people are troubling me, on which i told them that you are there if dibari gets done, i will make a video and give it to you, because there was no change till then and then the four walls were made and the toilet was cleaned at the same time.
impact_corroboration_details: ashish kumar gramin, anita devi gramin, sunita devi education committee chairman

underlying_reason_of_issue: low quality service delivery of entitlement provision, the community is ignorant about this problem

impact_achieved_description: there was no boundry, no playground in the primary school of birsa tola village of mahuwatand pancahayt. also there was only one common toilet for all which wasnt functioning and all students had to go out to releive themselves in open space. cc filmeda video on this issue and discussed probable solutions with community and school authority. rte act of 2009 states that each school should have a seperate toilet for boys and girls. after filming the video, basanti soren had the followed up with the (block education officer) beo. authorities tooka time of one year to sanctioned the toilet for the school. now the toilet is constructed and is being used by school children of primary school of birsa tola.

sheela malto, a resident of goda pahar in borio block of sahebganj district, participated in class 8 in anusuchit janjati vidyalaya bandarkola borio. vidyalaya headmaster nikunj and hostel warden adhikak arun kumar akela leveled rape charges against sheela and she was expelled from the school in january 2015. shikha ne video banaya hai in feb 2015. jaisevidyalay me toilet nahi hai, nahane ki beostha nahi hai. the larks go to the jungle to go to the toilet and think about the school's spring. after meeting sheela, i came to know that the teachers are also acting astutely with chatron. sahebganj ke dc umesh prasad ko saari baat batayi gayi aur video clip bhi dikhaya gaya me camera. after a few months, sheela got admitted back to school. ------------------sameer++english: sheela malto, a tribal of goda pahar village, borio block, sahebganj district, was studying in class 8 of scheduled tribes school. in january 2015 sheela was removed from school by school headmaster and hostel superintendent trough false allegations. the thing was sheela was speaking loud about the peoblems in the school which wasn't okay with the schaal headmaster. there weren't proper toilets hence students had to defecate in open. there weren't proper bathrooms since they had to bathe in the open using a handpump. even the teachers were sexually harassing the girl students. cc filmed a video on this issue and approached the district collector with the issue. cc screened the video to dc. a few months later sheela was again called into the school and resumed her education.

there are 351 children left in saraikela district's hudu schools and there are only 3 teachers who are doing well. sujeeta showed the video to the teachers and went to the sikcha samiti. teacher ne awedan teachers ko pehle hi de chuka tha par department se koi teacher nahi diya gaya tha. sujeeta ne sikcha samiti ke kuch sadasaya ko karke karke beo ke paas gaye aur video ka screening kiya. beo did not give assurance. in january 2016 there was appointment of 1 teacher in hudu school. 351 students. this was largely affecting the students' education and also made it very difficult for the three teachers present in the school. cc filmed a video on this issue and screened the video to teahers and village school committee. the present teachers had already submitted applications in the past for additional teachers but no action had been taken. cc along with a few members of school village committee approached block education officer and screened the video to him. beo assured that he will appoint new teachers as soon as possible. few days later a new teacher was appointed in the school.

rte, 2009 states that there must be at least one teacher for every 30 students. such was not the case in karika government school, where there were only 4 male teachers and 1 female teacher for 375 students, including high school where no teacher was present. neither the school management, nor the education department made an effort to take an appropriate action. xavier hamsay lives in west singbhum district, and he made a video on the issue, held three screenings for the community. the principal of the school attended the meeting and met the zila shiksha adhikari to submit the complaint application. xavier met the block education officer, who got scared after watching the video and never saw him again despite numerous efforts to schedule an appointment from the cc. meanwhile, he would also take regular updates from the principal on the progress. in the month of may, rajya sachiv came to the school, so xavier mobilized the students to speak for them. some of the students also called the office of zila pariksha adhikari but were warned to not call again, or else would be sued. the principal and teacher of the jalmay school assisted the cc to write another application, and after one week, 2 teachers were appointed, easing the education of children from a total of 4 villages.
underlying_reason_of_issue: low quality service delivery of entitlement provision

impact_achieved_description: issue video was made on march 2015, after which cc talked to forest department officials if mahendra was working there. they said , no one with this name is working with the department. cc explained what the matter was and then took the victim to police station taljhari to register an fir. after which on 15th jan 2016, mahendra returned the money to raami paharin. out of rs 8000, advocate dilip kumar ghosh of rajmahal court kept rs 2000 with himself and gave in written that this money will also be given when final statement from raami in the case was recorded.

in the village aidega of kolebira block, simdega district (jharkhand), there was a pond of 15 acres, which was infested by water hyacinth and people of that area was facing many difficulties in taking bath and cultivating from past 10 years. farmers, whose fields were below pond level, were the most affected. in rainy season, hyacinth used to wash away and spread in nearby farms and due to that farmers were not able to cultivate rice in that area since last two and a half year. farmers were told to get compensation but they got nothing. villagers had organized meetings, prepared papers and sent it to the block many times but nobody listened or paid attention. community correspondent warles surin documented this issue and screened it in the community and wrote an application with the villagers. then he gave the application to the village head. after a year of submitting the application cleaning of hyacinth started and it took 2 years to clean completely. people were then able to use that pond water for their daily use.                   new description : like many villages in india, ayedega has come up around a body of water, in its case a 15 acre pond. the pond is the life of the munda tribal inhabitants of the village. water from the pond is used by the villagers in every facet of their lives. they use the water for everyday needs like drinking, bathing, irrigating their fields and raising their cattle. the fish and snails caught from the pond contribute to the cooking pot. last seven years water hyacinth (an invasive weed) had created unforetold havoc to life and livelihood in this small community. a tightly enmeshed mat of water hyacinths clogged the pond making it difficult for the villagers and the cattle to source the everyday requirement of water. the ecological balance of the area had been messed with. the number of fish in the pond had dipped. during monsoons, the hyacinths flooded along with the water. they invaded and settleled onto the ploughed fields. this natural dumping of the plant has had an adverse effect on the quality of the soil and the produce. the villagers were sick of this aquatic menace. they had complained many times to the authorities and received promises of immediate action. six years had passed and the village had seen no steps taken by the village or block authorities. some villagers volunteered to wade into the water and do some clearing. but that was hardly enough. cc warles surin became aware of the situation during his routine visit to the village. the tender for removing the hycinth had already been sanctioned at the district, but funds were embezzeled by the village chief hira mani samad. the villagers called warles to make a video on this matter. the cc along with community went to the panchayat to submit an application and show the video. the village chief (vc) refused to sign a receiving copy of the application. the cc warned the vc that the matter will be escalated to the block development officer and that his role will be investigated. the village chief got the point and the very next day he employed 5 workers on his own money to remove the hycinth. it took a year to fully clean the pond and it is today totally free of the weed.
impact_plan: make community awaden and give it to bdo.

impact_achieved_description: agaria tola village is nesteld between two mines, one run by the tata company and the other one by central coal field limited. tata company started 101 yeras ago & ccl in 1993. 150 people reside in this village.these companises had promised the village a steady supply of water (for drinking and domestic use) when their common lands were acquired for mining. however, both companies had failed to keep their promise and were sending only 1 or 2 trucks eery week or other week. this situation got acute during summers. cc mohan bhuyan made a video on this issue and did community screenings of the video. 2 months later the company installed drinking water pipeline from chutua river and connected it with two large storage tanks in the village from where the villagers are now fillnig water. the supply is regular

in jitratongri village a big herd of 14 wild elephants destroyed standing crops, raized to ground 16 houses, and killed a man kartik manjhi. people have been sighitng wild elephants in their neighborhood months before this incident and it was even flashed in tv and newspapers. villagers had phoned the forest officials several times to warn them about the elephants. the forest department is required to arrange for torches, fireworks and bring in elephant evading experts when such information is received. on phone about the nearing elephants but no action was taken by the department. as a result of this negligence, the villagers had to suffer huge losses and a man died. the forest range officer came to village upon learing about the death and handed rs.25,000 to the wife of the deceased. the compensation in such cases should be rs.200,000. besides, none of the villagers were not compensated for their lost crops or broken houses. cc mohan bhuyan made a video on this matter, mobilized the community and went to the forest divisional office in rangad and met with the assistant conservator of forests (acf). mohan and the villagers showed hiim the video and appraised him of all issues. the acf wanted formal paperwork (written complaints) which mohan organized and got it signed by the village head and thanna prabhari (vilalge sherif). mohan also organized for the medical report of the deceased and all the paper work was submitted to the forest divisional officer. mohan screened the video again while submitting the papers. after 1 month of submission villagers were fully compensated for all losses for which they had been waiting from 9 months.

during 1980 the government did a survey in bandgao village and constructed a road. once again in 2008 the government came in to survey and started the road work without consent of the villagers. their sacred groves (sarna) and agriculture land were to be destroyed by this project. about 15 villagers were loosing their land, many others were loosing thier jackfruit trees, mango trees and mahua trees, and a total of 3500 people were to lose their sarna by this new road. the sarna was not only sacred to the people of bandgao but also to 39 other villages in that area. people were protesting this project since the they were not informed about this and their consent, which is legally required, not taken. the villagers spoke to the contractor many times but was that was useless. cc xavier hamsay intervened and made a video and screened the video in the village where the contractor were also present. the screenings and discussions also galvanized those villagers who hadn't yet taken a position on this matter. eventually the road work was stopped the route changed so as not to destroy trees, agriculutral land and their sarna.

impact_plan: cc is advised to prepare an application and complain to sp, pakur since local police station could not find solution.
target_official: superintendent of police, pakur, ajay linda- 06435222091

impact_achieved_description: cc made application with the people who were claiming compensation and met co, basiya, burain saaru. the issue video was screened. though he received the application he was not keen on taking the matter urgently. vv jharkhand state office made calls and communicated with youtube links of the video as well as other videos which reflected good work that shanti was doing. after some time, officer responded to the cause and got the amount cleared and transferred to jafar khan and other's account. it was verified that  the amount was released by the office and had reached to their respective accounts but jafar khan, he used the money to repair his house , but was not updating the passbook. after some time cc helped the character get his passbook updated and took video shots of it.  english:  the houses of 10 families from kirinkela vilalge, pancahyat moreng, block basiya, gumla district had been damaged by haevy rains in august 2017. vilalgers demanded disaster funds for themselvse from governemnt hwoever they did not receiev any. cc filmed a video on thsi issue and held a community meeting where the video was screemned and application addressing the co was signed by all. next cc along with community vsiited teh co office with application and screened video to him. he assured of help. after a regular follow up by cc and videovolunteers jhakhnad office team teh officer approved teh compensation amount to teh families. they received teh amount in thier passbooks.

impact_plan: talk to health prabhari of markacho, narendra prasad tiwari and then forward the case to cs - bp chwarsiya

impact_achieved_description: mukesh rajak made a video titled 'pay fine, take education' that was published on the 30th of june 2010, about a school in his village where teachers were taking bribes from students for teaching, conducting exams, and other activities. he showed it to the block education officer (beo) who went to visit the school and suspended the headmaster. the corruption ended and the students are very happy that they can study for free. afterwards, people from kumargadiya, a neighboring village, called mukesh and informed him that teachers in their school were not attending classes and asked him to help them. once again, mukesh contacted the beo.she took action at once and punished the teachers. while visiting the schools, the beo also noticed the crumbling infrastructure and lack of proper sanitation facilities. she personally supervised the problem and got the building renovated. thanks to mukesh's work, the children of over 500 families in the district began to receive a higher quality of education.
second installment of indira awaas yojana was given to the beneficiary family within four days of the video being shot.

saal se handpump kharab tha,vdo banne k 10 din k baad effect ho gya, vdo banne k baad samuday ne application likha, bdo k pass application likha gya tha,21 july 2016 ko bdo ko applicatin dene gay the magar bdo se mulakat nai hua, on 25th july ko phir se bdo k pass gay us din mulakat hua bdo se, bdo ne water department k je ka number diya aur bdo office se hi halima ji ko bola ko call je ka ka lagane ko bola ko je se baat karne par jen kaha ki 2 din k andar hand pump thik kar denge, 30 julay ko mistri aya aur hand pump ko chek kiya aur chalagya logo ne kosish kiya, magar kuchnahi hua, vdo bana kv kuch nahi hoga ye mudda halima k liye prathishta k baat ho gya tha, ab log halima ka pahle se jada maan saman karne lage hai, hand pump banjane se janta ab kafi khush hai : there was no water supply in mohada panchayat at mohada village of 1000 residents since two years. the water filter plant equipments which were provided were no more functioning and thus water was not being transported to village through pipelines. villagers were using water from river. the handpump in the village was also not functioning since a year. cc filmed video on this issue. cc and community wrote down application in the name of block development officer (bdo). then they went to the office 2 times since bdo wasn't present in his office during one visit. bdo gave the phone number of junior engineer (je) during and asked to call him. cc and bdo both spoke to je. then je assured them that they would visit the village within a couple of days. as je assured, repairmen arrived in the village in a couple of days and the handpump was repaired.

success. the bridge was broken, a new bridge is under construction and finished. though, the complaint was raised by cc and screening was done before bdo and sdo, rad construction department gumla. it it's own course administration started construction of new bridge. cc regularly visited site of construction and took shots and interviews during the process. since this issue was of district administration and the bridge was needed by thousands of people using that road, administration with the due procedure of things was successful in building the bridge. cc kept track of the construction going on.  english: the bridge on the koel river was cracked yaers ago and thus the villagers were not able to use the bridge. they had to cross the river via a longer terraineuos distance. cc filmed teh video on this issue . cc held a community meeting in the village and discussed the issue. cc along with the community visited the bdo and sdo office and submitted the application. the officails assured of help. since this issue was of district administration and the bridge was needed by thousands of people using that road, administration with the due procedure of things was successful in building the bridge. cc kept track of the construction going on. soon the construction of a new bridge began.

amit topno ne pani ki samsya ke upar 3 saal pehle video banaya tha. the problem was that apart from 20 families of khasuwa toli of purvi panchayat of khunti district, there was a problem of pine water for 500 years. gaon walon ko kapra dhone, nahane ke liye 3-4 km nadi padta tha. had to go to other's place even for pine water. jivan horo ko pine ka pani ke liye liye road cross karke paani hota tha. there is also a possibility of accident in the body. sabse first toh amit topno ne video banaya aur video banane ke baadsamuday me dikhaya aur application unke saath milkar likha. after these things happened, the rights of phd were shown to omkarnath and khaswa toli got rid of the water problem. amit wrote an adhan to make water available to torpa's vidhyak polus surin as well. in logon ne assurance diya. after 3 years water supply unit was established by phd. now water supply is being done through pipeline in every house. i am happy in the logo of the vehicle. english: 500 families in khsuwa toli, purvi panchayat in khunti district were facing drinking water crisis. the villagers had to go to a river 3-4 kms away to bathe and wash clothes. they even had to go far places to get drinking water. jivan horo had to cross a busy road to get drinking water which could lead to accidents. firstly amit topno made a video on the issue. he then submitted an application with the community. after this the video was shown to public health department officer, omkarnath and he was informed of the crisis. amit also wrote an application to the legislator of torpa, polus surin. they gave him an assurance. after 3 years a water supply unit was placed by the public health department. now all the households are getting supply of water through pipelines. the people are happy now.
impact_plan: awaden bena kar vibhag me dena

impact_achieved_description: success story-gutuhatu, derang aur behtratoli nirmal gram yojna se jo souchalay banne wale tha wo adhura para huwa hai.

in dhanbad district, jhariya block (jharkhand) road from putki more to phusbangla was in very bad condition. the stretch of the road was 6 km for repairing that road people were agitating and protesting since many years but they did not received any help. factory owners of giridih, transporters and railway were earning profit but common man was suffering from that. since last 12 years the road was not repaired. on 17 march 2013 villagers gave an application about the bad condition of road and pollution to the commissioner but no one helped then they agitated and commissioner sent sdo to talk to them, he gave them written application but nothing happened. community correspondent bharti kumari, who also uses the same road made video about it and went to the dc (district collector) office and filed application about it. after a struggle of 1 year the road was finally repaired by the government.  - by sandhya marwada
impact_plan: application has to be written and submit to official with the involvement of community.

impact_achieved_description: a railway crossing bridge between singra and pandedih village , situated in dhanbad district baghmara block,was in a dreadful state.  there were big potholes on the bridge because of which people were facing difficulty in transportation. the bridge belonged to teh railway department thus it was thier responsibilty to fix it. commuters feared they might fall off from thier vehicles or the bridge might futher deteriote due to existing pothholes. this bridge is crucial for almost 35000 commuters beloning to 5 villages around it. cc bharti filmed a video on this issue and contacted the railway assistant divisional engineer. she expalined him teh issue and requested him to take suitable measures quickly. after this, the village head and community submitted an application to railway assistant divisional engineer. a few months later the pothholes in the bridge were repaired by the department . now, people can easily travel and there is no fear of accidents from potholes anymore.

jharkhand pauls video all is not well was strong statement about the state of affairs in bagichabedo village in jhakhand. it showcased the apathy of the politics and when paul showed this to the block development officer , it motivate him to act immediately. paul malto showed the clips from his camera to the bdo and it took a month to complete the well. issue and impact not clear. however, this is an old video so no rush in findign this out

english: school teacher xavier lugun told that there is no kitchen in our school, which is necessary. we are making a house by making a cover of grass, we are always making a gift to the teacher, somewhere snakes, bitches, chipkali, don't fall on the pakwan. teacher ne kai baar likhit application beo ko di. kaam nahi bana toh badgaon ke bdo ko avedan diya in written form. abhi tak kaam nahi ban raha hai. ye baat xavier lugun school ke teach rne bataya. xavier made a video on this issue and made a visa visit to the beo of badgaon block and showed the video to them. beo ispar baat karne se katra bhi raha tha. bas itna hi ki ki ispar vichar karnege. beo was calm till xavier reached. par video dekhne ke baad baar baar kah raha tha ki uske paas samay nahi hai, usko chaibasa jana hai. is visa par dobara meromghuthu school bhavan me baat karte samay chera. ja baad me kitchen bankar tayar ho gaya. ab kitchen shade me bcahon ke kiye bhojan banta hai. english: the school teacher xavier lugun informed that there was no kitchen which was necessary. they were somehow cooking under a straw shed. the teacher always feared that snakes, scorpions or lizards might fall into the food. the teacher submitted written application several times to the block executive officer. when nothing worked out he submitted another written application to block development officer of badgaon. nothing worked out still. xavier made a video about the problem and showed it to the block executive officer. the block executive officer seemed disinterested. he said he will think about it. after seeing the video he repeatedly said that he did not have time and that he had to go to chaibasa. the issue was discussed again and later a kitchen was made. now the food is cooked for the children under the kitchen shed.

the 10 kv tranformer of loyongkel lungitdi has not been functional since 4 months due to ehich teh 22 families in the village were living without any electricity. villagers has submitted application once to officer sand personally visited the executive engineer to solve the issue, however teh elctricty didnt resume in teh village anyhow. cc filmed a video on this issue and held a community meeting and screening with 25 peopel later. next day cc along with the community members travelled to meet the sdo at electricty office. when no respense arrived from officers cc again screened the issue video to executive engineer at department. in a few days engineer told cc and villagers that they have bought a 16 kv transformer at teh department ie the block. they will install the tranformer as soon as teh technicians on leave for dusshehra resume thier job.
end caste violence and ensure fair ration sin rural jharkhand

the government school building in merumgutu village in singbhum district was in a dilapitated state. for the past three years the building was slowly taken over by wines and trees. the doors haven't been opened to the children for as much time. those who could afford, sent their children to the missionary schools, but children of parents who cannot afford this continued to play around in the fields with nowhere to go. cc basanti hunni screened an old impact video in the village with a view to inspire them to action. this worked. after the screening the cc and the villagers spoke with the teacher and submitted an application to the block development office. after 3 months the school was operational. all the trees & wilderness was cleaned up. the water handpump was fixed. the school building was painted and the crumbling roof repaired. mid day meals was restarted and a teacher is now regularly teaching the kids.

ahalya devi is nurse at radhanagar, baghmara block, dhanbad district, she is at stage of retirement but she always has lot of work and no facilities at her work place (primary sub health center, radhanagar. is mudde par video banane ke halim baada ne dr. s. m jafrullah, the immediate medical practitioner of chc baghmara, was shown the video. me puraskrit karne ki baat kahi thi. parantu kuch dino ke baad hi uska transfer ho gaya. you can do it. before it becomes permanent, it has to be transferred. because of this, the medical officer of chc baghmara, dr. manish kumar, has taken over the job. now he is working again on the post of moic. he is very busy. don't meet a pplication lekar gayi par bina mile hi lautna para. ahkirkar met halima on 11 july 2016 and submitted her application. unhone saw the application and told me softly that bpm se receiving le lijye. bpm ne kisi chij ka wala dete huwe receiving nahi diya. one day halima again did the work of giving milkar receiving. unhone kaha ki ish par baat karenge. on june 16, 2016, halima went to hsc radhanagar and anm ahaliya told that out of 23 centers, now they have got only 12 centres. english: ahalya devi is a nurse at radhanagar, baghmara block, dhanbad district, she is at stage of retirement but she has always lot of work and no facilities at her work place (primary sub health center, radhanagar. halima showed the video to the health officer dr. s. m jafrullah. he was happy to see the video and assured that he would immediately resolve the issue in 1 week. he even talked about rewarding ahilya. but the officer was transferred after a few days. 2 officers came after that but they were also transferred. next came chc baghmara's medical officer dr. manish kumar who took the role of the moic. the cc was unable to meet him but submitted the application. he read the it and asked to get a receiving from the bpm. the bpm did not give the receiving. she went to him another day and this time he said he would talk about it. the cc went to hsc radhanagar on 16 june 2016, to inform ahilya that now instead of 23 centers she only had to do vaccinations at 12 centres.
impact_plan: community screening and writing the application.
target_official: prabhari cikitasa padadhikari - dr. visheshwar kumar

impact_plan: community screening. screening to civil sergeon and written application will be given to him.

impact_achieved_description: issue telmocho panchayat's telmocho up health center building in baghmara block of dhanbad district is in dilapidated condition and toilet is also missing. impact process - bharti kumari held a meeting with the community and made an application with the help of the community. sahiya and mukhiya ne isme madad ki. the application was created in the name of civil surgeon anil kumar sinha and former external medical practitioner. after a few days, applications were submitted to the civil surgeon and the post-doctoral surgeon. prabhari chikitsa padadhikari sm jafarula said that the fund for repairing will be released from the block, but the vehicle that has a banana toilet can be made from the mukhiya's fund. the chief minister also said that funds will be raised to build toilets. abhi telmoch upswasth kendra ko repair kiya ja chuka hai. english: the sub health center of telmocho village, telmocho panchayat, baghmara block, dhanbad district building was in bad condition and the toilet in the center was also not functioning. the local residents regularly visiting teh centeer feared to access treatment from the center. also teh staff and visitors had no other option than to go in open to defcate. cc held a community meeting and all of them decided to submit an application. the sahiya and village head were also present during teh community meeting. applications were submitted by cc with community to civil surgeon and hospital incharge regarding this issue. hospital incharge etold them that they will repair teh hospital building when the funds will arrive from district level, however its the vilage heads duty to repair the toilet since the toilet doesnt belong to health department. village head also promised that it will be her responsibility to build the toilet. a few months later the hospital building was repaired.
impact_plan: write the application with the community while you finish shooting.

impact_achieved_description: icds appoints aanganwadis for better healthy outcomes of the pregnant and lactating mothers and the children. however, aanganwadi workers of hisatu village were irregular and rude to the women who approached them for food or other assistance. the reason being they were not paid for the annual year 2013-14. another problem is the maternal vehicle that was an auto rickshaw, which does not reach on time. a 30-year old mother having delivered a baby, expressed her grief to have paid for the emergency auto herself and not been reimbursed in any way for the same. nirmala ekka lives in ranchi, and made a video on the problem, and held a meeting where the auxilliary nurse midwife and the up-mukhya were also present. they elected a sahiya from within the community who now works for the assistance of the pregnant women. 4 women accompanied nirmala to meet the child development project officer to address the problem and told him a video had been made as evidence to the problem, so the cdpo asked to wait. the cc also raised this problem during a health workshop organized by an ngo in november 2015 but no assistance was given. after efforts worth a whole year, 2-3 vans were kept as ambulances for transferring women in labor to the hospital in april 2016, aiding around 500 women.

the nirmal bharat yojna (now renamed as swach bharat abhiyan) provides for construction of a toilet in every household. however, in nicitpur village of khunti district many households were not able to finish construction of tolets. this was mainly because payment were not being released from the block office. amit topono, our cc in khunti district made a video about this and followed up the matter for the next 6 months. he met with the panchayat sevak (village council assistant), rojgar sevak (empolyment assistant under the mnrega program) and the block development officer. he also presented the case and the video in the public hearing conducted as part of the social audits under the mnrega program. amit also met the district comissioner, the highest official in the district for fast tracking this case and also filed an application under the right to information act. the matter was finally resolved in september 2014.

prakhand jaldega of district simdega panchayat patimba of kharwagarha village of nira kumari on 12-2-2014 for 13 years; this ghatna ka jab pata chala to samuday ma meeting ve huwa or gram sabha ve huwa gram sabha ma es samasaya ka samadhan nahi huwa to mukhiya ke doora es samasaya ke prasasan ko nirnay ka nirnay gaya gaya gaya or es ghatna ka jab unkay ghar walay police station ma fir darj karwana gay to 1 mha tak taltay rahay or fir darj nahi kiya uskay bad hrln ke adv. fir has been filed against manoj nag in simdega civil court for 1 month or for 20 months against police administration. avi larka or larki ke sadi honay ke bat kahi ja rahi hai but larki ke pariwar walo ko sadi ke ki jaankari hai or es sadi ke liya ki liya jur ve nahi hai. avi larki ke goad ma ak chota bacha ve hai. ---------------------sameer++english: a minor girl aged 12 years studying in class 7 had been missing from block jaldega, panchayat patiamba , village kharwagarha since march 2013. the parents of the girl approached the police station but their complaint wasn't being lodged by the officials. the three men who had kidnapped her and kept her at surat, gujarat belonged to the same village. cc filmed the issue and called a village meeting regarding this issue. in this meeting meeting it was decided by the community that village head be pushed ahead to appeal the administration to lodge a complaint and find the girl. even after all this the police kept avoiding the parents to lodge complaint for a month. the complaint was finally lodged through a hrln advocate in simdega civil court. 2 years later all the three men who abducted the girl have been sent to jail.
impact_plan: fir should be filed by the minor girl's family on 3 people, or the minor girl should be punished soon or the one who makes us run away in the wrong way, should be punished.

impact_achieved_description: badgaon block of pachmi singhbhum district has 11 handpumps in songra gaon of hesadih panchayat and only 2 handpumps are in good condition and 9 handpumps have been damaged for 4 years. this doctor held a meeting in the gram sabha and the total number of 60 people was included. after the meeting, the people of the village wrote an application in the name of mla chakradhapur shashi bhusan samad and started submitting applications to him. unhone awashan diya ki ish samasya ka samadhan wo karenge. uske aweda dene ke andar handpump ka repair kiya kiya gaya vibhag ki taraf se.------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ years in gonra village of hesadih panchayat, badgaon block, west singhbhum district. people were facing immense problems as they had to stand in queves for water and frequent quarrels between villagers were common. cc filmed the issue of nonfunctional handpumps. a meeting was held in village council regarding this issue of unfucntional handpumps which was attended by 60 villagers. villagers decided to submit an application to mla. application was submitted and mla assured that the handpumps would be repaired soon. a month later the handpumps were repaired and all the villagers are using the handpumps now.
impact_plan: the bdo or the mla was given the same day's wages.

impact_achieved_description: maria goreti ne 2016 main video banaya. 9 logon ko old age pension nahi mil raha tha. april 2016 main video banane ke turant baad woh co aur clerk se jakar mili. but he was told that this year's quota has been paid, now next year he will be paid. iss tarh se co talte gaye. abhi 2021 main naye bdo aaye hai aur unhone iska karya sambhala hai. maria sent him the video, got it and applied again. toh iss saal sabhi ka pension ho gaya hai. by telling the story of cc, other people also got help through a social worker.

impact_achieved_description: under the pradhan mantri pension yojana, there is a provision for every poor and helpless widow to get pension after the death of her husband, but surji devi in khamra village kaswagarh, bokaro district, gomiya block panchayat of jharkhand, filled and submitted the form continuously for seven years after the death of her husband, but they did not get pension and there are 3 widows like them who were facing a lot of problems due to not getting pension, i made a video on this problem on 5th december 2015. after making the video, screened it in the village and shared it in 3 groups of whatsapp, talked to the ward member about this problem, went to the office and met the chief 3-4 times, did video whatsapp 4 times and once a month through the medium of the phone kept on giving information about this problem to the block development officers by going to the block and also showed the video 3 times through whatsapp and 3-4 times through the medium of phone. in this way everyone started getting pension from 2021.

screening_shared_to: community members, panchayat official, bdo, news outlets or journalists

impact_achieved_description: sumita devi's passbook was in the hands of the chief. and sumitra devi was asking for money, because of us she was asking to return the passbook. after shooting halima's video, mukhiya got such a feeling that we sent one person to sumitra's paas and promised to return the paasbook. par diya nahi. halima, your doctor went to the bank and met the manager and a new passbook was issued and sumitra did not withdraw money from her account. harrassment of lonely women by officials. english: sumitra devi's bank passbook was with the mukhiya. he was demanding money from her in exchange for it. when halima made the video, the headman found out about it. he then sent over a man to sumitra and promised to return her passbook. but he never gave it back. halima took sumitra to the bank. she explained her situation to the manager and collected a new passbook. sumitra could then withdraw her money from her bank account.
impact_plan: halima  will bdo regarding the matter.

impact_achieved_description: in chhatrutad panchayat of dhanbad district, baghmara block (jharkhand), there were 4 people who were not getting their handicapped pension due to slow working process of government hence, they were facing many problems. in spite of having a handicapped certificate, pension was not provided to them. they went to meet head of the village, appealed in panchayat and in block office but nothing happened. community correspondent halima ejaj who belongs to the same panchayat got to know about the issue. she documented the issue and screened it in the panchayat and to the bdo (block development officer). as a result a process of pension distribution was start within two days of screening and the four people started receiving their handicapped pension (rs. 400). - by sandhya marwada

handpumps in chatrytand apar ward of chatrutand panchayat , baghmara block, dhanbad district were not working from last 1 year. a total of 150 villagers were dependent on these handpumps mainly for drinking water. especially women and girls walked long distance to bring drinking water from the neighboring village. for bathing, washing utensils all teh villagers depended on a small village pond, where the water was contaminated. villars often fell ill using this pond water. children had to skip school, men and women were not able to attend work. villagers had approached government repair person to fix the problem but he told that repair work was complicated. on the other side private repair person demanded a huge price to repair the handpumps which poor villagers could not afford to pay. cc filmed a video on this problem and held a community meeting to devise a solution. in the meeting all of them decided to write down an application in the name of bdo. 2 days later the villagers and cc visited the bdo office and submitted the application. bdo asked cc to call the junior engineer on the mobile number he gave. cc called up junior engineer thus explaining him the peoblem of handpumps. engineer assured villagers that he would resolve the issue soon. 2 weeks later the handpumps were repaired by the engineer. villagers now have access to safe and clean water. ********************************************************** ********************************************************** ******* ****************************** issue:- chatrutand apar of chatrutand panchayat of baghmara block of dhanbad district tola me 4 handpumps hain aur sab 1 saal se bad pare huwe hain. people go 1 km away to get pine water. the pond is used for bathing and washing, the dirty water of the village also comes out in it. cattle are also bathed in the same demand. impact process :- halima ne video banane ke baad samuday ke saath meeting rakhi aue samuday me video screening ki . after holding the meeting, an application was written on behalf of the community. the application was written in the name of the bdo of baghmara. after 2 days, the community came to the bdo with the words of laxmi devi and gave them an application and requested them to take action and also showed the video to the bdo. bdo - girjanand kisku ne halima ko junior engineer abhay singh ko contact number diya aur unse baat karne karne ko kahe. halima introduced herself and met a junior engineer. unhone jald hi aakar ke team ke saath handpump repair karne ki baat kahi. handpumps were repaired after 2 weeks. aur iske karan logon jo pani ko lekar ke jo samasya jhelni parti thi wo kam ho nahi ho rahi.
impact_plan: write the application with the community to the bdo

make video and screen to bdo
