impact_achieved_description: impact - rasan card issued to the ch of the video husan ansari and everyone else. in total 181 families from 2 panchayats got rasan card issued as targeted in the video. additionaly due to frequent visits by the cc to the block office, building pressure and collaborating with others from people from different panchayats who were not issued the rasan cards; at the end in total 10,000 rasan card got issued in the block in dec 2016.  process - after making the video the cc met the following government officials and gave them applications several times. both to the jila shikayat nivaran padadhikari & jila khadya aaaporti adhikari were separately given applications 3 times. at block office she and the community members met the - prakand aaaporti adhikari & bdo 2 times.   after making the video she did 2 community meeting - in which people from 4 villages. at this meeting they named their struggle to get rasan card  bhojan ka adhikar sangarsh morcha and decided that they will do one day sit in dharna/protest at the block office. the dharna at block office with about 250 took place on 4th nov 2016. at the end of the darna the cc and the community members gave their demands to bdo - demands were immediate issuing of rasan card and access to pds rasan. after this, every week she went to block office with 4-5 people to take updates on the matter. during the follow up visits she other govt officials as mentioned above.   after mary's efforts not just 181 families got rasan cards in her panchayat but in her whole block 10,000 rasan cards have been distributed. as, during her constant visits to the block office she met people from different panchayat struggling for the same and took them along creating a movement; pressurizing the block officials.   english: poor villagers from kherbari vilalge has thier names listed in the ration beneficiary list however they still werent receiving the ration. from december 2015, ph card (purwikta card) were alloted. villagers were facing difficulties to feed thier families due to lack of ration facility. after making the video she did 2 community meeting - in which people from 4 villages. at this meeting they named their struggle to get rasan card  bhojan ka adhikar sangarsh morcha and decided that they will do one day sit in dharna/protest at the block office. the dharna at block office with about 250 took place on 4th nov 2016. at the end of the darna the cc and the community members gave their demands to bdo - demands were immediate issuing of rasan card and access to pds rasan. after this, every week she went to block office with 4-5 people to take updates on the matter. during the follow up visits she other govt officials as mentioned above. after mary's efforts not just 181 families got rasan cards in her panchayat but in her whole block 10,000 rasan cards have been distributed. as, during her constant visits to the block office she met people from different panchayat struggling for the same and took them along creating a movement; pressurizing the block officials.
impact_plan: video bena kar screening karna aur awaden bena kar bivag me dena.
in bibhag, screening should be done and awaden should be given.
target_official: circle officer-basia block- vijay nath misra

impact_plan: award is given to the department.

impact_achieved_description: 40 km from ramdih dantolike madan baraik of arya panchayat of basia block of gumla district to get ration from pds. it's been a long time since 5 months. because there is no name in the pds of your village. there are 5 children in their family who get 5 kg of food per week. inke saath 6 vekti is samasya se prabhavit hain. ye log block me co aur bdo ke paas bhi gaye list me naam karwane par abhi apne gaon ka janvitran me inka naam nahi tha. es story me impact ho gaya hai, video banana suru nahi ke hai. badlao subdivision officer ko awaden samuday ke saath deya gaya tha jeske karan avi apnay najdeek ke pds deukan me hee rasan mil raha hai total 25 logo ko. english: 25 peopel from ramdih danto, arya panchayat, basia block, gumla district had to travel 40 km walking or arranging vehicle through own funds to buy ration in pds shop for 5 months. thier names were somehow omitted from the beneficiary list of pds and this is why the problem occurred. when they visited the bdo office they found out that thier names were missing in janvitran pranali. cc filmed the video and held a community meeting. in the meeting they wrote down an application in the name of sub divisional officer and discussed the issue. as decided in meeting cc with community submitted the application to sdo and requested for prompt action. soon the names of these families were included in the janvitran list. in present date all 25 families are receiving ration at pds shop in their village itself.
10 widows of jamdih bartand village of rampur panchyat had applied for widow pension since 2009 but no action had been taken. cc shanti baraik's video has solved the matter for 5 out of the 10 women.

issue - hiralal of lara village of churchu prakhand of hazaribagh district is not getting the biklang pension. impact process - august 2015 ko issue video bana manju ne hirlal ke viklang pension ke upar video shoot kiya tha. hiralal did not even apply. manju kisku got hiralal's disability certificate from anganbari sevika in 2016. the anganbari worker was given the responsibility of making a disability certificate and pension from the block side. manju got hiralal's disability certificate from the anganbari worker. the servant said that hirlal's name should also be ashamed. on 30-11-2016 manju kisku was received from bdo sushil xaxa of churchu block of hazaribagh district in the name of hirlal and he gave her application. the bdo said that at present the anganbari worker is responsible for making the vikalng certificate. first of all, you should contact the anganbari sevika. jaise he unse disability certificate milega aur block me jama ho jayega toh pension milna shuru ho jayega. on 30-11-2016, manju kisku again went to meet the anganbari worker. milkar came to know that hirlal's disability certificate has been issued. in april 2017, hiralal soren got a vikalng certificate and now he is getting his pension. english: hiralal of lara village, churchu block, hazaribag district wasnt receiving the monthly disability pension. disabled are entitled to receive rs.400 under indira gandhi nishakt scheme and rs.200 under swami vivekanand nishakt scheme once they have thier disabled certificate. cc filmed a video on this issue in august 2015. cc met the anganwadi helper of the village to avail help for processing disability certificate. anganwadi helper was the one responsible to identify and submit application for disability pension, and ths responsiblity was sanctioned by bdo office. cc met the helper and requested her to issue the certificate and the helper agreed. when the person received no certificate in following days cc approached the bdo with application. bdo told that it was teh helper authorized to issue the certificate and asked cc to contact her again. cc again met the anganwadi helper at village and upon meeting cc came to know that certificate has been issued. in april 2017 hiralal received his certificate and now he is availing his monthly disability pension.
impact_plan: write the application submit to bdo.

impact_achieved_description: issue -simon murmu of jamuwa village of kusumbha panchayat of bishungarh block of hazaribagh district is handicapped in both his legs. unko 13 saal pehle pehle ke liye baishakhi mili thi par ab tut chuki hai. simon is working hard to tie your goat. impact process- manju kisku first wrote an application in the name of cdpo in collaboration with the victim simon kisku and submitted it to the cdpo office of bishungah block. tab karamchari ne apne goddam me vaishaki ko check kiya par nahi tha, uske baad unko baad me simon ke saath aane ke liye bola gaya. phir nischit din ko phir se manju kisku simon kisku ko lekar cdpo office gayi phir simon kisku ko naya baishakhi diya gaya. ab simon is using new baishakhi. english: simon murmi is a handicapped person from jamuva village, kusumbha panchayat, bishungarh block, hazaribagh district. he had received a baisakhi 13 years ago by the government which has reached in bad state recently. simon was somehow managing with it by tying it with cloth. cc filmed a video on this issue and held a meeting with teh family for solution. they decided to visit the cdpo office with application. as decided cc and simon vsiited teh cdpo office and submitted application. at that moment the office store didn't have any new clothes to provide to simon. thus they ask simon to come on another decided day to collect the clothes. on the decided day, cc and simon again visited teh offiec and teh cuts were provided to him.
impact_plan: wirte the application in the name of cdpo and submit it in her office.
write the application and fill up the pension form and submit it to block office to co

impact_achieved_description: jila khunti prakhand murhu panchayat kayora gao patrade ke rahnay wali sumi huni purti jinke umar 62 wars hai inka olad age pension wars 2009 sa 2013 tak mila eskay bad nahi mil raha hai jiskay karan apna jiwika chalanay ma kafi dikat ho raha hai.  cc has raised this issue and character met with co, murhu and they explained the issue with the official and then co has suggested to fill a form to resume the pension of the character and later, she received her pension.   english: the government of india has entitled monthly pension to all the persons aged above 60 years. the pension amount differs across various states of india. sumi huni purti, a woman aged 62 years residing in patrade village, kayora panchayat, murhu block, khunti district was receiving the monthly pension rs.600 from the year 2009 uptil 2013. after 2013 somehow her pension was not being disbursed. thsi had a major impact on her living. cc filmed a video on this issue and later made a plan with the women to solve this issue. they both met the co and made him aware of the issue. the co officer instructed cc and women to fill the pension form again with the required documents and submit it to him. soon after the forms were filled , a few days later woman started receiving her monthly pension.

impact_plan: screening in the middle of the day and making arrangements and going in separation and video screening.
community meeting will be done and application will be prepared in the name of bdo.
video bena kar screening karna aur bivag ke adhikari ko awaden dena.
write the application and submit to prakhand khadya padadhikari.

impact_achieved_description: issue:- naima khatun or subajan bibi, who are living in mohada panchayat of dhanbad district bhagmara prakhand, have been stopped from getting pension on 20-10-2015 or they can go away in prakhand or 15 lavouko's pension has been stopped. because of which many people are suffering. impact process:- bharti ne video banane ke baad samuday ke saath ek meeting ki. the plan for the future of the body has been taken up and an application has been written in the name of circle officer rajendra singh of baghmara block. recruitment took the help of the community, went to baghmara block with the help of 2 people and went to the circle officer and submitted the application. the circle officer assured that it will be taken care of. naima khatun and bank beneficiaries have started getting pension after 2 months. english: 16 persons from mohada village of mohada pancahyat, baghmara block stopped receiving their monthly pension from august 2015. these persons belonged to weaker sections of the society thus it became difficult for them to survive without the pension amount. cc bharti filmed a video on this issue and held a community meeting. in the meeting they wrote down an application in the name of circle officer. cc along with 2 community members visited the circle officer at block office and submitted the application. the officer assured that he would take action soon. two months later all the 16 persons started receiving the pension.
impact_plan: by making a video, people should pass the screening or they should be given adhikari to the divorce.

impact_achieved_description: in naoniyabera village, ramgarh, jharkhand five families under the bpl index going through severe financial hardship was not receiving the allotted amount of rice from the ration shop. ration shops are the last line of defence in the public distribution system. in this case bpl families who are allotted 35kgs of rice every month by the government was only receiving 12kgs for 15 rupees. our community correspondent basanti soren when informed about the situation, decided to respond with a film on the issue. the family consists of daily wagers who tows coal for a living and depends on their daily wages for two essential meals. the film shows the hardship they have to bear and if they miss work for a day, they miss the meal too. the village sarpanch was informed about this crisis and he assured to look into the issue. after three months the families were allotted bpl ration card and they are now receiving the allotted amount of ration.

impact_plan: the application has to be written and submitted to the co.
write the application and submit to circle officer of borio block.
form and application have to be filled.

impact_achieved_description: 26 families from daminbitha village, daminbitha panchayat, mandro block, sahebganj district didnt have any ration cards. villagers several times approached the village head with applications for ration card. the village head always assured them of help but never did the work seriously. whenever the villagers approached the block office to inquire about their applications through the village head, the officials denied of receiving any such applications. they weren't receiving the ration since 2 years. cc filmed a video on this issue and held a community meeting with villagers. an application was written in the name of village head and sdo (divisional officer). cc along with villagers approached the village head and made him to sign the application in front of all the villagers. the village head did so, and cc submitted the same application to sdo in the block office. upon discussing the issue with the sdo, he assured of help. 2 months later the ration cards were distributed among the 26 families. ********************************************************** ****************** issue 26 families in bhiyan toli of daminbitha panchayat of daminbitha panchayat of mandro block of sahebganj district have not received the food card of 26 families. whose doctor has been given to the gram pradhan, mukhiya for a long time and the application has been given. block ja kar logon ne pata kiya toh block ke sataff ne kaha ki unka application nahi aaya hai. for 2 years we are not getting our ration. character name- leelavati devi. impact process - after making the video, sanju malto kept meeting us every day and submitted an application in the name of chief and sdo. then sanju went to the mouth and got his signature done. then we went to the sdo office after taking the application and got rid of their problems and also submitted the application. sdo ne jald samadhan karne ki baat kahi hai. after 2 months, his ration card was updated.

impact_plan: write the application with messi paharin and submit to bdo and co of mandro block.

impact_achieved_description: issue-ram bodra of hatnadah village of hudu panchayat of saraikela block of saraikela district who is 65 years old and is not getting pension due to being in bpl category. apart from this, 7 elderly people are also getting pension. ye log 2 baar form bhar chuke hain. impact - ram bodra ne 3 baar awedan de chuke the phir bhi usko pension nahi mil raha tha. after sujeeta's video was made, sujeeta wrote an application in the name of ram bodra and submitted it to the block, 7 months after its submission, ram bodra started getting pension. english: ram bodra along with 7 other old aged from hatnadah vilalge, hudu panchayt, saraikela block, were not receiving the old age pension they were entitled to. they had applied 2 times themselves to avail pension however that was of no use. cc filmed a video on thsi issue and held a community meeting. an application was written addressing the bdo and signed by all. next cc with community vsiited teh bdo offiec and submitted teh application and screened video to officer. later after 7 months the all 8 people started receiving the pension in their accounts.

impact_plan: give the benefits of the community to the bdo.
making a video for the beach screening of every day and giving bivag may awaden.
video bana kar samuday ke beach screening karna or awaden bana kar bivag ma dena.
application has been given to co of khuntpani

impact_achieved_description: families in amrabedo village of sahebganj district (jharkhand) was not getting proper ration (35 kg rice) since past 7 months in spite of having antyoday card and due to that they were facing many problems. they asked several times in panchayat about the issue but no clarification was given to them. community correspondent jyoti malto who lives in the same village and belongs to the same community made a video about it. she wrote an application to the block development officer about the issue. after two months of writing application, proper ration (35 kg rice) was distributed amongst the antyodaya card holder families.
impact_plan: write the application with devi pahrin and submit to bdo office.
community screening and writing the application.

impact_achieved_description: the bank passbook of 50 elderly people in ambatari village was kept by the postman and he refused to to hand over the passbooks to the pensioners. postman did not disburse thier pension regularly. he would often give rs 100 after 4 months and took thier signatures for full amounts. pension amount is rs 700 people above 70 years and rs.400 for those above 60 years. in this case they should have received rs.2800 and rs.1600 respectively for the 4 months. postman was embezzeling thier pension money. cc reshmi devi who belongs to same village made a video and held a community meeting . the cc and the community confronted the postman and warned him of the consequences of submittinng application and video to his superior officers. he handed over the passbooks. all pensioners now get the correct amounts.

forms were filled under indira gandhi national pension scheme of all aged. all forms were submitted to chatrutah panchayat chief. months passed but chief took no action then cc decided to visit bdo. cc contacted baghmara bdo & screened him video. bdo was very happy to know the case & assured cc of complete cooperation. acting upon his words he soon sent panchayat sevak of the same panchayat for inspection & all the old applications were passed. later cc took all the old to bank & helped them retierve thier first pension. rajasva gram, murlidih.
impact_plan: write application with the community and visit to bdo to block.

impact_achieved_description: 10 handicapped people from padogoda were not receiving their disability pension for the last 7 months.to solve the issue they visited the block office, the post office and the bank several times but nothing good came of it. cc bharti kumari made a video on this and went to the district welfare departmetn office with one of the hadicapped persons. the officer promised action within a week. when the cc followed up after a week she was told to go the post office. after of a month of back and forth she managed to get their pensions released.

since the last 18 months birsa manjhi of village ulhara had not received his monthly old age pension of rs.400. he had paid many visits to the bank and the block development office to inquire but was unsuccessful. birsa and his wife are old and cannot go to work and this paltry pension is their only source of income. cc basanti soren made a video on this issue and followed up with the authorities for 6 months after whcih birsa started receiving the pension. birsa is happy now that his pension is coming in every month.

impact_plan: give it to the bdo by making adwaden from the samudey.
don't make awaden and give it to the department.
he is going to give information about the incident to the sp.

impact_achieved_description: mubid ansari's family and 3 other households from birbera village of tundu panchayat were receiving regular ration from the year 1997 to 2002. from 2002 onwards they didn't recive any ration. cc bharti filmed a video on this issue. cc and the community alter held a community meeting and decided that they will submit an application to bdo (block development officer). in next days, cc with mubid visited teh bdo office and met him. they screened him the problem video and discussed the issue with him. bdo assured that he will start receiving the ration soon. a few days later mubid started receiving the ration.

pooja : the block development officer of bhagmara recruited 187 people in jharkhand as literacy workers from village lohapatta 18th october, 2013 to 10th november, 2013 on a monthly income of rs 4500/ month. he promised their dues would be paid by march, which did not happen. bharti kumari lives in dhanbad district, and she made a video when she got to know about the problem. she arranged a screening for the community, and managed to mobilize 3 members to accompany her to meet the block development officer, who explained that there were more people being listed as the recipients of the money. he promised that in a matter of two to three months, their dues would be paid. the process took two months to bring about an impact, and all the members were compensated accordingly.
impact_plan: by making awaden from samuday ke logo, bivag may dena or video ka screening karna.
target_official: prakhand bhabmara bdo girganand kisku mo-9471191628

impact_plan: give it to dc by raising wages from the community.
the application has to be written with the community and submitted to bdo.

impact_achieved_description: she did the community screening in community. made the plan to visit dc. they started working on impact in the month of march. village pradhan and some members went to meet dc muthu kumar and gave the  application. dc phoned bdo of mandro in front of them and asked him about the incomplete indra awas. he told him to inquire about. next day, block team visited the site. then the work started after two weeks. the construction have been done.. she did the community screening in community. made the plan to visit dc. they started working on impact in the month of march. village pradhan and some members went to meet dc muthu kumar and gave the  application. dc phoned bdo of mandro in front of them and asked him about the incomplete indra awas. he told him to inquire about. next day, block team visited the site. then the work started after two weeks. the construction have been done.. she did the community screening in community. made the plan to visit dc. they started working on impact in the month of march. village pradhan and some members went to meet dc muthu kumar and gave the  application. dc phoned bdo of mandro in front of them and asked him about the incomplete indra awas. he told him to inquire about. next day, block team visited the site. then the work started after two weeks. the construction have been done.

20 tribal families of tataria village, kharwa panchayat, mandro block, sahebganj district didn't receive the new ration card for which they had submitted an application in february 2015. these families survived themselves by selling firewood in the neighboring market and buying ration out of it. cc filmed a video on this issue. these families were struggling for ration card for almost 2 years. cc screened the video in the community among 30 people. cc along with community called up a meeting decided to meet the officer at the block. they all later submitted an application to the officer and screened him the video. after 5 months all the 20 families received their ration cards. they all now have access to government ration at subsidized rates. ********************************************************** ********************************************************** ********************** district sahabganj prakhand mandro panchayat kharwa gram tataria ke samina paharin ke awala 19 parivaar ko logo ko new ration card aaj tak nahi mila hai jiske suchna villages ne february 2015 ko awaden de kar rasan card ke mang kiye. is mudde's doctor sanju made a video. ration card ko lekar gaon walon ne bahoot paryas kiye the. adim janjati ko ration card se kaphi madad mil jati thi, jab unke paas naya rasahncard nahi tha tho unlogon ko lakri bazar me bechne ke liye jate the taki bazar se ration kharid sake. it bothers me for 2 years. sanju ne samuday me video dikhaya tha jisme 30 gramin upasthit the. along with the community, the rights of the authority also went away. adhikari ko bhi video dikhaya gaya. gaon walon ko baad 5 months ko new rasahn card mila.
impact_plan: video bena karna screening karna aur awaden bena karna bivag me dena.

impact_achieved_description: the husband of madgi paharin, a resident of durgatola panchayat of borio block of sahebganj district, was murdered in 2013. uske baad madgi paharin apne 5 bachon ko palne me asamrth thi. in the body, we have asked for grant from dc of sahebganj and we have to pay 31500 rs. paas huwa and on 19-07-16 madgi paharin whole money was withdrawn from gramin vanchal bank. people named basdev and sailesh pandey took away the body. the community didn't make any efforts for the solution of the problem, because it is not possible to be troubled by salesh pandey. shika ko issue mile ke baad sahebganj ke sp ke paas madgi paharin ke saath avelan di aur sp ne karwai karne ki baat kahi aur borio thana prabahi ko iski sukna di phir shikha aur madgi paharin mile from borio thana prabahari aur ghatna dene wala salesh pandey and basdev went to their homes. thana prabahri and police force were also with shika and madgi paharin. basdev apne ghar me nahi pay gaya evam salesh pandey bahoot sharab piya huwa tha. jiske baad thana prabhari ne 4 days kamay diya aur phir shikha aur madgi paharin ko lekar borio police station gayi. 4 days later, salesh pandey and basudev were called to the police station and then a case was registered in the police station and madgi pharin was given 31500 rs. to install nagad diya. badlao lane ne samjik karyakarta hiralal paharia, sahebganj sp murgan, borio police station prabhari lala bihari prasad ne saath diya. english: madgi paharin's husband of durgatola panchayat of borio block of sahebganj district was murdered in 2013. she faced a lot of difficulties in raising her 5 children. she demanded a grant from sahebganj district commissioner received rs. 31500 from special welfare officer. she got a clearance of all the money from gramin vananchal bank on 19-07-16. two men named basdev and sailesh pandey conned her. no one in her community came forward to help her. when shikha found out about the story she went with madgi paharin to the sp. the sp told that he would take action and inform in the borio police station. the police officer went to salesh pandey and basdev's residence. basdev was missing and salesh was found drunk. after 4 days, the police registered a case and gave madgi pharin her rs. 31500. social worker hiralal paharia, sahebganj sp murgan, borio police-in-charge lala bihari prasad helped to bring change.
impact_plan: meet sp of sahebganj and explain the matter to him then file fir.

impact_achieved_description: issue:- jila west singhbhum ke saranda 700 pahario ka ghana gangle hai jha hoo munda adiwashi adhiktar niwash kartay hai. 248 gharo ka saranda axan plan ke that wars 2012 me saranda wasio ko indrawash yojna se jora gaya th bank a/c ke dawara awash nirman ke liya 1st installment rs.24,000/-bhugatan keya gaya hai.es rupia se diwal khara karne ka tha. uska bad 2nd installment rs.24,500/- chapper adi benana ke liya milna tha jo ke avi 3year ho janay ke bad ve bhugatan nahi kiya gaya jiske karan indrawash adhura para huwa hai. impact process:-kamal has given short information in the mail. i wil write in detail after phone conversation with him  english: 248 families were enlisted in indira awas housing scheme in 2012 under the saranda action plan in jojogutu village . the first installment rs. 24000 was deposited into the accounts of beneficiaries. however the second installment of rs. 24.500 never arrived in their accounts. as a result the house of these families were left incomplete. most of teh houses needed funds for the roof, which the villagers had to cover eith leaves. this is prredomianntlya  tribal arae. cc filmeda  video on this issue and held a community meeting. an application was signed by alll villagers addressing the rural development officer. cc and community when vsiited the officer . teh video was screened to him. he told cc that thsi amtter was out of hsi reach and teh district collector needs to get involved. later cc posted the audio report on issue sharing platform cgnetswara which was found by teh district collector. after for days dc sent officails into teh village for inspection. they found incompleted houses and thsu assured vilalgers of defibete help. a few days later funs of 129 villagers ie teh second installment was released into thier accounts. the vilalgesr then compelted thier homes.
impact_plan: video bena kar screening karna aur bivag me awaden den.

impact_achieved_description: issue :- harish soy of pandrasli village of matkobera panchayat of khuntpani block of west singhbhum district, in 2016, 17 people did not have to pay wages. impact process :- kamal got this problem in the meeting of gramsabaha. uske baad kamal purty ne mate e baat ki aur uske baad online janch ki. and then called baithak again in the village. then kamla did an online test in front of the labourer. mic ke janch me usne majduron ka payment aur adhar card link ha ki nahi uske upar janch ki. then gave the application tire karke to bdo. no action was taken even after giving application. kamal again went to mate and cft and took full information. because of that kamal ne online aur whats app se yojana banao abbhiyan kolhan me shiyat kiya. after 3 weeks the work started. and the work of paying the laborers started. abhi pure khuntpani block me jahan is tarah ki problem hai vahan par karwai ho rahi hai. english: 17 people worked in pond construction under mnrega of harish soy in pandrasali village, matkobera panchayat, khuntpani block, west singhbhum district in 2016, however thier wages were not being paid. mnrega schemes mandate the payment of wages within 15 days of work. cc being active member of village council came to know about the issue during a meeting. cc filmed a video on this issue and held a community meeting to discuss the issue. cc did an online research regarding the problem infront of the people whether the payment accounts have been linked with adhar cards or not , this mostly being obvious reason for non payment. cc along with community submitted application to bdo. some days passed when no action was taken by officers, cc more information from mate and cft. with this help they lodged online complaint in whatsapp yojna banao abhiyan. 3 weeks later investigation began on the case and the wages of unpaid laborers were released. similar attacks in other parts of the state are under investigation due to this impact.
impact_plan: kamal has filed an online complaint.

impact_achieved_description: from the house of nunigopal das in damjori village of domjori panchayat of potka block of purvi singhbhum district, pcc raod adhura para tha. due to the incompleteness of the road, there was donkey and mud on the way, due to which people were going to face problems. in the rain, people turn away from the face of being dirty. it seems more and more in the body because it is too far away. about 7-8 villages with a population of about 6000 were affected by this problem. tulsi ke video banane 9 mahin baad road ka kaam shuru huwa. pcc road from nunigopal das's house to latakhal nala which was built around 3 kilometers near kalyan vibhag. with the banning of pcc road, 7-8 villages have been affected and around 6000 population are getting benefited. after making pcc road, people are getting the benefit that they can go to hospital, market, school, college and other places of work without any problem in the rainy season. jahan reached tata motor hospital by walking around 45-50 km. ki duri tay karni parti thi. ab pcc banne ke baad vahan pahunchne me logon ko sirf 15-50 km. what will be the distance and what will be done. english: the pcc road from nunigopal das's house to latakhal nala in east singhbhum district, potka block, damjori panchayat, damjori village is incomplete. as a result, there are a lot of potholes on the road and people are facing difficulty. during rainy seasons the people have to take other routes. 6000 people from 7-8 villages were affected by this problem. construction work started 9 months after tulsi made the video. pcc road from nunigopal das's house to latakhal nala was 3kms which was built by the welfare department. after the pcc road was constructed, 7-8 villages got connected and about 6000 people gained access to it. now they can easily reach hospitals, markets, schools, colleges and other places even during monsoons. earlier, to reach tata motor hospital people had to travel 40-50km but after pcc people only have to travel a distance of 15- 20km.

in karando village 2500 villagers faced severe problems for 20 years(doctors, teachers didnt come into village) as there are no bridges on the several water nallahs. villagers several times wrote application & spoke to sarpanch (village council head) & village head but they didnt respond regarding the road repair. cc made a video on this issue & discussed it with village head & community , alos scrrened it to village head. 6 months later the road work started & the road is free of hassles now. road making also benefited the local to get employment under mnrega .the sarpanch acknowledged the issue and undertook the construction of the road even before aparna could finish her video. this is a good example of the power of media and it's perceptive strength in highilighting small yet important gaps to the very local authorities who then act to solve the issue.

the road going from jaldega block to lachragarha is 11 km long (simdega dist., jharkhand). the road had been in a dilapidated state for the past 3-4 years.  there were huge potholes on the road and therefore the local tribals had to face difficulties while travelling on the road. the school rickshaw driver and many people like him were scared that they may fall down. it was taking nearly 1 hour to travel on this 11kms road. the block officer of that area mr. mukesh kumar bawri, was well aware of the condition but he was not taking any action regarding it. community correspondent warles surin who is the resident of the same block came to know about the issue and he documented it and showed it to the block development officer. people of that village organized a block level meeting and discussed about repairing of the road. soon the road was repaired with gravel and officials assured to make a new road in short time. - by sandhya marwada

dhobani primary school in eastern singhbhum district, potka block (jharkhand) had 89 students in the school but there was not a single permanent teacher available in the school. a teacher from jhuriya primary school used to come and teach the students. a meeting was conducted between parents and teacher to appoint a permanent teacher in school but no decision was take in the school. community correspondent tulsi hembrom who belongs to the same community, made a video about this issue and gave a written application to the block education officer about the lacking of teacher in the school. as a result of that, after 8 month of giving application a new teacher was appointed on march 2015 in the school.
impact_plan: meet smc and prepare application and visit beo to submit application.

impact_achieved_description: in the primary school in masnodih panchayat of domchanch block 34 students out of the 150 did not get the free school uniform that were distributed. cc dimpi devi made a video and screened it in the village and also showed it to the sarpanch. a lcoal ngo sangram helped her to access the local officials and the block education officer. all students got the unifroms they were entitled to.

isu video ke utkramit madhya vidyalaya me every year saraswati puja and 26 january in the name of school ke students money in the form of donation. sangram sanstha ke samasaya ko pahal gaya ke dawara ki sangram sanstha kya gaya hai. wars 2016 me kesi ve thra ka chanda nahi leya ja raha hai. ya samasaya sangram sanstha ke pahal ke dawara hai he sambhaw ho hai es badlao ki abhav bhavak hai and students are quite happy.

mariam ke dawara manrega ke tahat brikch ropan ka kam kar rahe majduro ko majduri nahi melane ke upar video banai. samuday ke beach screening ve keya gaya jesme samuday ke 30 log upasthit thay aur majduro se awaden bena kar laber office gey screening keya awaden deya fer kuch den ke bad dist. laber office ve gey fer laber office ke adhikari apnay tem ke sath fild ka visit ve keye aur 1 wars ke bad 70 laber ko bakaya majdori ka bhugtan keya gaya. bakaya majduri ka bhugatan hone se majdur kafi khus hai.  english: wages of 70 labourers worked under the mnrega scheme in planting trees in the village were not paid. cc filmed a video on this issue and made teh community aware of thier rights in mnrega. mnrega wages are entitled to be paid within 1 month of the work. cc filmeda video on this issue and held a community screening in the village. the screening was attended by 30 villagers. during teh screening cc and villagers wrote application in the name of block labor officer and district labour officer. in teh following days they submitted thsee applications to the officers and expalined the issue to them. a few days later a team from labour department visited the vilalge and investigated the issue. 1 year later all teh 70 labourers were paid thier due wages.  engish: labourers from sithiyo village wernt paid for their work since 10 months passed . they had worked under tree planting project in the village under mnrega scheme. village officials had submitted the master data of labourers for receving the payments in august 2012 but the payments never arrived. villagers were confused whether they should continue working in the scheme or not, hence some of them left. village officails also bought labourers from neighbouring village for work . cc filmed this issue and held a community meeting. they all wrote a application and submitted it to labour officer. labour officer inspected teh situation and senta  notice letter to higher officails of forest department. the forets officials then came to village to inspect the situation and prepared a letter for disbursing payments. a few days later all the payments were disbursed to villagers.

pooja : the construction of the building for the veterinary medical facility in mahuda village had been incomplete for one and a half years, and this had adversely affected almost 25 neighboring villages, dependent on the facility for their livestock care. veterinary medical officer, who had been working in the center for 3 years, explained that the private facility did not have proper infrastructure, the rainwater would constantly drop through the ceilings and it was difficult to maintain records. bharti kumari lives in dhanbad district, and she made a video when this came up in the monthly meeting. upon interviewing the thekedar, it was found out that his funds were returned with no prior information, so he could not have continued the construction. she, along with one community member went to meet the zila pashu chikitsak adhikari, who told that their funds till march 2016 were finished, so they had to cut on the funding of the vet center. the whole process took more than a year before the construction could begin again.

kasiadih village's anganbari bhavan adhura para huwa tha ish mude ko lekar chunu hansda ne video banaya tha. anganbari sevika usi adhuri bhavan me hi bachon ko parha rahi thi. plaster also does not belong to the earth. video banane ke baad iska screening samuday me kiya gaya. then chunnu went to meet the supervisor, because he did not want to meet, he met the bdo of churchu block, christo kumar besra, and showed him the video of the anganbari of kasiadih village. bdo ne uspar pahal karne ki baat kahi aur kuch dino ke baad wahan par kaam chalu ho gaya.--------------sameer++english: the anganwadi (courtyard shelter - they were started by the indian government in 1975 as part of the integrated child development services program to combat child hunger and malnutrition. a typical anganwadi center provides basic health care in indian villages.) building was incomplete since many days. cc filmed a video regarding this issue. despite the fact that the building was incomplete, all the activities were carried out in the same building. it was difficult for the anganwadi workers to manage the children in this incomplete building. the concrete on the floor of the building was also damaged. this video was filmed in the community to make all the villagers aware of the situation. cc then went out to meet the supervisor looking after construction but he wasn't present at his place. thus cc met block development officer and screened him the video. bdo assured cc that he will solve the problem soon. a few days later the construction of the building began. the building is complete now.
impact_plan: supervisor or bdo sa milna tha.

impact_achieved_description: bundu ki sahiya rekha devi ko sahyog rashi nahi mil raha tha. usko 2 saal se koi rashyog rahi naihi mil rahi thi. ish mude ko lekar video banaye. ekjut sanstha ko edited video diye. ekjut ne bdo ko ye video dikhaya. aur ekjut sansta ke saath milkar jan sanvad kiya gaya. us jan sanvad civil sergeon, bdo-bundu block, bank manager-sbi and tamar vidhayak raja peter upasthit the. there are 60 villages in the us and 200 villages in the world. video ko vahan screen kiya gaya. the authorities listened to reason and promised to tolerate. and soon i started working on god and there was no possibility of doing janvad. t receiving their payments regularly since 2 years. they also weren't receiving any facilities on time. cc filmed a video on this issue. cc shared this video with a local organization named �ekjut sanstha�. this ngo & cc screened the video to bdo. they also organized a public meeting. this meeting was also attended by civil surgeon, bdo, bank manager of sbi & local mla. a total of 20 health workers and 200 villagers attended the meeting. the cc's video was screened in the meeting. the officiasl after watching the video assured to solve the issue as soon as possible a few months later this problem was solved.

bindhani village, madgada panchayat of kanhachatti block, rajiv gandhi rural electrification scheme. poles have been erected and wires have been fixed but no electricity since 5 years 2010. villagers tried almost every possible action right from district administration to state administration. the major effect is on education which is sad becuase villagers feel on one side government is spending huge funds on education and the basic necessity electricty isnt being provided to villagers. people are poor and cant afford fuel lamps for which fuel is rs.60 per litre. when the fuel from the lamp runs out children arent able to complete thier study. people are farid of accidental bites from snakes and scorpions during night. two children from dalit community died of snake bite which coulndt have had happened if electricty was present. there was electricty in a neighbouring community just 200mts away but not in this village. cc filmed this issue and held a meeting with the community. next day all villagers approached the block officer to submit him an application for the electricity. cc with community also submitted application to newly elected district panchayat president who later helped a lot. it took 1 year of struggle to get electricity. 3000 people from a toatl of 5 villages benefited. villagers are now able to charge thier mobile phones, watch tv. farmers are able to save up money on diesel which they used to spend when there wasnt any electricity.

in ichaghutu rangatoli village, kulburu panchayat, kamdara block, gumla district 500 people had no access to electricity from 18 months but instead they were receiving the bills. many poles were erected in village but no electricty was running in village. people visited sdo officefew times, submitted application but even then officials said earlier bills wont be cancelled , they ll ahve to pay all.( officers thought electricity was being stolen by villagers) cc made video, submitted application signed by all villagers to sbo ( sahayak vidhyut karyapalak abhiyanta) & screened video. after this 1 & half moth later electricty connection was started in village & previous were also rejected.

vill-khatkura bazartoli,panchayt-itam,block-basia - in this village, people were left in the dark due to the problem of transformer. it was a lot of trouble to make food at night and to save money in the morning. villagers did not apply to junior engineer, but there was no work. shanti made a video on this issue in march 2015 and held meetings with the villagers and filed an application in the name of executive engineer and worked in the district. vehicle executive engineer se mile aur awedan diye. executive engineer ne kaha ki abhi transformer nahi hai yahan, jab ayega toh ham bheja jayega. shanti ne executive engineer aur junior engineer se phone par lekar ko transformer kafi baar ki. junior engineer ne old transformer ke paas lane aur new transformer ke paas le jane ke liye kaha. called again on 14th july 2015. the junior engineer charged rs.1200 for loading the transformer and rs.1500 for the heavy load. isko lekar khub bahasbaji huwi. transformer doctors came and on july 14, the chief minister told them to complain by calling 181. 181 number rpar call karke junior engineer dowara paisa lene aur transformer nahi carhaye jane ki baat rakhe. the toh junior negineer aju kachap ne phone karke kaha ki aaplog complaint wapas lijye. if you have earned money from your blog, you will return it. shanti said to the junior engineer that first of all the transformers should be carried so that they would return the complaint to the village. on september 10, 2015, vidhansabha adhyach dinesh oraon was written and taught. transformer of 25 kb was installed on 17 january 2016. aur ab bati jal raha hai. ------------------------sameer++english: the villagers of khatkura bazartoli , itam panchayat, basia block were forced to live in dark since last one year as a result of defunctional transformer. especially women and children faced difficulties since they could not cook food and study in the dark. villagers had submitted application to junior engineer but no action was being taken by him. cc filmed this issue and held meeting in the village in the meeting they decided to submit an application to executive engineer at district level and explain the matter to him. this engineer assured villagers that the transformer would be installed soon. the application was submitted and the cc continuously followed up on this issue with junior engineer as well as executive engineer later days. few days later, junior engineer asked villagers to return the defunctional transformer and take away a new one. villagers went to district but to their surprise they didn't receive anything. again few days later they were called at district. there the junior engineer asked to pay 2700 towards loading the transformer and vehicle rent. villagers had to pay him the money as they had no option. but later after brining the transformer into the village they made a complaint on toll free 181 number of chief minister regarding the junior engineer asking for money. as a result officials from district came to village to inspect the matter and the junior engineer got scared. he asked villagers to cancel the complaint. cc told him to first install the transformer, return the money & then they all will cancel the complaint. villagers submitted an application to chairperson of legislative assembly to install the transformer. few days later the transformer was installed and the villagers are happy now.

in gumla district, tati village electricty transformer hasnt been working from 8 months caused 700 villagers have no access to electricity. villagesr tried to solve the issue by meeting politicians, sdo but no use. (officers said their named wasnt listed , u dont even have your bills).villagers even met dbc ( peopel who take tenders from elec dept for transformers). after video was made & screened to je, he inspected village & issued a order to replace transformer. to avoid delay villagers themselves took tarnsformer to gumla( city) & got it repaired & fixed . electricity works now.

after making video shanti went to the franchisee office but they did not receive connection form and demanded 1400 rs for new connection. after that when speaker of jharkhand assembly dinesh oraon visited the area cc asked him for free connection enrollment camp in that area. it did not succed even after speaker's assurances. after that cc remained in direct communication with sdo electricy and je, gumla for electricity related other issues in her area. after much effort on 10th feb 2018, a free connection camp was organised and 75 families were given new connection for free. now villagers can use electricity at their homes.

jharkhand renebul urja vikas abhkaran of jilla gramin vikas abhikaran gave solar light and solar street light and solar lantern. 20 grams were given money for this, but they did not get it. amita had a meeting with mundari khunkati parishad and also screened her video. we also wrote and submitted log applications. khuntkati mundari parishad's members ke saath official ko video screen kiya gaya. adhikari ne kaha ki yojna ki rad hone ke face se ye tender nahi ho paya. and the money given to the villagers was refunded to them.--------------------------sameer:english+++---------20 villagers of mundari khunkati had filled up forms and submitted cash for availing solar lamps under jharkhand renewable energy development project. many days passed after submitting the application but they didn't receive any solar lamps. cc filmed a video on this issue. cc also held a community meeting with mundari khunkati council and screened the issue video to the villagers. villagers wrote a fresh application and submitted to officials at district. the video was also screened to the officials and the matter was discussed with them. officaisl told that since this was scrapped by government funds for solar lamps didn't arrive since they didn't receive any lamps. the officials however refunded the amount paid earlier to all the 20 villagers.
impact_plan: screening is done by going to khunti dc.

impact_achieved_description: janani shishu suraksha karyakram is one of the most important schemes of indian government whose purpose is to provide facilities to pregnant women and infants free of cost. also pregnant women should be given rs. 1400 and sahya rs. 350 as incentives but villagers of baghmara block, dhanbad district (jharkhand) were not provided any such incentives from primary health centre. as a result they were not able to give proper health care to their children.  community correspondent halima ejaj got to know about the issue, she documented it and screened it to the sarpanch and mahila adhyaksha. after seven months all pending incentives were paid off to the women. - by sandhya marwada

in year 2015, 40 new born girl child in mahuda village ( baghmara block, dhanbad district) jharkhand weren�t able to get benefit from ladli laxmi yojana because of not having a birth certificate. since last one year primary health centre of mahuda & sub-health centre of radhanagar were not issuing birth certificate to them. villagers gave written application to collector office twice but no action was taken regarding this issue. community correspondent halima ejaz, whose family was also affected of this issue, made a video about it and showed to the block medical officer in charge dr. s.m. jafrulla and he took immediate action to resolve it. in a month of complaint all the birth certificates were started issuing in primary health centre, mahuda. - by sandhya marwada

in jamdih village of rampur block, the anm (auxillary nurse midwife) had not opened the health centre in the last one year. as a result around 500 people, including women and children, faced health problems. the villagers confronted the anm about this but to no avail. cc shanti baraik came to know about this problem and made a video. the anm got scared of being exposed and started opening the centre regularly. she requested the cc not to show the video to her higher officer. people, who had to earlier resort to quacks for treatment, are now getting regular health services.

pooja : the government appoints auxilliary nurse midwives so they provide assistance to pregnant women who are not so financially sound free of cost. such was not the case in baraghutu village where an anm charged rs 300/- from the sister in-law of a 30-year old woman, who had delivered a healthy baby boy in sadar hospital. shikha kumari lives in sahibganj, and she made a video on the issue when she got to know about the incident from her sister.  while making the video, she got to meet with ravi kumar, who worked at nakshatra channel and told him about the problem. he came to interview the hospital in charge, who in turn called the anm. the issue was resolved instantly, when the video was not complete, and there was no need to screen the video to any of the higher authorities.

labor contractor had trafficket 12 men, 2 women and 4 children from jharkhand and 'sold' them to a contractor in goa. the workers were mistreated and paid only 200 rupees a week (whereas the daily rate in goa is about twice that for a day). the contractor had taken away their phones, id cards and put them all in a small house where they couldnt connect with anyone else. one of the workers somehow managed to get the word out to his wife in jhakhand and the wife happened to be cc shanti bariak's neighbor. shanti travelled with the wives of the workers from jharkhand to goa and managed to locate them all. the contractor was defiant and violent. he slapped and punched the workers as shanti was arguing with him to release them. advocacy managers in vv's goa office spoke with the police officials asking them to intervene but they were of no help. shanti and the vv staff spent a whole day in margaon police station but no action was forth coming. i think the police was involved. the contractor must have paid them beforehand. because they didnt do anything after talking to us. we just kept waiting", says shanti. later, with the help of a local social activist joseph vass, the vv team and the cc approached the district superindent of police and all the workers were released after about 20 hours of drama. shanti was filming most of this rescue operation and once the film was done she arranged for community screenings of it. in one place there were more than 500 people in the audience. they all thanked me so much and i felt great because i could be of help to these people", says shanti.

pradeep bhengra of kunhari village, basiya block (jharkhand) went to bangalore on 28/10/�14 to work in a particular factory but he was missing from there. due to that his family members were very worried. he told his mother that he was going for a month there and would return soon but he didn�t went bangalore. when his family asked to his friends who went along with him, they replied that pradeep was not with them. then, they went to police station to report fir but the police didn�t help them. community correspondent shanti baraik, who is a resident of the same village made a video about the issue and went to meet the sp (superintendent of police) of district and told him about the issue. as a result of that after a month of filing a report, police found pradeep in odisha and brought him back to the village.

shanti wrote the application in the name of pey jal vibhag. department sent the mechanic and the hand pumps were repaired. the repairing was done in the month of may 2015..  rampur revatoli village, there was no access to water for almost three years and the villagers had to go several kilometers to fetch the water and the hand pump was broken too.the villagers had made a written request and have given it to the cc. the cc has taken the request to the engineer. after the complaint was given, it took about 3-4 days for the pump to start working and te villagers had access to water. the video was made by the cc and screened to the water dpt authorities and and the samudaya(villagers). the repairing was done in the month of may 2015..  rampur revatoli village, there was no access to water for almost three years and the villagers had to go several kilometers to fetch the water and the hand pump was broken too.the villagers had made a written request and have given it to the cc. the cc has taken the request to the engineer. after the complaint was given, it took about 3-4 days for the pump to start working and te villagers had access to water. the video was made by the cc and screened to the water dpt authorities and and the samudaya(villagers). the repairing was done in the month of may 2015.
impact_plan: samuday ke saath awaden tayar ker ke separation me de na th.

impact_achieved_description: meeting was held in village. then community member told mukhiya to repair the handpump. mukhia contacted jalsahiya and the handpump was repaired. two times she visited mukiya of baromudi panchayat, laskar tudu.couple of times,he was informed.. the villagers had no access to water as the hand pump was not working. the cc made the video with the help of the women in the village and went to the mukhya a couple of times. a meeting was also held in the village and the video was screened. the villagers also went along and the village head has agreed to give three pipes but gave only two. the panchayat memebers have spent some money of their pwn but have approached the water board authorities and have requested for the pipes to be fixed.the pipes got fixed and the villagers now have drinking water. . the villagers had no access to water as the hand pump was not working. the cc made the video with the help of the women in the village and went to the mukhya a couple of times. a meeting was also held in the village and the video was screened. the villagers also went along and the village head has agreed to give three pipes but gave only two. the panchayat memebers have spent some money of their pwn but have approached the water board authorities and have requested for the pipes to be fixed.the pipes got fixed and the villagers now have drinking water.

impact_achieved_description: mission dhavada majhi tola panchayat east sasbeda ward no. 7 block gomiya district bokaro jharkhand had a centuries old very dirty road full of mud which was not being constructed even after a lot of efforts by the villagers due to which there was a problem in commuting and commuting. goriti kuzur had made a video on this problem on may 2, 2016 at the behest of akash kumar, where 12 families were facing a lot of problems. after making the video, the ward contacted the ward, informed about any problem, showed the video and also informed the head of the video whatsapp about this problem. video whatsapp and met him many times and discussed about this problem by going to the block and contacting the block development officer to show him the video contacted the officer about this problem, show him the video, kept reminding him by calling whatsapp several times and once a month and there was a camp in the block, submitted applications along with the villagers, in this way on september 2022 under the road mukhyamantri gramin pati yojana, a 225-feet road costing rs 249,000 has been completed. now 500 to 1000 people passing through this road are getting a lot of relief. 12 families here are also very happy.

impact_achieved_description: in pakur district of maheshpur block,(jharkhand) on the northern bank of the river there were many villagers of total 3 panchayats who had to travel through the boat to reach the other side of that river. especially 150 students and farmers were facing more problems due to no bridge they had to travel 10 km instead to 2 km daily through the boat. at times incidences of drowning also had happened in the past. government was not paying any attention to the issue. community correspondent emiliya hansda once visited that village and she came to know about the issue. she made a video about it and screened it to the panchayat and to government officials. as a result officials visited the place and issued orders to make a bridge on the river. formation of a new bridge was started after 6 months of making an issue video.  - by sandhya marwada

there is a provision in pradhanmantri gram sadak yojana to connect every village to the main road with good roads but in pakur district of maheshpur block from hathimara mission school to kilyapokar navoday vidyalaya( nearly 1 to 2 km distance) road was transformed into a mud and due to that nearly 200 students were facing many problems. during the monsoon the condition of that road used to get worse. villagers of neighbor village were also facing problems in travelling through this road. emilya hansda, the community correspondent was also one of them. she documented this issue and showed it to the villagers and to the legislator of that area. a new road was started constructing in 10 months of making an issue video. - by sandhya marwada
impact_plan: jila parisad ke sdasay sa milnay or bat karnay ke liya bola gaya.

impact_achieved_description: according to the pradhan mantri gram sadak yojana (pmgsy) every village must be connected with the other areas through good roads but near kakjol pakudia mission road (jharkhand) and bridge condition was very bad since last five years. village school was near the bridge so students were facing many problems in passing that road. during elections, politicians assured villagers to repair the road and the bridge but nothing happened. community correspondent elijabeth murmu read about the issue in a newspaper and she made video about it. she screened it to the village head and discussed about the issue to the villagers. after 3 months of making a video construction of new road and bridge was started in the village.  - by sandhya marwada
