impact_achieved_description: issue-pundag basti of ormanjhi block of ranchi district is situated at a distance of 27 km from ranchi. the population of pundang village is 500. pradahnmantri gram sarak yojna in us gaon se pundang gaon ko nahi jora gaya hai. the situation of the sarak of the village is very bad. impact process - in feb 2016 a community meeting was held in pundang village with the participation of women and men. aur usme video screening kiye. in the meeting, it was decided that 10-12 gramin blocks will go and bdos will meet. in march 2016, about 11 people were sent to their office from bdo. bdo of ormanjhi block rajnish kumar was told about the road condition of the village. usne sabse pehle pucha ki-gaon me gram sabha huwa ki nahi? the villagers said that there is a village meeting. then people talked about the sarak of their village. villagers kept the demand for road and asked bdo - what should be done to the villagers. unhone assured that - aap log aaye hain toh aaplogon ki baaton ko rahunga me dehyan me, aur jald hi kaam shuru hoga. uske kuch din baad 100 gaz road bana, mukhiya ke fund se. uske baad kaam ruk gaya tha. abhi saarak par miti bharne ka kaam churu huwa hai. now the road of the village will be made up to 14 km. english: pundang village of ormanjhi block, ranchi district situated only 27 kms from states capital was not benefitted under the pradhamnantri gram sadak yojna (prime minister rural road scheme). the development of the village was being affected severally due to bad condition of road. cc filmed a video on this issue and discussed the problem in the village. a community meeting was held by cc in february 2016 where the video was screened. as planned in the community meeting 11 villagers along with cc approached teh bdo in march 2016 with application for road. bdo assured teh villagers that their road will be constructed soon. few days later a 90 meters road was constructed through village heads funds and then the work stopped. as of now the remaining road is being filled with soil and a proper road is being built upto 14 kms.
impact_plan: write the application and meeting with bdo and submit the application. community involvement.
underlying_reason_of_issue: denial of service delivery or entitlement provision

impact_plan: make video and screen to project manager, ccl parej project

impact_achieved_description: the mud road leading to the forest from agaria tola village was completely blocked off by mining overdump (waste). this blockage severly limited agaria's 200 people from accessing thier rights over forest produce. they go collect firewood or fruits, bathe and drink thier cattle, fill potable water for themselves. this problem had been going on for the past 8 years and was created by the mines opearted by tata. cc mohan bhuyan made a video and along with the community approached the rural development officer at tata. the officer said that the road can only be cleared once the mining is over which will take 6 months. the villagers went back and made a blockade and stopped all the company trucks going into the mines. this yielded results and the road was repaired and access to forest has been cleared.

issue:- cook kranti devi and sahiyika, who built a kitchen for children in the primary school of rampur panchayat in kamdara block of gumla district, have not received their payment since april 2015. he has to sell jakar in the datuwan market to run his family. impact process:- shanti kumari baraik did the first screening after which the application was written in the name of dec. uske baad badlao ke liye kamdara ke brc accountant anjali madam se meet. someone said that their account number is wrong. aap gumla me jaakar baat kariye. tab shanti baraik the teacher and shikranti devi the doctor gumla went to idbi bank and met the accountant. application was written in the name of the bank. after that money was released in sikranti devi account. english: the cooking staff in the parimary school of bartand vilage of rampur panchayat, kamdara block, gumla district were not receiving thier wages since april 2015. these staff were poor triabsl who had to feed themselves by selling herbal stick sin the market in the absence of wages. cc filmed a video on this issue. later she organized a community screening and wrote down an application in the name of dec. next, she met the brc accountant at kamdara block regarding the issue. the officer said that the account number of the cook was wrong. officer advised to visit the district office and rectify the matter. cc with teh cooking staff and a school teacher visited the idbi bank accountant at gumla office. they submitted an application to correct the account number. a few days later the cooking staff received thier wagse in thier account.
impact_plan: by making awaden of the community, give the rights of divorce.
target_official: mid day mil accountant - anjali maidam

impact_achieved_description: scholarship was not provided to 150 students from 7th class to 10th class in the secondary school of dumbar village of churchu block, hazaribagh (jharkhand). due to which students of the school and their parents were facing many problems as scholarship was the only source to buy books and pens for students. books were provided by the school till the 8 standards only and after that, they have to manage on their own but their parents did not have an adequate amount of money to buy stationary. community correspondent manju kisku made a video about the issue and screened it to the block education officer. as a result of that student received their scholarship money for the whole year within a month. school also received last 2 years worth of money under scholarship.
impact_plan: video bana kar samuday or school may screening karna.
video bana kar samuday, school or bivag ke adhikari ke pass screening karna.
video bana kar bivag may dikhana or awaden dena.

impact_achieved_description: secondary school in purnadi village of domchach block, kodanar district (jharkhand) was lacking basic facilities and infrastructure due to which students and teachers were facing many problems. they did not have the boundary of the building, toilets, and hand pump and because of that workers were not able to cook the mid-day meal in the school. students were forced to drink and use water from the river, due to which they were getting ill. community correspondent vinti vishwakarma documented the issue and showed it to the block development officer (bdo) as a consequence of that a panchayat started constructing a boundary around the school but meanwhile villagers demanded to assimilate a temple and a health center inside the boundary, because of that the construction work stopped again. cc again made another video about the issue and screened it to the villagers. a meeting was arranged between villagers and school teachers in which they discussed the consequences of adding temple and a health center. at the end of the discussion it was decided to build a boundary excluding temple and health center and after 6 months, the boundary was built and a hand pump was repaired in the school.

the toilets in simaldahi middle school in maheshpur were in very bad condition due to which 44 students suffered. cc emeliya hansda screened an educational video made by another cc in the village to make them realize that problems like these can be solved. application was prepared after the screening and it was handed over to the block education officer. the toilets were repaired and the students now don't have to jump the wall to go outside to relieve themselves.

impact_plan: making a video every day or screening pass by the authorities.
make a video every day or pass screening by adhikari.

impact_achieved_description: utkaramit primary school in pundang, ormanjhi block of ranchi district, 52 students of the school were required to use dirty water due to the extraction of red water from chapakal, a video was made by nirmala. on 8-7-2016, around 10 women came to ormanjhi block, but in the beo meeting, they applied to the office. on 20-02-2017 again ormanjhi block nirmala gayi thi par us din bhi beo se mulakat nahi huwi. on 01-03-2017, beo madam from ranchi office was upset due to the problem. uske baad ko 29-04-2017 ko naya handpump kora gaya. english: the handpump in primary school of pundang village, ormanjhi block was fetching muddy red water which was not at all suitable for use. the 52 students and the mid day meal cooks depended on the unhygienic pond water for consumption. cc filmed a video on thsi issue and held a discussion in teh village. an application was written down in the meeting in the name of beo. next 10 women along with cc visited teh beo office where teh application was submitted. beo was busy in a different meeting thsu video coulnt be screened and face to face discussion couldnt happen. cc kept following teh issue with officer over the phone. after two months a new handpump was installed in the school premises.
impact_plan: meeting in community and meet ormanjhi beo.

impact_achieved_description: teachers in village godda pahar of powal panchayat of borio block of sahebganj district are not studying for two years. the resident of the village is unaware of the fact that he should be told. godda pahar ke vidyalay me 1 to 5 tak hai jisme ek hi teacher the ganga ram. in february 2015, shikha ne video banaya jiske baad. after 2 months, shikha again had a meeting with beo praful chandra singh of borio. i will check the vidyalaya. on 20-02-2017 shikha phir se godda pahar gayi jahan unhone dekha ki teacher ab rojana aa rahe hain. but the teacher is there. gram pradhan se baat huwi unhone ki baat ki shikha ke video banane ke 15 mahine baad aayi me school me nahi jaayi, jabki uske pehle kabhi nahi aayi aayi aur nov 2016 se teacher daily bachon ko parhane ke liye aa rahe hain. english: a teacher named ganguram of a school which has class from 1 to 5 ,in godda pahar village of powal panchayat were not visiting the school since 2 years which was keeping 30 children away from education. the villagers were unaware as to where to complain about this issue and to whom. cc shikha filmed a video on this issue in february 2015. in the next month cc explained this issue to the block education officer(beo) and took his appointment for a visit. two months later when cc called the beo office she came to know that a new officer had been posted. on speaking with him about teh issue he said to cc that he will investigate the matter. when cc visited the village on february 2017 she found that the teacher is visiting the school again. when cc met the village head during her visit she came to know from him that an investigation team arrived 15 months after she filmed the video. he also said that this was the first time any investigation team arrived in the village. villagers were happy that the officials took thier matter seriously.
target_official: distirct education officer - sahebganj - govind singh

impact_achieved_description: issue - in cuha pahar village of mando block of sahebganj district, there is 8th standard and there are 4 teachers. magar wo saal me sirf 2 din aate hain. 26 jan and 15 aug. and the rest of the day remains absent. the children of our village go to another private school and they are given 200 rs a month. impact process:- shikha ne is video ko august 2015 me banaya tha.uske baad shikha ki baat april 2016 ko mandro block ke beo se phone par iski suchna di. but no one can do anything. uske baad shikha ne gramino ko ye vieo dikhayi. it was because of us in december 2016 that there was talk of working with ndtv. uske baad january 2017 me ndtv team ke saath cuwa pahar gaye aur phir se unke dowara shoot huwi. uske baad sahebganj ke district sikcha adhichak ko iski suchna di gayi aur unke office me jaakar unse interview bhi liya. unhone afshos kiya kiya ki teacher pahar apr pahria bachon ko kyun nahi parhate hain, paper me bhi only report jama karte hain. in front of shikha, they phoned brc and heard a lot. later on, the beo circle met marandi and also took her interview. ndtv team ke lautne ke baad video ko kuch important personality aur jharkhand govt. a panel discussion was also held with minister saryu roy. because of that, they did not go to sahebganj and they also went wrong with the administration of sahebganj. uske baad khalbali machi aur action lete huwe uska samadhan kiya gaya. now the school is open and the children are also getting mid day meal. english: the teachers assigned by state educational authorities in middle school of cuha pahar tribal village, mando block, sahebganj district never attended the school except for two national celebration days ie republic day and independence day. the children in teh village had to attend far off private schools through a payment of rs.200. cc being from the same community filmed the issue in august 2015. a year later cc informed the situation to the beo over phone. however no action were taken and still teachesr were not regular. later in january 2016 ndtv in collboration with videovolunteers vsiited the village to film thsi issue.then the team visited the district education officer and interviewed hin. the block education officer was interrogated by the deo on his own and the beo was later interviewed by the team. the issue was highlighted by some important persons in those states and was also raised by politicians in panel discussions. as a result the teachers were regular in the school. the school now runs daily

pandya munda from salgadih village was not receiving his monthly old age pension of rs.600 since the last one year. he had visited the bank several times for the same but to no avail. cc amita tuti made a video on issue and took pandya munda to met the block officer. they submitted an application on the matter and showed the video. the officer immediately asked the computer operator to check the records and found that pandya munda's name was not in the records. the officer immediately made corrections and recorded munda's name and he is now receiving pension.

english: in arya panchayat of basia block of gumla district, dhansingh dam was built for irrigation from jalashay pariyojna, after which there was no water for 6 years. pani na milne ka karan tha ki nahar me pura mud bhar gaya tha jis karan vahan ke gramin rabi phasal nahi uga pa rahe the. shanti ne video banane ke baad jila parishad chaitu oraon se phone par is dam ki stithi ke bare me baat ki. because of us, on 16 january 2015, milking the community's saath, anumandal karyalay basia medharna was given and anumandal padadhikari was also written like this. anumandal adhikari ke saath ye charge huwa ki application ko we will bhejenge to the discrict commissioner. aur jaise hi dc ka nirdesh ayega mai nahar ko thik karwane ka kaam karwanunga. 300 people of the community were involved in badlao lane. after removing the heavy soil in the afternoon, there are waves of happiness in the villages and every 6 villages are trying to irrigate the people with dams. english: dhansingh dam jalashay project was made for irrigation in gumla district, basia block, arya panchayat but from 6 years the villagers did not get water. the canal was filled with mud and for this reason the villagers could not grow rabi crop. shanti made a video and contacted the district officer chaitu oraon explaining to him the state of the dam on the phone. on 16 january 2015 a protest was held at the subdivision office, basia by the community, and they submitted a written notice to the subdivision officer. the subdivision officer discussed that he would send the application to the district commissioner. as soon as the district commissioner's orders come in the canal will be repaired. 300 people from the community came together to bring change. the villagers were delighted after the mud was removed from the canal. nowadays, 6 villages use this dam for irrigation.

impact_plan: got tired in the village meeting.
make a video and do a beach screening every day or create a logo.

impact_achieved_description: witch hunting is a rampant practice in jharkhand especially in tribal communities. on 7 august 2015, 5 innocent women from from karanji maraitali village were dragged out of thier homes by thier own  villagers and were beaten to death within minutes accusing them of being witches. all the people in the village belong to "sarna" tribal community. a month before this killing took place a young boy had expired due to illness,  and thus villagers suspected all those 5 women had performed witchcraft on him to kill him. on the day women were kille din the village ,  a advocate and 4 police men had visited the village to investigate the matter.the family members of the victims said that these officials would often  visit the village and would assure help, but do nothing. the main persons who killed those women were still on the run and were not arrested.  the afmily members of victims had often seen the killers in the village in thier homes, which made them worry more. cc came to know about the issue from newspapers.  somehow cc came in contact with ngo "aali" to seek legal help during her work on this issue. cc filmed the the video on this issue which was screened among the members of aali organisation.  the screening helped to understand the issue in depth and plan further steps to solve the problem.  cc and aali representatives visited the victims familiy in the village and discussed the issue with them. later cc with aali membesr approached the polic eofficer at block level to discuss the issue.  police officer were very casual and negligent about this matter. they said they have given thier phone numbers to the villagers and they will inform them whenever anything happens again. cc told the police that killers were seen in the vicnity of the village itself  and she wiill move to higher police officails if tehy dont arrest the killers soon. police officail assured cc and aali team that they will arrest the killers soon. 1 week later police arrested  a handful of people and jailed them. community urged cc to help meet higher police officials at district level so that more people could be arested and more protection be given. cc and aali organisation also submitted a written application to cid officer  at district level with 3 demands of the community which were 1) main killers be arrested 2) compensation be relaesed 3) 4 policemen would patrol 24 hrs in the villagers regularly.  as a result of ccs efforst with teh help of aali 40 people were arrested, 1 lakh 20000 were compensated to each victim familt (total 5). the case is running at the ranchi cicvil court. as a result of ccs and aalis efforts lives of 3 more women were saved who were on the next hit list to murdered as witches in the same village.

17 year old nati paharin of sahebganj district, bacha panchayat, mandro block pergodda bedo's was sold off by her husband maheshwar paharia for 70,000 rupees. women trafficking is a major issue in this belt and cc is aware of the issue. the girl's family found out about the incident on 15-06-2016. they filed an fir at the nearest police station.  shikha filmed a  video on aug 2016, after which she contacted the mirja chawki station house officer and asked for a copy of the fir. she also inquired about the arrest of maheshwar to which the commissioner responded that they are trying their best but he is missing. in oct 2016, she again met with the station house officer brhamdeo chawdhri and case in charge  tiwariji but they denied giving her an interview. during this time, the girl's brother ranjan malto was in regular communication with shikha. on 20 november 2016, nati paharin contacted shikha and gave her the complete address. cc shikha took nati paharin's brother to meet with sahebganj sp. the sp said that they will first arrest maheshwar.  in the meantime, cc shikha spoke to nirmal gorana in delhi . she sent nati's photo, adhar card, school tc, and fir copy and narrated the entire story through whatsapp. after that on 21 dec 2016,  nirmal gorana rescued nati pharin from panipath and kept her safe at panipath shelter home.  the station officer mirja chawki sent over  nati's brother and 2 policemen to panipath. they left for sahebganj from delhi on 26-12- 2016. the shelter home police informed that nati was pregnant and would stay at the shelter. later on shikha shared the story with dainik jagran and prabhat khabar and the story was published in the newspapers. now nati is brought to sahebganj.
impact_plan: fir has been launched. will contact mahila koshang.

impact_achieved_description: people living below poverty line are supposed to get rice (amongst other things) at rs.1 per kilo from the local fair price shop run by the public distribution system. corruption in pds shops are ramgarh in jharkhand. in lopongtandi ulhara village the shopkeeper was charging rs.50 for 32 kilos of rice. the 80 people who were depended on this shop were not only forced to pay more but also got 3 kilos less (each family is entitled for 35 kilos of rice). many times the villagers had confronted the shopkeeper about this but he always made an excuse of not having enough stock. cc basanti soren made a video on this issue and spoke to shop keeper about the dire consequences of his actions. basanti and community had a meeting and decided that when they went the next time they would rs.35 rupees and take 35 kilos. then entire community went together and asked for 35 kilos of 32 kilos for the right price. a verbal fight ensued. when the shop keeper realized that basanti was filming the confrontation she agreed to give 32 kilos for rs.32. this was a victory for the community. the cc screened her 'success story video to the shope keepr which made her realize that she's still in the wrong and started giving full ration to the villagers. everyone now gets the entitled 35 kilos at rs.1 per kilo.

isu video about tulsi hembrom ke dawara isu video 2015 me banaya tha road ke upar jo ke jila purbi singhbhum block potka panchayat ke murgagutu ke hartopa tak tangbanga nadi tak narega ka doora murum road banaya ja raha tha jese adha - adura kar diya gaya hai. isu video banane ke bad tulsi hembrom ke doora pahal karne ke pehle he es road par vibhag ke doora pcc road benna chalu ho gaya. isu video banane ke 20 months ke bad es samasaya ke upar badlao ho paya badlao se 12 gao ke logo faida huwa hai jeske abadi 9400 ke karib hai. i am quite happy with the use of pcroad. english: in east singhbum district, potka block, hartopa panchayat teh road from murgagutu to tangbanga around 2 kms was to be filled with soil under mnrega but was left unfinished which was affecting the people commuting over the road. 3 years had passed since teh road aws approved to be concretised however the road aws still incomplete. cc filmed a video on this issue and discussed it with community members. later cc along with 3 community members submitted an application requesting completion of road to gram sevak at panchayat. when cc highlighted the issue through video, news was also published in local newspapers which helped put pressure on authorities. 20 months later the entire road was made into pcc road.

people in pajania village worked for 36 days to build a well for one khalil ansari, however, they were only paid wages for 18 days. the workers had submitted an application to the concerned department but it was of no use. cc bharti kumari and the community made another application and went to meet block programe officer and presented the matter and showed him the video. bpo cited lack of funds as a reason for delayed payment and assured prompt payment. after two months all the 8 of them were paid their dues and khalil ansari's well is also fully built.

kishun mahto of telmocho village, in telmocho jalapurti plant since 1997, is working as a key man. inka payment was not received for 14 months. due to which the family was in a bad mood. his son had to work at the drug store to run his family because he didn't have money to run his house. bharti made a video and wrote an application in the name of executive engineer and submitted it to his office. bharti ne samuday me screen kiya jisme 8 log shamil the. videos of bharti kumari, kishum mahto and 1st executive engineer from the community were also shown. after one week, the executive engineer called kishun to meet him and signed the voucher and sent it to the phd department. kishun mahto was given a dd of 53,000 after one week. english: kishun mahto from telmoncho village has been working in water department of telmonco since 1997 on contract basis. he wasn't receiving any salary since 14 months. this was largely affecting his life since he was the sole breadwinner in the family. his son was forced to work in a medical store to earn instead of attending the school. kishun had several times submitted application to executive engineer but he didn't get any response. cc filmed a video on this issue and she herself met the engineer along with the kishun. a week later engineer called kishun and asked him to sign a voucher to submit it to phd department for payment. a week later kishun mahto received a demad draft of rs. 53,000 from the engineer.

13 tribal families of basko bera pahar village, kherwa panchayat, mandro block, sahebganj district were struggling since many years to receive ration card so taht they can avail ration from government ration shop at subsized rates. these families earned thier livelihood by selling wild herbs and bamboo firewood. they had several times approached the village head. one of the family had submitted the application 6 times in the bdo office but they didn't receive any response. cc filmed a video on this issue and called up a community meeting in the village. the video was screened to almost 50 people in the meeting and an application was written in teh name of block development officer. cc and villagers submitted this application to block development officer. they also approached the marketing officer, to whom they screened the video and discussed the problem. the official assured villagers that they would be provided teh cards. six months later all teh 13 families received the ration cards and are thus receiving the subsidized ration by the government. ****************************** ********************************************************** ****************************** panchayat kherwa of mandro block of sahebganj district, basko bera pahar me gangu pahar and 13 parivar ka ration card nahi tha jiske karan unko rasahn nahi mil rahi thi. the villagers also applied to the chief and asked the bdo not to do anything. sanju ne video banaya aur video banane ke baad community me screening kiya jisme gaon ke 50 log shamil the. villagers helped for badlao. baithak ke baad application likhe aur aur anumandal padahadikari ke paas submit kiye. marketing officer was video screened. 6 months after impact aaya jab cc ne impact par kaam shuru kiya tha.

primary school teacher mamta murmu and other 4 teachers of pahadpur village (jharkhand) were not getting paid since last 16 months. in july 2014 district supply officer a.b.e. khalkho went for inspection in school, he made a report on less number of students present in school since then, her salary had been stopped. community correspondent mary nisha made video on this issue in november 2014. she instructed her to write application to the bdo, sundar pahadi and she submitted it within 2 days. after a year of filing application she got her salary. - by sandhya marwada

two teachers of upper middle school in kulbhanga village never showed up in the school for the last two years except on 15th august (independence day). as a result 45 children were being deprived of education. several times villagers had visited the district collector's office and submitted applications twice but no steps were taken. cc shikha paharin made a video and discussed the matter with some villagers. cc even appraised the district collector of this matter who spoke to the concerned bdo about the problem. next day the cc, the community and the dc met again along with the district school commissioner and action was assured. the following day the two teachers were suspended and their salaries stopped. 15 days later 2 new teachers were appoint. the school now runs smoothly and all 45 children are going to school.shikha and the community prdahan had complained to the dc.
impact_plan: write the application with the involvement of community and dc has to be met.

impact_achieved_description: in a primary school of lakhandi village of saraikala block, saraikala district (jharkhand) there was no kitchen since 8 years to make mid day meal and because of that food was being cooked in the corridor of the school which was not safe. during monsoon season it used to become more difficult for cooks to cook mid-day meal for students. a hand pump was fitted in the school but it was not working properly and also the water of that pump was not potable. a toilet was constructed in 2010 but it was also in a bad condition. community correspondent sujita tudu, who is the resident of the same village, made a video about it and showed it to the block education officer (valmiki prasad), he took immediate actions and after 7 months, construction of a kitchen and toilets was being started soon. also water from the hand pump was also potable after repairing it.

6 year old girl was raped by a 14 old boy in bhagatkocha colony of ranchi. cc nirmala ekka knew the victim's mother and she had narrated the incident to her. after consulting the lawyer, nirmala and the mother to argora police station and lodged a complaint. the boy confessed the crime but the girls family was afraid that the police may mis record statements. therefore the cc and the community pressured the police to record victims statement in the magistrate's court where the statement is taken more seriously. uske 4 mahina baad sabse pahle bachi ki maa ka gawahi huwa.uske ek saptah baad nirmala ke gawahi juvenile court me huwa. aali org. ne compensationn ke liye court me awedan dakhil karaya. uske 3 mahina ke baad 20 feb 2016 ko compensation mila. compensation ka amount 20 hazar rupye mile.

there are total 5 sadasay in lagori tudu's family and they come from bpl family. kranti murmu ke dawara video benaay ke bad lagori tudu ke dawara se indra awash ke leya bivhag me awaden jama ke fer kuch mah ke bad he lagori tudu ka name indrawash ke list me aa gaya fer kuch deno me indrawash nirman ka kam chalu huwa aur within 3 months, the family of lagori tudu is quite happy after indraawash has been completed. english: lagori tudu and his family of 5 members belongs to bpl category and had been applying for indira awas scheme for the past two years. however they never received any benefit inspite of being eligible for the scheme. indira awas is government scheme wherein poor and eligible families receives funds for construction of houses. cc kranthi filmed a video on this issue. cc and lagori decided to submit a fresh form for the scheme and speak with the village council officers. this time lagoris name was listed in teh beneficiary list. within 3 months the house was constructed.
impact_plan: prepare the application with lagori family.
vinti visited thrice to the village. she was associated with sangram org. they wrote the article and gave it in the akhbar called khabar mantra and prabhat khabar. it was published.
divorce by doing beach screening of the community or by making awaden.
application has to be prepared and to be submitted to bdo of mandu.

impact_achieved_description: kundan das of 5 years age from jayantigram village in madhurpur block was bitten by a fox while he was releiving himself. due to medical negligence at various govt hospitals kundan developed rabies and eventually died. cc mukehs rajak made a video and vv started an online campaign. cc mobilised community and submitted application to surgeon and the district collector. after 18 months of follow ups, kundan's parents were compensated an amount of inr 1.5 lakhs. besides they are assured a regular montlhy supply of rations and have arranged for good schooling for kundans sister.
ya video benane ke bad mobile per gao me 6 logo ke beach screening keya gaya tha.

20 workers of nagar nigam in ward no. 37 in ranchi (jharkhand) didn?t get their salary of 6 weeks from past 3 months and because of that they were facing many problems. when workers asked for their salary but supervisor replied to leave the job if they had any problem with the work. community correspondent nirmala ekka documented this issue and screened it to the nagar nigam officer. he assured them to pay the salary in 3 weeks and as a result of that within 2 weeks all the workers were salaried their money.
impact_plan: mobilize the safaikarmi and meet the ward parshad with safaikarmi.

impact_achieved_description: issue video - pandrasali village in khuntpani block, west singbhum was electrified in 2009. since then there is no lineman provided, due to which villagers have to deal with any repairs like fuse or transformer malfunction etc. complaint was made to electricity department in ckp circle twice in 2012-13 but nothing was done. villagers also complained in jseb headquarters in ranchi but nothing was done. villagers have stopped paying for electricity bill currently. impact process :- the people of pandrasali village had applied 2 times in the power department of chakradharpur and nothing was being done even after applying for each. chakradharpur electricity department didn't get any response, then jseb, ranchi electricity department's headquarter also gave application for the people who are living outside. kai baar awedan dene ke baojud kuch karwai nahi hone ki face se gaon walon ne gaon me ek baitahk ki. it was decided in the meeting that the whole village will be surrounded by electricity and will apply. every month the meeting is held in the village, the log of the women's group and the gram sabha are held. on october 2016, 250 villages surrounded the division. even after enclosing the power, there is no effect on the power supply and no one can heal the power. later on, kamal purty filed an online discussion in mukhyamanti online jan sanvaad on 22/12/2016. because of this, vibahg woke up and vibhag started working for electricity in pandrasali. on 26 april 2017, a transformer was installed in the village by the department. now there is electricity in the village. english: pandrasali village in khuntpani block, west singbhum was electrified in 2009. since then there was no lineman appointed in the region, due to which villagers had to themselves deal with repairs like fuse or transformer malfunction. complaint was made to electricity department in ckp circle twice in 2012-13 but nothing was done. villagers also complained in jseb headquarters in ranchi but nothing was done. villagers had stopped paying for electricity bill since there was no electricity due to malfunctions.cc filmed a video on this issue. the villagers submitted applications 2 times at chakradharpur electricity unit but no action was taken. thus villagers submitted a fresh application to jseb at ranchi electricty head unit however even then no action was taken. villagers held a meeting in the village and they decided to mob the electricity office and stage their demands. in october 2016 250 villagers held the same protest. even then there was no change. cc later submitted an online complaint on mukhyamantri online jan sanvaad. this complaint actually worked and electrcity department had to employ a lineman in village effecting from 26 april 2017.
impact_plan: make video and meet chief engineer, jseb

impact_achieved_description: aamna bibi, a resident of purni singhdho village in madhupur district, lost her new born baby due to doctors negligence at the sub divisional hospital in mahdupur. cc mukesh rajak mobilised the community and submitted an application to surgeon and district magistarte. he also screened the video. after some days when no steps were taken by the administartion, the video was screened in the village and community was mobilized to take out a protest rally to the sub divisonal hospital. after 18 months, aamini bibi was compensated rs.85000. ( rs.85000 for indira awas & toilet, monthly pension of rs.600 to father in law, doctors attend the hospital regularly) after the incident since the facilities at hospital were improved it benefitted all the people from 222 villages that fall under madhupur block. 4 new security guards, 3 new sweeper  have been appointed after the incident by hospital management committee . also new bedsheets, 50 blankets have been approved.

from january 2013 in piparatand village of banswada panchayat of baghmara block, dhanbad district (jharkhand) due to absence of auxiliary nurse midwife (anm) in health centre, vaccination of infants and mothers was not occurring since past 1 year. due to which infants and new mothers were facing many problems. in emergency situation, villagers had to move in baghmara health centre which was very far. community correspondent bharti kumari documented the issue and screened it to chief medical officer sm jafarullah and wrote him an application to ensure that vaccination are resumed at the village. as a result of that after 3 months of making a video, a new anm was posted in piparatand village.

there was a huge water problem in oraon tola of bokaro district gomiya block panchayat khamra for about 80 years. the well and seven chapakals were whipped by the government, but water came out in only 1 chapakal, but hardly 2 buckets of water comes out of it, due to which more than 200 people here had a lot of drinking water problems and clothes and bathing. had to go to the river. the villagers of this place demanded water by giving an application to the indian explosives limited company located here and also protested at the gate of the company, but the water was not received, then on 9 june 2015, at the behest of the headman and with the cooperation of the villagers, i video was made. after making the video, contacted the chief, did video whatsapp twice in 2017 and 2018, went to the block and informed the block development officer about this problem and also gave the application and ph.d. in this way the department was contacted by phone, on behalf of the drinking water sanitation department, the work started by engineer swaraj sharma on 2019, 20 and now from march 15, 2021, water is coming to every house through pipes, which is providing water to 9 lakh people. are getting.
impact_govt_official_support_details: panchayat officials, block development officer or other block officials
impact_raised_awareness: screened/shared a video about the problem
themes: an entitlement problem - meaning a government anti-poverty scheme that people apply for
underlying_reason_of_issue: low quality service delivery of entitlement provision

impact_achieved_description: shanti wrote the application in the name of pey jal vibhag. department sent the mechanic and the hand pumps were repaired. the repairng was done in the month of may 2015.. the video was made in august 2014, pahan toli village, both the handpumps were broken. it's been two years since the hand pumps were broken. the villagers have been fetching water from a far away well and the water was dirty and contaminated. the cc had requested the villagers to write a letter to te water board, but as they were unaware, she had to do that too. the pump was repairedi n 4-5 days after submittting the letter and screening the video to the water board members. the village samudaya has helped shanti make the video and it was creened in the village and to the water board engineers. . the video was made in august 2014, pahan toli village, both the handpumps were broken. it's been two years since the hand pumps were broken. the villagers have been fetching water from a far away well and the water was dirty and contaminated. the cc had requested the villagers to write a letter to te water board, but as they were unaware, she had to do that too. the pump was repairedi n 4-5 days after submittting the letter and screening the video to the water board members. the village samudaya has helped shanti make the video and it was creened in the village and to the water board engineers.
impact_plan: vivag ma awaden aor video dikahana tha

impact_achieved_description: the aganwadi center (creche) in behradih village was built 10 years back but it has not been functional. ration or food were not being given. cc vinti viswakarma, with the support from ngo sangram made an application and sent it to ncpcr. the national commisson of protection of child rights then sent off a letter to the district collector of koderma asking for action. dc then sent an official from the block office to inquire the matter. the issue was solved and the aganwadi is now functioning well and about 120 people are getting its benefits.

godhra river is located between rajdoha and murgaguttu village 10 km away from the hartopa and domjuri panchayat, eastern singhbhum district, potka block (jharkhand). the river flows between two mountains and people of these two villages uses its water for bathe and their cattle. every year, from december to february that spot used to turn into the tourist spot and the tourists used to throw plastic and left-over food into the river which was polluting the water and due to that villagers were facing problems in bathe. community correspondent tulsi hembrom who belongs to the same community, documented this issue and screened it in the community. as a result members of gayatri parivar, narvapahad took the responsibility to clean the area. within a 3 months of making a video godhra river was cleaned.

impact_achieved_description: issue:- 6 women of jambuwa village of kusumbha panchayat of bishugarh block of hazaribagh district are not getting the incentive amount due from janni surakcha yojana. unko account number, adhar card, janam parman patra jama karwaya gaya 2 saal pehle hi hi, ki liye inhone daur - bhi kiya par protsahan rashi nahi mil rahi hai. impact process:- video banane ke baad badlao parikriya shuru kiya. sunita devi told about the problem that the beneficiary and her son have not received the payment amount. anm punam tirkey ne madad karne ki baat kahi aur unlogon se document manga. unhone said that the document will be forwarded. sahiya sunita devi has also received the money of 3 women in the account of the beneficiary. english: 6 women from jambuwa village, kusumbha panchayat, bishugarh block, hazaribagh district did not receive the motivational monetary award provided by government to the women post delivery. thier adhar cards, birth certificates and completed forms were submitted 2 years ago but even then they didnt receive any funds. they hassled a lot for the scheme benefit however thier efforts were in vain. cc filmed a video on this issue and discussed the issue with women. a plan was laid out where they decided to begin with anm and sahiya firstly. women and cc approached the anm and talked about teh issue. she asked to submit the documents to her which the women did at the spot. cc and women also met the sahiya and told about teh issue. sahiya and anm are the only ones who are authorized to process the funds thus dealing with them was an important step. after much wait 3 women received the funds in their accounts.

impact_achieved_description: before sanju's video was made, there were open applications for pension and the middle man didn't even log on to get the money. sanju also wrote an application along with the video banane ke saath samudaya ke saath and also submitted the adhikari. 5 people got pension after 4 months of video banane. english: surji paharin of 61 years is from district sahibganj, block mandro, panchayat kherwa village ambrabedo. even after applying for old age pension 3-4 times he did not receive any. there are 5 other women from the same village who are also deprived of their pensions. they too applied for it several times. the middle man even took money from them. sanju made a video about their problems. at the same time he submitted an application to the officer. 4 months later, people started receiving their pensions.

impact_achieved_description: in ambrabedo village of kherwa panchayat of mandro block of sahebganj district, wild elephants damaged the house of gangu paharia and ate all the grains. jab sanju ko pata chala toh sanju gangu went to paharia's village and went to his village. sanju spoke to his family and got ready to write an application. his family members said that you should take a photo of the damage done along with the application. video aur awedan ke baad van pramandal adhikari ke paas jane ka nirnay liya gaya. kuch din ke baad gaon se 5 log van pramandal adhikari kk tiwari ke paas gaye aur unko footage dikhaya gaya aur awedan bhi diya gaya. they signed the application and asked to give it to bara babu. bara babu and ranger ne bataya ki jaise hi fund ayega aapko phone karke bula liya jayega. unhone unkoa mobile number bhi manga. gangu paharia got 6000 rupees as compensation after 3 months. ------------------sameer ++ english : sahabganj district , ambrabedo village wild elephants entered the village and destroyed gangu paharia house, household things, ate up 200kg ration and freshly harvested crop . they also destroyed the seeds he had kept for next crop. the house wall and utensils were also destroyed. gangu had submitted applications to forest officials several times but there wasn't any response. villagers informed the details of the damage caused by wild elephants to the forest department and demanded compensation. cc filmed the issue and submitted an application to deputy forest officer at block level. after 5 months gangu paharia received rs.6000 compensation. he bought 200 kg of rice and some seeds for his next crop.

for more than 6 months due to nonsubmission of certain identity documents. surji being non literate person coulnt resolve this issue, nor she could ask help from the officials who always treated her with no respect. she and her family faced problems in feeding herself and her family due to non availability of pension. cc filmed a video on this issue and held a meeting with surji and her community members regarding solving the problem. they decided that they will freshly fill up the pension forms and submit them again to teh official. following day, cc with surji bought the pension forms from the mandro block office and teh information regarding the submission of this forms. they filled up the forms when they returned home and few days later submitted the forms and documents to the circle officer in teh block office. officer assured cc and surji that pension will be resumed soon after all teh investigation is being done. 4 months later pension arrived in the passbook of surji. ****************************************** ********************************************************** ***** issue:- district sahabganj prakhand mandro panchayat kharwa village ambra bado's surji impact_achieved_description: durgapur, a village of 500 people in jamtara district, had no electricity but every household received bills for usage! cc kranti murmu made a video on this issue and screened the footage back to the community and galvanized them to act. soon after the screening they wrote out a formal written complaint and decided upon a date to take the delegation to the block. on the decided date they went to the block office but were sent away to the district headquarter to meet with the sub divisional officer. they met the sdo, showed the footage, submitted the application. two weeks later an electricity transformer was installed in the village.

impact_achieved_description: 75 households in pahan toli village did not have access to electricity from 4 months. they had no othe option and thus have to spend thier lives in dark. the problem was that the transformer had gone faulty and it needed replacement. also teh vilalgers had to walk or travel at least 5 km to get thier mobile phones charged at teh rate of rs.10 per charging. inspite of no electricity the villagesr were receiving the bills regularly. villagers had given applications thrice but no action was taken. cc amit topno filmed a video on this issue on janaury 2017. they held a community meeting in the vilalge and an application was written in the name of electricity department officer. cc along with 5 villagers submitted the application at the kamdara electrciity department in the same month. the electrciity officaisl finally responded and askeed vilalgers to carry teh transformer in the village at thier own expense. electrcity department would have taken more days to carry teh transformer to vilalge thus vilalgers themselvse decided to carry it, so that they can have electricity quickly. at teh end of teh month the tranformer was repaired and was setup at bambiayro pahan toli located tower. electrcity supply began teh same day and teh 350 vilalgesr are acessing the electrcity convieneintly

impact_achieved_description: saraikela district ke jankipur gaon me electric poll aur wire toh 2004-2005 se laga huwa tha par abhi tak bijli nahi aayi thi because transformer unko nahi diya gaya tha jiske karan raat ko gaon walo ke liye raat ka samay andhkar me gujarna hota tha. isko lekar sujeeta ne video banayi thi. video banane ke baad gaon me meeting rakha gaya aur bijli kaise gaon me pahunche uske upar charcha huwi. gaon wale awedan pahle hi bijli department me de chuke the isiliye dubara dena nahi chate the. unhone nirnay kiya ki humlogon ne mukhaya ko vote dekar hai toh usko ye kaam saunpna kahiye. tab gaon walo ne mukhiya ko kaam saunpa. uske kuch dino baad karwai shuru huwi. aayaa in transformer village. jahan wire aur poll nahi the vehicle bhi poll se wire ko connect kiye gaya. ab 5-6 electric poll lagana baki hai. the transformer has been installed. -----------------sameer++english: the people of saraikela had no electricity and thus had to spend their lives in darkness. the electric poles and wires were set up across the entire village in 2004-2005 year, however no transformer was provided to the villagers by the electricity department officials. cc filmed a video on this issue and a community meeting was held in the village to discuss what can be taken collectively to solve the electricity problem. the villagers had already submitted application for receiving transformer to electricity department but didn't get any response from them, thus they were little apprehensive in submitting the application again. then they came up with the idea that they will push the village head to approach electricity department since they all have elected him. thus villagers and community spoke with village head and handed over him the job. a few days later the village head began the application process. transformer was given to the villagers. many houses that didn't have electric poles and wiring near them were also given electricity supply. transformer has been installed in the village now and all these tribal villagers have electricity in their homes.

impact_achieved_description: in kundgari village, there is no ban on toilets under nirmal bharat yojna. especially women are getting more worried. in the rest of the villages, the toilet is banned along with the plan, but in kundgari village, there is no ban. the head of ora prakashan has also applied for this reason, but no action is being taken. mukhiya ka kahanna tha ki logon ke us gaon ne vote nahi diya tha isiliye application ke dene bhi koi kaam nahi kar rahe hain. anita oraon ne ish samasya par banayi video aur samuday me baithak ki. 20 people of the village attended this meeting. on the other hand, there is no need to ban toilets in other villages. anita ne mukhiya ko kiya kiya aur pahal karne ki baat kiya aur unke taraf se koi action nahi ho payega toh bdo ko iss samasya se avagat karayenge. the chief came to know about anita's work and brother came to anita's house. after 5 months of meeting, bricks and sand started falling for the construction of toilet. now all the household toilets have been banned and the villagers are using them.---------------------sameer:english : 1000 villagers of kundgari village had to defecate in open since no toilets were being sanctioned to them inspite of government scheme for constructing toilets was available under nirmal bharat scheme. especially the women of these villages faced main problems. toilets were being actively constructed in the neighboring villages but not in this village. several villagers had submitted application to village head but still were not benefitted. according to village head the reason for him to not sanction toilets was that the villagers didn't vote for him in last election & hence he was acting against the villagers. cc filmed the issue and held a community meeting that was attended by 20 villagers. at the end of meeting cc made a phone call to village head and told him that if he doesn't sanction the toilets for villagers then all the villagers will approach the block development officer with the video. the village head realized his mistake and subsequently he went to meet cc at her home. village head discussed the issue with cc and agreed to sanction the toilets. 5 months later the village head bought construction materials for toilets in the village. at present day all the villagers have their own toilets and are using them without any problems.

impact_achieved_description: toilets are being constructed by bccl in khuntpani block of west singhbhum district in schools (under swachh bharat abhiyan) which the contractor of bccl has given incomplete construction and labor has not been paid. a video was made on this issue and a video was made in the village of khuntpani. it was decided in the meeting that the application should be given to the contractor of bccl and in the afternoon there was a meeting with rajnikant verma, district magistrate of west singhbhum district. after 3 days of the meeting, kamal talked to the contractor on the phone and met the bccl engineer. and made the application. uske kuch dino ke baad jila sikcha padadhikari se milne gaye. milne par jila sikcha padadhikari ne kaha ki unko iski khabar mili hai aur kaam jald hi shuru hone wala hai. we have lost material for 3 days and we have paid for one week. in this work, the idf ngo also made a difference. ---------------sameer++english: bbcl had undertaken the responsibility to construct toilets in schools of khuntpani block, west singhbhum district under the swach bharat mission. the contractors who undertook the construction of toilets didn't complete them and also didn't pay the laborers who worked in it. cc filmed a video on this issue. cc held a community meeting and also held a meeting with school committee members. in this meeting all of them decided to submit a fresh application to the contractor and one more application to district education officer named rajnikant verma. 3 days later cc spoke to contractor on phone about the issue and also met the bccl engineer. cc submitted an application to engineer. a few days later the cc met and discussed the issue with the district education officer. district education officer told cc that he is aware of this issue and the construction work will begin soon. 3 days after this meeting, construction materials were bought on the site. a week later all the unpaid laborers were also paid.

impact_plan: write the application in the name of bdo and keep the demand accordingly.

impact_achieved_description: in ambatari village of kanachatti block, chatra district (jharkhand) a school had been opened but there was no hand pump for water in the school since last 12 years. they were using water from the river for cooking and drinking and during summer time the river used to dry due to which students and school management was facing many problems. they didn�t have any information from the authorities about putting up a hand pump. sometimes due to bad quality of water, students used to get ill. school management gave application many times but nothing happened. community correspondent made a video about the issue and she also wrote an application and submitted to the block education officer. as a result of that after 8 months school got a new hand pump and student and teachers started getting clean and safe drinking water.

in purandih village 220 students and their teachers were facing problem for 7 yearss since the school had play equipment or drinking water. the toilet was dirty and villagers often used the school premise as open latrine. students had to walk to the far away river to get water. the school officials had made many complains to their higher authorities and had give an application to the district commissioner but the problem persisted. the villagers too ignored the proble. one student informed cc vinti viswakarma about the problems and she made a video after discusing the matter with school authorities. vinti screened the video bacl to students, teachers and the village head. the village head assured some action within 15 days but he did nothing. after 2 months the cc followed up again and a boundary wall built around the school but later it was destroyed by the villagers from one side as they wanted a temple nearby to be included within the boundary. presently, there's a court case between the villagers and the school authorities.

impact_plan: prepare the application with the community in the name of block development officer.

impact_achieved_description: shanti wrote the application in the name of pey jal vibhag. department sent the mechanic and the hand pumps were repaired. the video was produced in the month of april and impact was done in the month of may 2015.. the handpump in tati village has been broken and this was the case for the last six months. the video was made by the cc with the help of the mahila mandal in the village. the women wrote a letter to the water and sanitation board. the cc has taken the application to the board and the video was screened in the village and to the board members. after 4-5 days all the three hand pumps were fixed. the change happened in april. . the handpump in tati village has been broken and this was the case for the last six months. the video was made by the cc with the help of the mahila mandal in the village. the women wrote a letter to the water and sanitation board. the cc has taken the application to the board and the video was screened in the village and to the board members. after 4-5 days all the three hand pumps were fixed. the change happened in april.

impact_achieved_description: district bokaro prakhand gomeia panchayat gomeia's dhobi tola's dhobi tola's dhobi tola has a chapakal, which has been used for the last 3 months because of the break of the chapakal. chapakal ke maramat nahi hue fer manju raj ne es samasaya ke upar video banaya. women like sarita devi or others make curry from their own house or eat paneer. the video was made in the name of marriage with the help of bad community and people gathered in the marriage for 6 months after the marriage was sent to the staff. english: a handpump in dhobi tola village of gomia panchayat was not working for 3 months. it was mainly the women who fetched water from the handpump. the main chain of the handpump was broken and the villagers were somehow managing to fetch the water from the handpump. villagers had several times informed the officials regarding the issue but they never repaired it. cc manju filmed a video on the issue. the cc then held a community meeting where they all decided to submit applications to the water department. in the following days they submitted the application. 6 months after submitting the application the handpump repairperson came to the village and repaired the handpump.
impact_plan: video bana kar samuday or bivag ke adhikari ke pass screening karna or awaden dena hai.

impact_achieved_description: 40 handpumps of the panchayat of chatrutand block of dhanbad district were found to be in bad condition since last one year. the handpump of panchayat sacivalay was also damaged. halima ne video made in march month. ish video ko banane se pahle logon se tarah tarah ki baten sunne ko mil rahi thi ki gaon wale itne dino se paryas kar rahe hain toh abhi tak kuch nahi ho paya hai toh aap kya kar sakte hain. then halima ne apna video samuday me screening kiya aur pani ke mudde par video banane ke baat rakhi. bhatdih ke logon ne kaha ki agar aapko lag raha hai ki aap kuch kar sakte hain toh ek paryas aap aap bhi sakte hain. ish video ko 16 march 2016 ko bankakar bhejne ke baad halima ne 22-03-2016 ko 22-03-2016 ko saath ek baithak rakhi. in the form of halima, there is no problem with the villagers, and there is no need to give support to the people. baghmara vidha sabha's vidhayak gave dhullu mahto aur usne sakko gambhirta se lete huwet karte karte huwe borewell dilaya dilaya se water problem. in bringing badlao, our village's sahiya shobha devi, sevika kalyani rai and sakcharta karmi asha hazari, vipul hazarine were assisted. badlao aane se us gaon ke 140 parivaar ko labh huwa evam us panchayat ke aur 2 gaon tetuliya and belakhonda bhi borewell ki suvidha di gayi english: 40 hand pumps were not functional since the past year in dhanbad district chatrutand block. people had difficulty in drinking water. halima had made a video on this issue in the month of march. she showed the video to the villagers and had a discussion. everyone agreed to try one more time to solve the problem. halima conducted a meeting with villagers on 22-03-2016 where she asked for their support. people submitted a collective application to baghmara vidhan sabha mla dhullu mahto. he took the matter seriously and ordered to install a bore well to solve the crisis. shobha devi, sevika kalyani rai, asha hazari, and vipul hazarine helped in bringing change. 140 families get water from the bore well. villages, tetuliya & belakhonda also got bore wells.

impact_plan: video bena kar screening karna aur bivag me awaden dena hai.

target_official: tej kumar hassa, bdo, jamua, giridih

impact_achieved_description: beena bharti ke dawara pani ke samasay ke upar 1 video bena jisme samasaya th 1 chapakal school ke campus me aur usmay 100 log paani bharnay jatay hai jiske karan kafi bher ho jata hai aur logo ko kafi dare line me lagay rahna parta hai aur chapakal i took out a lot of water. isu video benane ke 2 month ke bad he school me bondry lag gai aur alag se ak nay chapakal ke boring ho gai. in this change, i have been the first to help bharti. jeske karan yaha ke samuday kafi khus hai. english: there is only one handpump among 100 villagers in argudih village of nawadih panchayat, jamuva block, giridih district which was located in school campus. villagers had to face problem especially in summers because the pump had pulled less water during that season. thus drinking water was scarce in the village. consequently a few villagers had to fetch water from a very long distance. cc has been filmed a video on this issue. 2 months later a new borewell was drilled for the hnadpump and a new handpump was set up in the village. also a school boundary was constructed so that the school handpump be used only for school purpose.

impact_plan: by going with the community, there is a reward for separation.

impact_achieved_description: process- basanti huni purty ne urikel village me jakar gramsabha me apna parichay bataya aur apna video ke bare me baat kahi. gramsabha ne kaha ki aap is par video banaye aur kisi tarah ka dikat hogi toh ham sabhi mada karne ke liye ready hain. write applications for making videos and collect them in pey jal vibhag. basanti ne pey jal vibahg me phone karke avgat karayi se samsya. 2 times like alone he is gayi in the division. murhu block me till the house chapakal ke samanne hai unka usne detail likhwaya. his detail was also given in the district office. he got the help of anand kumar singh, executive engineer of the phd of the district office. got the support of the villagers too. aur gaon wale labh le rahe hain. english: 6 out of 7 handpumps in urikel village consisiting of 400 residents were nonfunctional since 3 years. the villagers had submitted the application for repair twice but the officials took no action. vilalgers had to depend on well water for daily needs. the well water was not safe for drinking. basanti hunni purty introduced herself at the gram sabha in urikel village and spoke to them about the video. gram sabha assured her that she can make the video and would receive any help if required. after making the video she wrote an application to the drinking water department. basanti called the drinking water department and informed them about the issue. she even went to the department twice. she gave them the written details of the house next to the tube well in murhu block. she gave these details to the district department as well. the executive engineer anand kumar singh of the district public health department gave her support. the villagers also received support and now they are getting benefits.
impact_plan: meeting with community and involve mukhiya.

impact_achieved_description: cc has raised the issue of drinking water facility inside the anganwadi centre where 32 children were getting their nutritional food from one village. cc has submitted an application to the department as well as she has called on phone and sent several sms and wa message to the concerned department officials, after that cc also sent the issue in local newspaper which they have carried it. another cc kamal purty also helped the cc in getting impact on this issues  english: gaigai village, indpiri panchayat, murhu block, khunti district didnt ahve any drinking water facility for 2 years due to which the anganwadi people had to rely on dirty ground water. cc being associated with the community filmed a video on this issue. after discussing the isssue with community , cc sent a application for drinking water facility to department officials and sent several messeges and video to other related official sof department. cc made it possible teh issue gets published in a local newspaper. within a few months anganwadi was provided with drinking water facility. a new handpump was installed within anganwadi premises.

there are 6 handpumps in gaigai village of indpiri panchayat in murhu block of khunti district and they have been in bad shape for 2-3 years. date-14-02-2017 ko handpump repair huwa hai. impact process- women come to their grandmother in the morning to bring water, they have a place to meet and a place to share the rest of the world. in that place basanti started repairing chapakal because the water was dry. basanti ka video banane se pehle se ho raha tha. on 7-4-2016 phd, khunti's father got rid of the problem by phone. on 9-4-2016, going to murhu block, karamchari ke paas jinke ghar ke saamne handpumps hain unka naam likhwane ke liye bole. basanti also did not give the details of his area. uske baad bhi kuch action nahi liya gaya. published in the newspaper on 6-9-2016 from the newspaper of dainik jagran. par kuch nahi ho raha tha, application bhi likhe the par koi karwai nahi ho raha tha. on 14-02-2017, basanti phd, khunti's district karyalay application's receiving doctor went and started talking about her and her village. executive engineer, anand kumar singh called murhu's pey jal division on the phone and asked to repair the handpump as soon as possible. usi din block se handpump repair ke liye mistri sabko bheja gaya aur we log gaye 14-02-2017 ko gaon ka handpump repair kiya. 36 families are getting their benefits. out of six handpumps 3 have been repaired and are working while officiasl ahve approved the reapir of remaining three handpumps that would be functional soon. english: 6 handpumps in gagai village of indipiri panchayat of murhu block were not working since two and a half years. the women had to fetch the water from the village well which was drying up faster. cc filmed video on this issue. she then called up the public health department officer to inform about the problem. the story was published in "dainik jagran" a local newsdaily, but nothing happened. application was also given but nothing was happening still. on february 2017 cc basanti went to the public health department, khunti district with the receiving of the application and told them about the village and herself. executive engineer, anand kumar singh called the drinking water department and asked them to repair the handpump immediately. the same day the labors were sent from the block to repair the hand pump. it was repaired on same day .out of six handpumps 3 have been repaired and are working while officials have approved the repair of remaining three handpumps that would be functional soon.
impact_plan: by making a video, screening the beach of the community and making awaden in the community.

impact_achieved_description: vinati viswakarma made an issue video on sanitation, the issue was that - kabrabut village of bangakhalar panchayat of domchanch block of koderma district has 1 chapakal which is in bad condition since last 7 months. there are 29 families living in our village. these people eat donkey's dirty water - they use it for pain. video banane ke duran hi unhone sangram jo ek sanstha hai usko involve kiya. video shooting pura karne ke baad vinti ne video clip domchanch block ke bdo narayan ram ko dikhayi aur unhone turant pahal karne ki baat kahi. prabhat khabar also shared the story with koderma's bureau chief vikash kumar. those who have read the issue seriously have given great attention to it in their newspaper and published it in their newspaper. after looking at the newspaper, the dc of koderma took a song and ordered the department to repair the handpump. after 3 days of our order, the residents of gaon were served water. abhi karib 300 grams iska labh le rahe hain. english: vinati vishwakarma had made a video on the issue of sanitation. the problem was that koderma district domchanch block bangakhalar panchayat, kabrabut village had 1 tube well which was not working since 7 months. 29 families stay in that village. the villagers consume dirty water collected in the hole. they involved an organization named sangram during the video process. after shooting the video, vinti showed it to block development officer narayan ram and he immediately spoke about the application process. after that she shared the story with the bureau chief of prabhat khabar koderma vikash kumar. he took the issue seriously and published the story in the newspaper. after reading the news the district commissioner of koderma noticed the crisis and ordered the department to fix the hand pump. after his orders passed the hand pump was repaired in 3 days and the villagers were getting water. now 300 villagers are getting water from the hand pump.
impact_plan: meet bdo and show the clip of the video

impact_achieved_description: the video has not been sent to the community's beach meeting, but there has been no response to the head of the community it is necessary to meet with the chief once after 1 wars; let's go back with the community. for 4 days bad chapakal karne wale gaao aaye aur chapakal chak karke karne kar deye. there is a lot of happiness in the community because of the kindness of chapakal. english: two handpumps are not working for 6 months at kundgari chagnitoli of bargaon panchayat of senha block. 36 persons are affected by this. in summer the well gets dried. cc filmed a video on this issue and held a community meeting. in thsi meeting an application was written down by community members and was handed over to village head. a year passed but the village head did nothing to repair the hand pump. villagers kept following with the village head regarding the issue. the once again the villagers went collectively to meet the village head. this time he assured taht he'll send repairperson to fix the handpump. 4 days later handpump repairperson came to the village and repaired teh handpumps. now villagers have access to clean and safe drinking water nearby.
impact_plan: have the meeting in community and write the application in the name of mukhiya prakash oraon.

impact_achieved_description: kaika village is nestled in the middle of forest at about 15 kms from nh75e highway in bandgaon block, west singhbhum district. the village consisting of 60 families had to drink the unsafe water from nearby pond since there were no other drinking water resources available. there is a hand pump in the village but it belongs to the school. school authorities shouted at villagers whenever they fetched water from it, thus villagers kept away from the shool handpump. cc filmed a video on this issue and screened this video the to the public health department official in preasence of district panchayat head. after watching the video the official assured of permanent solution as soon as possible. 5 months later a handpump was installed in the village. villagers now have access to clean drinking water. ********************************************************** ********************************************************** ***** one day xavier was passing through the village of hmasay kaika. usne kuch milawon ko cuwan se paani ke liye paani lete deka. pani ganda aur matmaila lag raha tha. xavier ne unlogon se pucha - kya aapke yahan aapke gaon me swach pani ka koi dusra source i.e. handpump, well nahi hai? unhone kaha- nahi hai. by doing the weekly meetings of the village, i came to know through the medium that there is only one handpump in the village, which is near the school and because of its failure, the people of the village are not able to take water from our handpump. tab xavier made a video whose body is menjari as the main character. is video ko junior engineer phd badgaon, sunil baxla ko dikhaya. during the screening deepak bara from vv, zila parishad member joshphin hamsay, robin hapadgara of konseya village sat in the. after watching the video, baxla ji said – there is a problem of water in the vast areas and we will try to remove it soon. screening was also done in the community. badlao aa gaya in august 2016. deepak bara, hoshphin hamsay, robin hadgara and gramsabha helped in this change.
target_official: pay jal evam swachta vibhag-junior engineer

impact_achieved_description: issue:- zilla west singhbhung prakhand bandgao panchayat panchayat sawneia garam heramda ke dukhni mundi ko aapnay gao ki 2 chapakal pichlay ki 1 years se ek 3 years se kharap hua hai hai kareon 1km far ke water lana hai hai body ke samay kamay jata hai hai aur esi karan subha apna beta ko samay par school nahi veg pati hai ya samasaya enkay alawa es gao ke 75 log pravawith hai. impact process:- xavier hamsay ke paas gaon ke us gaon ke log aye aur nalkup bad hona ki samasya ki paas rakhi xavier ke paas rakhi. xavier ne junior engineer anil baxla se baat ki uske din ke baad xavier unse meetne ke liye gaye. je said that we are living in mistry bandgaon and we can go to meet him. xavier again came into contact with the handpump mystery. usne kaha ki old handpump ka repair ke liye usme ek plate lagta hai wo abhi uske paas available nahi hai jaise milta hai wo kar denge. then xavier met je again for pipe. kuch din ke baad je ne pipe ko uplabdh kar diya. mr. pipe ko lekar went to heremda gaon gaye and repaired handpumps. abhi gramin iska istemaal kar rahe hain. english: dhukni mundu of district west singhbhum, block bandgao panchayat sawneia village heramda had to travel 1 km far away to get water because the 2 tube wells in her village were not functional since 1 year and the other was not working since the past 3 years . as a result, she was unable to send her son to school. there were 75 such people facing the same crisis. some of the villagers met with xavier hamsay and told him about the problem. xavier hamsay spoke to junior engineer anil baxla and met him the same day. the junior engineer said that the labor stays in bandgaon itself and he can meet. xavier then met with the hand pump worker. he said that in order to repair the old hand pump he needed a plate which was not available. when he gets the plate he will fix it. xavier again met the junior engineer for the pipe. after a few days the pipe was provided. the repair man went with the pipe to heremda village and fixed the hand pumps. now the villagers are able to use the hand pumps.
impact_plan: beach screening of the community by making video and giving awaden in divorce.

impact_achieved_description: last may 2017, 4 out of 5 hand cranks were damaged in bada basti of pandrasali toli chonsai of matkobeda under khuntpani block of west singhbhum district. due to which sini purti had to go down 500 meters to fetch water even though there was a hand pump in front of the house. along with my family, around 200 people from 37 families in the village were affected by this problem. to solve this problem, 2 women groups of the village took a decision in the meeting and applied to the department. after that kamal purti was told about this and asked to apply. after that i gave written information to kamal purti department. no mechanic was sent even after a week of written application. then the women of the women's group were going to get the repair done by a private mechanic by donating money. contacted the department again with gangaram purti and lakshmi purti. the department sent a mechanic after one month in the month of july and all the four hand tools have been repaired. right now, after repair, all 4 chapakals are safe and the whole village is using them. english: the 4 water handpumps of the total 5 were not functional in bada basti, pandrasali toli choisai, matkobeda, khuntpani block, west singhbum district as a result of which 36 families had to fetch the muddy water from nearby pond 1 km away. cc himself being from the same village was facing the issue of drinking water. cc held community meeting with the village women and discussed the issue. an application was written in the name of engineer of water department and submitted in following days. there was no response from official even when a week passed. the women decided to solve the issue themselves and collected money needed to employ technician to fix handpumps. cc and women thought to approach officials once again before doing it themselves. a fresh application was submitted to official by cc in presence of community. a month later technicians arrived in the village and repaired all the handpumps. the villagers have the access to clean drinking water now.
impact_plan: i have made an application and have to give it to the people.

impact_achieved_description: five elderly women, who are all eligible for old age pension, in deopahar village in sahebganj district are 'dead' on the governments record and thus have not gotten their pension since october 2013. cc shikha paharin interviewed all these five women and have shown the officials that their records are obviously wrong. four out of the five women have started getting their pension because of shikha's video and follow up. she is working on the last remaining case.
